    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "But if ye had known what\nthis meaneth, I will have mercy, and not sacrifice, ye would not have condemned the guiltless."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "For the Son of man is Lord even of the sabbath day."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "And when he was departed thence, he went into their synagogue:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "And, behold, there was a man which had\nhis hand withered. And they asked him, saying, Is it lawful to heal on the sabbath days? that they might accuse him."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "And he said unto them,\nWhat man shall there be among you, that shall have one sheep, and if it fall into a pit on the sabbath day, will he not lay hold on it, and lift\nit out?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "How much then is a man better than a sheep? Wherefore it is lawful to do well on the sabbath days."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "Then saith he to the man,\nStretch forth thine hand. And he stretched\nit forth; and it was restored whole, like as the other."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "Then the Pharisees went out, and held a council against him, how they might destroy him."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "But when Jesus knew\nit, he withdrew himself from thence: and great multitudes followed him, and he healed them all;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "And charged them that they should not make him known:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "That it might be fulfilled which was spoken by Esaias the prophet, saying,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "Behold my servant, whom I have chosen; my beloved, in whom my soul is well pleased: I will put my spirit upon him, and he shall shew judgment to the Gentiles."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "He shall not strive, nor cry; neither shall any man hear his voice in the streets."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "A bruised reed shall he not break, and smoking flax shall he not quench, till he send forth judgment unto victory."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "And in his name shall the Gentiles trust."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "Then was brought unto him one possessed with a devil, blind, and dumb: and he healed him, insomuch that the blind and dumb both spake and saw."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "And all the people were amazed, and said, Is not this the son of David?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "But when the Pharisees heard\nit, they said, This\nfellow\n doth not cast out devils, but by Beelzebub the prince of the devils."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 25,
    "text": "And Jesus knew their thoughts, and said unto them,\nEvery kingdom divided against itself is brought to desolation; and every city or house divided against itself shall not stand:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 26,
    "text": "And if Satan cast out Satan, he is divided against himself; how shall then his kingdom stand?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 27,
    "text": "And if I by Beelzebub cast out devils, by whom do your children cast\nthem out? therefore they shall be your judges."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 28,
    "text": "But if I cast out devils by the Spirit of God, then the kingdom of God is come unto you."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 29,
    "text": "Or else how can one enter into a strong man’s house, and spoil his goods, except he first bind the strong man? and then he will spoil his house."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 30,
    "text": "He that is not with me is against me; and he that gathereth not with me scattereth abroad."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 31,
    "text": "Wherefore I say unto you, All manner of sin and blasphemy shall be forgiven unto men: but the blasphemy\nagainst the\nHoly\n Ghost shall not be forgiven unto men."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 32,
    "text": "And whosoever speaketh a word against the Son of man, it shall be forgiven him: but whosoever speaketh against the Holy Ghost, it shall not be forgiven him, neither in this world, neither in the\nworld to come."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 33,
    "text": "Either make the tree good, and his fruit good; or else make the tree corrupt, and his fruit corrupt: for the tree is known by\nhis fruit."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 34,
    "text": "O generation of vipers, how can ye, being evil, speak good things? for out of the abundance of the heart the mouth speaketh."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 35,
    "text": "A good man out of the good treasure of the heart bringeth forth good things: and an evil man out of the evil treasure bringeth forth evil things."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 36,
    "text": "But I say unto you, That every idle word that men shall speak, they shall give account thereof in the day of judgment."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 37,
    "text": "For by thy words thou shalt be justified, and by thy words thou shalt be condemned."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 38,
    "text": "Then certain of the scribes and of the Pharisees answered, saying, Master, we would see a sign from thee."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 39,
    "text": "But he answered and said unto them,\nAn evil and adulterous generation seeketh after a sign; and there shall no sign be given to it, but the sign of the prophet Jonas:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 40,
    "text": "For as Jonas was three days and three nights in the whale’s belly; so shall the Son of man be three days and three nights in the heart of the earth."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 41,
    "text": "The men of Nineveh shall rise in judgment with this generation, and shall condemn it: because they repented at the preaching of Jonas; and, behold, a greater than Jonas\nis here."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 42,
    "text": "The queen of the south shall rise up in the judgment with this generation, and shall condemn it: for she came from the uttermost parts of the earth to hear the wisdom of Solomon; and, behold, a greater than Solomon\nis here."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 43,
    "text": "When the unclean spirit is gone out of a man, he walketh through dry places, seeking rest, and findeth none."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 44,
    "text": "Then he saith, I will return into my house from whence I came out; and when he is come, he findeth\nit empty, swept, and garnished."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 45,
    "text": "Then goeth he, and taketh with himself seven other spirits more wicked than himself, and they enter in and dwell there: and the last\nstate of that man is worse than the first. Even so shall it be also unto this wicked generation."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 46,
    "text": "While he yet talked to the people, behold,\nhis mother and his brethren stood without, desiring to speak with him."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 47,
    "text": "Then one said unto him, Behold, thy mother and thy brethren stand without, desiring to speak with thee."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 48,
    "text": "But he answered and said unto him that told him,\nWho is my mother? and who are my brethren?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 49,
    "text": "And he stretched forth his hand toward his disciples, and said,\nBehold my mother and my brethren!"
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 50,
    "text": "For whosoever shall do the will of my Father which is in heaven, the same is my brother, and sister, and mother."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "The same day went Jesus out of the house, and sat by the sea side."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "And great multitudes were gathered together unto him, so that he went into a ship, and sat; and the whole multitude stood on the shore."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "And he spake many things unto them in parables, saying,\nBehold, a sower went forth to sow;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "And when he sowed, some\nseeds fell by the way side, and the fowls came and devoured them up:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "Some fell upon stony places, where they had not much earth: and forthwith they sprung up, because they had no deepness of earth:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "And when the sun was up, they were scorched; and because they had no root, they withered away."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "And some fell among thorns; and the thorns sprung up, and choked them:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "But other fell into good ground, and brought forth fruit, some an hundredfold, some sixtyfold, some thirtyfold."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "Who hath ears to hear, let him hear."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "And the disciples came, and said unto him, Why speakest thou unto them in parables?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "He answered and said unto them,\nBecause it is given unto you to know the mysteries of the kingdom of heaven, but to them it is not given."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "For whosoever hath, to him shall be given, and he shall have more abundance: but whosoever hath not, from him shall be taken away even that he hath."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "Therefore speak I to them in parables: because they seeing see not; and hearing they hear not, neither do they understand."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "And in them is fulfilled the prophecy of Esaias, which saith, By hearing ye shall hear, and shall not understand; and seeing ye shall see, and shall not perceive:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "For this people’s heart is waxed gross, and\ntheir ears are dull of hearing, and their eyes they have closed; lest at any time they should see with\ntheir eyes, and hear with\ntheir ears, and should understand with\ntheir\n heart, and should be converted, and I should heal them."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "But blessed\nare your eyes, for they see: and your ears, for they hear."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "For verily I say unto you, That many prophets and righteous\nmen have desired to see\nthose things which ye see, and have not seen\nthem; and to hear\nthose things which ye hear, and have not heard\nthem."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "Hear ye therefore the parable of the sower."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "When any one heareth the word of the kingdom, and understandeth\nit not, then cometh the wicked\none, and catcheth away that which was sown in his heart. This is he which received seed by the way side."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "But he that received the seed into stony places, the same is he that heareth the word, and anon with joy receiveth it;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "Yet hath he not root in himself, but dureth for a while: for when tribulation or persecution ariseth because of the word, by and by he is offended."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "He also that received seed among the thorns is he that heareth the word; and the care of this world, and the deceitfulness of riches, choke the word, and he becometh unfruitful."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "But he that received seed into the good ground is he that heareth the word, and understandeth\nit; which also beareth fruit, and bringeth forth, some an hundredfold, some sixty, some thirty."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "Another parable put he forth unto them, saying,\nThe kingdom of heaven is likened unto a man which sowed good seed in his field:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 25,
    "text": "But while men slept, his enemy came and sowed tares among the wheat, and went his way."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 26,
    "text": "But when the blade was sprung up, and brought forth fruit, then appeared the tares also."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 27,
    "text": "So the servants of the householder came and said unto him, Sir, didst not thou sow good seed in thy field? from whence then hath it tares?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 28,
    "text": "He said unto them, An enemy hath done this. The servants said unto him, Wilt thou then that we go and gather them up?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 29,
    "text": "But he said, Nay; lest while ye gather up the tares, ye root up also the wheat with them."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 30,
    "text": "Let both grow together until the harvest: and in the time of harvest I will say to the reapers, Gather ye together first the tares, and bind them in bundles to burn them: but gather the wheat into my barn."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 31,
    "text": "Another parable put he forth unto them, saying,\nThe kingdom of heaven is like to a grain of mustard seed, which a man took, and sowed in his field:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 32,
    "text": "Which indeed is the least of all seeds: but when it is grown, it is the greatest among herbs, and becometh a tree, so that the birds of the air come and lodge in the branches thereof."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 33,
    "text": "Another parable spake he unto them;\nThe kingdom of heaven is like unto leaven, which a woman took, and hid in three measures of meal, till the whole was leavened."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 34,
    "text": "All these things spake Jesus unto the multitude in parables; and without a parable spake he not unto them:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 35,
    "text": "That it might be fulfilled which was spoken by the prophet, saying, I will open my mouth in parables; I will utter things which have been kept secret from the foundation of the world."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 36,
    "text": "Then Jesus sent the multitude away, and went into the house: and his disciples came unto him, saying, Declare unto us the parable of the tares of the field."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 37,
    "text": "He answered and said unto them,\nHe that soweth the good seed is the Son of man;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 38,
    "text": "The field is the world; the good seed are the children of the kingdom; but the tares are the children of the wicked\none;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 39,
    "text": "The enemy that sowed them is the devil; the harvest is the end of the world; and the reapers are the angels."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 40,
    "text": "As therefore the tares are gathered and burned in the fire; so shall it be in the end of this world."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 41,
    "text": "The Son of man shall send forth his angels, and they shall gather out of his kingdom all things that offend, and them which do iniquity;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 42,
    "text": "And shall cast them into a furnace of fire: there shall be wailing and gnashing of teeth."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 43,
    "text": "Then shall the righteous shine forth as the sun in the kingdom of their Father. Who hath ears to hear, let him hear."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 44,
    "text": "Again, the kingdom of heaven is like unto treasure hid in a field; the which when a man hath found, he hideth, and for joy thereof goeth and selleth all that he hath, and buyeth that field."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 45,
    "text": "Again, the kingdom of heaven is like unto a merchant man, seeking goodly pearls:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 46,
    "text": "Who, when he had found one pearl of great price, went and sold all that he had, and bought it."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 47,
    "text": "Again, the kingdom of heaven is like unto a net, that was cast into the sea, and gathered of every kind:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 48,
    "text": "Which, when it was full, they drew to shore, and sat down, and gathered the good into vessels, but cast the bad away."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 49,
    "text": "So shall it be at the end of the world: the angels shall come forth, and sever the wicked from among the just,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 50,
    "text": "And shall cast them into the furnace of fire: there shall be wailing and gnashing of teeth."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 51,
    "text": "Jesus saith unto them,\nHave ye understood all these things?\n They say unto him, Yea, Lord."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 52,
    "text": "Then said he unto them,\nTherefore every scribe\nwhich is\n instructed unto the kingdom of heaven is like unto a man\nthat is an householder, which bringeth forth out of his treasure\nthings new and old."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 53,
    "text": "And it came to pass,\nthat when Jesus had finished these parables, he departed thence."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 54,
    "text": "And when he was come into his own country, he taught them in their synagogue, insomuch that they were astonished, and said, Whence hath this\nman this wisdom, and\nthese mighty works?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 55,
    "text": "Is not this the carpenter’s son? is not his mother called Mary? and his brethren, James, and Joses, and Simon, and Judas?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 56,
    "text": "And his sisters, are they not all with us? Whence then hath this\nman all these things?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 57,
    "text": "And they were offended in him. But Jesus said unto them, A prophet is not without honour, save in his own country, and in his own house."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 58,
    "text": "And he did not many mighty works there because of their unbelief."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "At that time Herod the tetrarch heard of the fame of Jesus,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "And said unto his servants, This is John the Baptist; he is risen from the dead; and therefore mighty works do shew forth themselves in him."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "For Herod had laid hold on John, and bound him, and put\nhim\n in prison for Herodias’ sake, his brother Philip’s wife."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "For John said unto him, It is not lawful for thee to have her."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "And when he would have put him to death, he feared the multitude, because they counted him as a prophet."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "But when Herod’s birthday was kept, the daughter of Herodias danced before them, and pleased Herod."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "Whereupon he promised with an oath to give her whatsoever she would ask."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "And she, being before instructed of her mother, said, Give me here John Baptist’s head in a charger."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "And the king was sorry: nevertheless for the oath’s sake, and them which sat with him at meat, he commanded\nit to be given\nher."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "And he sent, and beheaded John in the prison."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "And his head was brought in a charger, and given to the damsel: and she brought\nit to her mother."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "And his disciples came, and took up the body, and buried it, and went and told Jesus."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "When Jesus heard\nof it, he departed thence by ship into a desert place apart: and when the people had heard\nthereof, they followed him on foot out of the cities."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "And Jesus went forth, and saw a great multitude, and was moved with compassion toward them, and he healed their sick."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "And when it was evening, his disciples came to him, saying, This is a desert place, and the time is now past; send the multitude away, that they may go into the villages, and buy themselves victuals."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "But Jesus said unto them,\nThey need not depart; give ye them to eat."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "And they say unto him, We have here but five loaves, and two fishes."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "He said,\nBring them hither to me."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "And he commanded the multitude to sit down on the grass, and took the five loaves, and the two fishes, and looking up to heaven, he blessed, and brake, and gave the loaves to\nhis disciples, and the disciples to the multitude."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "And they did all eat, and were filled: and they took up of the fragments that remained twelve baskets full."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "And they that had eaten were about five thousand men, beside women and children."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "And straightway Jesus constrained his disciples to get into a ship, and to go before him unto the other side, while he sent the multitudes away."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "And when he had sent the multitudes away, he went up into a mountain apart to pray: and when the evening was come, he was there alone."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "But the ship was now in the midst of the sea, tossed with waves: for the wind was contrary."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 25,
    "text": "And in the fourth watch of the night Jesus went unto them, walking on the sea."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 26,
    "text": "And when the disciples saw him walking on the sea, they were troubled, saying, It is a spirit; and they cried out for fear."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 27,
    "text": "But straightway Jesus spake unto them, saying,\nBe of good cheer; it is I; be not afraid."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 28,
    "text": "And Peter answered him and said, Lord, if it be thou, bid me come unto thee on the water."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 29,
    "text": "And he said,\nCome. And when Peter was come down out of the ship, he walked on the water, to go to Jesus."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 30,
    "text": "But when he saw the wind boisterous, he was afraid; and beginning to sink, he cried, saying, Lord, save me."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 31,
    "text": "And immediately Jesus stretched forth\nhis hand, and caught him, and said unto him,\nO thou of little faith, wherefore didst thou doubt?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 32,
    "text": "And when they were come into the ship, the wind ceased."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 33,
    "text": "Then they that were in the ship came and worshipped him, saying, Of a truth thou art the Son of God."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 34,
    "text": "And when they were gone over, they came into the land of Gennesaret."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 35,
    "text": "And when the men of that place had knowledge of him, they sent out into all that country round about, and brought unto him all that were diseased;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 36,
    "text": "And besought him that they might only touch the hem of his garment: and as many as touched were made perfectly whole."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "Then came to Jesus scribes and Pharisees, which were of Jerusalem, saying,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "Why do thy disciples transgress the tradition of the elders? for they wash not their hands when they eat bread."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "But he answered and said unto them,\nWhy do ye also transgress the commandment of God by your tradition?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "For God commanded, saying, Honour thy father and mother: and, He that curseth father or mother, let him die the death."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "But ye say, Whosoever shall say to\nhis father or\nhis mother,\nIt is a gift, by whatsoever thou mightest be profited by me;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "And honour not his father or his mother,\nhe shall be free.\n Thus have ye made the commandment of God of none effect by your tradition."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "Ye hypocrites, well did Esaias prophesy of you, saying,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "This people draweth nigh unto me with their mouth, and honoureth me with\ntheir lips; but their heart is far from me."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "But in vain they do worship me, teaching\nfor doctrines the commandments of men."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "And he called the multitude, and said unto them,\nHear, and understand:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "Not that which goeth into the mouth defileth a man; but that which cometh out of the mouth, this defileth a man."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "Then came his disciples, and said unto him, Knowest thou that the Pharisees were offended, after they heard this saying?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "But he answered and said,\nEvery plant, which my heavenly Father hath not planted, shall be rooted up."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "Let them alone: they be blind leaders of the blind. And if the blind lead the blind, both shall fall into the ditch."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "Then answered Peter and said unto him, Declare unto us this parable."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "And Jesus said,\nAre ye also yet without understanding?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "Do not ye yet understand, that whatsoever entereth in at the mouth goeth into the belly, and is cast out into the draught?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "But those things which proceed out of the mouth come forth from the heart; and they defile the man."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "For out of the heart proceed evil thoughts, murders, adulteries, fornications, thefts, false witness, blasphemies:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "These are\nthe things which defile a man: but to eat with unwashen hands defileth not a man."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "Then Jesus went thence, and departed into the coasts of Tyre and Sidon."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "And, behold, a woman of Canaan came out of the same coasts, and cried unto him, saying, Have mercy on me, O Lord,\nthou Son of David; my daughter is grievously vexed with a devil."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "But he answered her not a word. And his disciples came and besought him, saying, Send her away; for she crieth after us."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "But he answered and said,\nI am not sent but unto the lost sheep of the house of Israel."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 25,
    "text": "Then came she and worshipped him, saying, Lord, help me."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 26,
    "text": "But he answered and said,\nIt is not meet to take the children’s bread, and to cast\nit to dogs."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 27,
    "text": "And she said, Truth, Lord: yet the dogs eat of the crumbs which fall from their masters’ table."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 28,
    "text": "Then Jesus answered and said unto her,\nO woman, great\nis\n thy faith: be it unto thee even as thou wilt. And her daughter was made whole from that very hour."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 29,
    "text": "And Jesus departed from thence, and came nigh unto the sea of Galilee; and went up into a mountain, and sat down there."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 30,
    "text": "And great multitudes came unto him, having with them\nthose that were lame, blind, dumb, maimed, and many others, and cast them down at Jesus’ feet; and he healed them:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 31,
    "text": "Insomuch that the multitude wondered, when they saw the dumb to speak, the maimed to be whole, the lame to walk, and the blind to see: and they glorified the God of Israel."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 32,
    "text": "Then Jesus called his disciples\nunto him, and said,\nI have compassion on the multitude, because they continue with me now three days, and have nothing to eat: and I will not send them away fasting, lest they faint in the way."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 33,
    "text": "And his disciples say unto him, Whence should we have so much bread in the wilderness, as to fill so great a multitude?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 34,
    "text": "And Jesus saith unto them,\nHow many loaves have ye? And they said, Seven, and a few little fishes."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 35,
    "text": "And he commanded the multitude to sit down on the ground."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 36,
    "text": "And he took the seven loaves and the fishes, and gave thanks, and brake\nthem, and gave to his disciples, and the disciples to the multitude."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 37,
    "text": "And they did all eat, and were filled: and they took up of the broken\nmeat that was left seven baskets full."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 38,
    "text": "And they that did eat were four thousand men, beside women and children."
  },
  {
    "book": "Matthew",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 39,
    "text": "And he sent away the multitude, and took ship, and came into the coasts of Magdala,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "And they came over unto the other side of the sea, into the country of the Gadarenes."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "And when he was come out of the ship, immediately there met him out of the tombs a man with an unclean spirit,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "Who had\nhis dwelling among the tombs; and no man could bind him, no, not with chains:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "Because that he had been often bound with fetters and chains, and the chains had been plucked asunder by him, and the fetters broken in pieces: neither could any\nman tame him."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "And always, night and day, he was in the mountains, and in the tombs, crying, and cutting himself with stones."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "But when he saw Jesus afar off, he ran and worshipped him,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "And cried with a loud voice, and said, What have I to do with thee, Jesus,\nthou Son of the most high God? I adjure thee by God, that thou torment me not."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "For he said unto him,\nCome out of the man,\nthou unclean spirit."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "And he asked him,\nWhat\nis thy name? And he answered, saying, My name\nis Legion: for we are many."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "And he besought him much that he would not send them away out of the country."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "Now there was there nigh unto the mountains a great herd of swine feeding."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "And all the devils besought him, saying, Send us into the swine, that we may enter into them."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "And forthwith Jesus gave them leave. And the unclean spirits went out, and entered into the swine: and the herd ran violently down a steep place into the sea, (they were about two thousand;) and were choked in the sea."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "And they that fed the swine fled, and told\nit in the city, and in the country. And they went out to see what it was that was done."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "And they come to Jesus, and see him that was possessed with the devil, and had the legion, sitting, and clothed, and in his right mind: and they were afraid."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "And they that saw\nit told them how it befell to him that was possessed with the devil, and\nalso concerning the swine."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "And they began to pray him to depart out of their coasts."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "And when he was come into the ship, he that had been possessed with the devil prayed him that he might be with him."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "Howbeit Jesus suffered him not, but saith unto him,\nGo home to thy friends, and tell them how great things the Lord hath done for thee, and hath had compassion on thee."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "And he departed, and began to publish in Decapolis how great things Jesus had done for him: and all\nmen did marvel."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "And when Jesus was passed over again by ship unto the other side, much people gathered unto him: and he was nigh unto the sea."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "And, behold, there cometh one of the rulers of the synagogue, Jairus by name; and when he saw him, he fell at his feet,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "And besought him greatly, saying, My little daughter lieth at the point of death:\nI pray thee, come and lay thy hands on her, that she may be healed; and she shall live."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "And\nJesus went with him; and much people followed him, and thronged him."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 25,
    "text": "And a certain woman, which had an issue of blood twelve years,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 26,
    "text": "And had suffered many things of many physicians, and had spent all that she had, and was nothing bettered, but rather grew worse,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 27,
    "text": "When she had heard of Jesus, came in the press behind, and touched his garment."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 28,
    "text": "For she said, If I may touch but his clothes, I shall be whole."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 29,
    "text": "And straightway the fountain of her blood was dried up; and she felt in\nher body that she was healed of that plague."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 30,
    "text": "And Jesus, immediately knowing in himself that virtue had gone out of him, turned him about in the press, and said,\nWho touched my clothes?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 31,
    "text": "And his disciples said unto him, Thou seest the multitude thronging thee, and sayest thou, Who touched me?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 32,
    "text": "And he looked round about to see her that had done this thing."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 33,
    "text": "But the woman fearing and trembling, knowing what was done in her, came and fell down before him, and told him all the truth."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 34,
    "text": "And he said unto her,\nDaughter, thy faith hath made thee whole; go in peace, and be whole of thy plague."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 35,
    "text": "While he yet spake, there came from the ruler of the synagogue’s\nhouse certain which said, Thy daughter is dead: why troublest thou the Master any further?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 36,
    "text": "As soon as Jesus heard the word that was spoken, he saith unto the ruler of the synagogue,\nBe not afraid, only believe."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 37,
    "text": "And he suffered no man to follow him, save Peter, and James, and John the brother of James."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 38,
    "text": "And he cometh to the house of the ruler of the synagogue, and seeth the tumult, and them that wept and wailed greatly."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 39,
    "text": "And when he was come in, he saith unto them,\nWhy make ye this ado, and weep? the damsel is not dead, but sleepeth."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 40,
    "text": "And they laughed him to scorn. But when he had put them all out, he taketh the father and the mother of the damsel, and them that were with him, and entereth in where the damsel was lying."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 41,
    "text": "And he took the damsel by the hand, and said unto her,\nTalitha cumi; which is, being interpreted,\nDamsel, I say unto thee,\narise."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 42,
    "text": "And straightway the damsel arose, and walked; for she was\nof the age of twelve years. And they were astonished with a great astonishment."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 43,
    "text": "And he charged them straitly that no man should know it; and commanded that something should be given her to eat."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "And he went out from thence, and came into his own country; and his disciples follow him."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "And when the sabbath day was come, he began to teach in the synagogue: and many hearing\nhim were astonished, saying, From whence hath this\nman these things? and what wisdom\nis this which is given unto him, that even such mighty works are wrought by his hands?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "Is not this the carpenter, the son of Mary, the brother of James, and Joses, and of Juda, and Simon? and are not his sisters here with us? And they were offended at him."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "But Jesus said unto them,\nA prophet is not without honour, but in his own country, and among his own kin, and in his own house."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "And he could there do no mighty work, save that he laid his hands upon a few sick folk, and healed\nthem."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "And he marvelled because of their unbelief. And he went round about the villages, teaching."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "And he called\nunto him the twelve, and began to send them forth by two and two; and gave them power over unclean spirits;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "And commanded them that they should take nothing for\ntheir\n journey, save a staff only; no scrip, no bread, no money in\ntheir\n purse:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "But\nbe shod with sandals; and not put on two coats."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "And he said unto them,\nIn what place soever ye enter into an house, there abide till ye depart from that place."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "And whosoever shall not receive you, nor hear you, when ye depart thence, shake off the dust under your feet for a testimony against them. Verily I say unto you, It shall be more tolerable for Sodom and Gomorrha in the day of judgment, than for that city."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "And they went out, and preached that men should repent."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "And they cast out many devils, and anointed with oil many that were sick, and healed\nthem."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "And king Herod heard\nof him; (for his name was spread abroad:) and he said, That John the Baptist was risen from the dead, and therefore mighty works do shew forth themselves in him."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "Others said, That it is Elias. And others said, That it is a prophet, or as one of the prophets."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "But when Herod heard\nthereof, he said, It is John, whom I beheaded: he is risen from the dead."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "For Herod himself had sent forth and laid hold upon John, and bound him in prison for Herodias’ sake, his brother Philip’s wife: for he had married her."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "For John had said unto Herod, It is not lawful for thee to have thy brother’s wife."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "Therefore Herodias had a quarrel against him, and would have killed him; but she could not:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "For Herod feared John, knowing that he was a just man and an holy, and observed him; and when he heard him, he did many things, and heard him gladly."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "And when a convenient day was come, that Herod on his birthday made a supper to his lords, high captains, and chief\nestates of Galilee;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "And when the daughter of the said Herodias came in, and danced, and pleased Herod and them that sat with him, the king said unto the damsel, Ask of me whatsoever thou wilt, and I will give\nit thee."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "And he sware unto her, Whatsoever thou shalt ask of me, I will give\nit thee, unto the half of my kingdom."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "And she went forth, and said unto her mother, What shall I ask? And she said, The head of John the Baptist."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 25,
    "text": "And she came in straightway with haste unto the king, and asked, saying, I will that thou give me by and by in a charger the head of John the Baptist."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 26,
    "text": "And the king was exceeding sorry;\nyet for his oath’s sake, and for their sakes which sat with him, he would not reject her."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 27,
    "text": "And immediately the king sent an executioner, and commanded his head to be brought: and he went and beheaded him in the prison,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 28,
    "text": "And brought his head in a charger, and gave it to the damsel: and the damsel gave it to her mother."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 29,
    "text": "And when his disciples heard\nof it, they came and took up his corpse, and laid it in a tomb."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 30,
    "text": "And the apostles gathered themselves together unto Jesus, and told him all things, both what they had done, and what they had taught."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 31,
    "text": "And he said unto them,\nCome ye yourselves apart into a desert place, and rest a while: for there were many coming and going, and they had no leisure so much as to eat."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 32,
    "text": "And they departed into a desert place by ship privately."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 33,
    "text": "And the people saw them departing, and many knew him, and ran afoot thither out of all cities, and outwent them, and came together unto him."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 34,
    "text": "And Jesus, when he came out, saw much people, and was moved with compassion toward them, because they were as sheep not having a shepherd: and he began to teach them many things."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 35,
    "text": "And when the day was now far spent, his disciples came unto him, and said, This is a desert place, and now the time\nis far passed:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 36,
    "text": "Send them away, that they may go into the country round about, and into the villages, and buy themselves bread: for they have nothing to eat."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 37,
    "text": "He answered and said unto them,\nGive ye them to eat. And they say unto him, Shall we go and buy two hundred pennyworth of bread, and give them to eat?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 38,
    "text": "He saith unto them,\nHow many loaves have ye? go and see. And when they knew, they say, Five, and two fishes."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 39,
    "text": "And he commanded them to make all sit down by companies upon the green grass."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 40,
    "text": "And they sat down in ranks, by hundreds, and by fifties."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 41,
    "text": "And when he had taken the five loaves and the two fishes, he looked up to heaven, and blessed, and brake the loaves, and gave\nthem to his disciples to set before them; and the two fishes divided he among them all."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 42,
    "text": "And they did all eat, and were filled."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 43,
    "text": "And they took up twelve baskets full of the fragments, and of the fishes."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 44,
    "text": "And they that did eat of the loaves were about five thousand men."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 45,
    "text": "And straightway he constrained his disciples to get into the ship, and to go to the other side before unto Bethsaida, while he sent away the people."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 46,
    "text": "And when he had sent them away, he departed into a mountain to pray."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 47,
    "text": "And when even was come, the ship was in the midst of the sea, and he alone on the land."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 48,
    "text": "And he saw them toiling in rowing; for the wind was contrary unto them: and about the fourth watch of the night he cometh unto them, walking upon the sea, and would have passed by them."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 49,
    "text": "But when they saw him walking upon the sea, they supposed it had been a spirit, and cried out:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 50,
    "text": "For they all saw him, and were troubled. And immediately he talked with them, and saith unto them,\nBe of good cheer: it is I; be not afraid."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 51,
    "text": "And he went up unto them into the ship; and the wind ceased: and they were sore amazed in themselves beyond measure, and wondered."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 52,
    "text": "For they considered not\nthe miracle of the loaves: for their heart was hardened."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 53,
    "text": "And when they had passed over, they came into the land of Gennesaret, and drew to the shore."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 54,
    "text": "And when they were come out of the ship, straightway they knew him,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 55,
    "text": "And ran through that whole region round about, and began to carry about in beds those that were sick, where they heard he was."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 56,
    "text": "And whithersoever he entered, into villages, or cities, or country, they laid the sick in the streets, and besought him that they might touch if it were but the border of his garment: and as many as touched him were made whole."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "Then came together unto him the Pharisees, and certain of the scribes, which came from Jerusalem."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "And when they saw some of his disciples eat bread with defiled, that is to say, with unwashen, hands, they found fault."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "For the Pharisees, and all the Jews, except they wash\ntheir\n hands oft, eat not, holding the tradition of the elders."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "And\nwhen they come from the market, except they wash, they eat not. And many other things there be, which they have received to hold,\nas the washing of cups, and pots, brasen vessels, and of tables."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "Then the Pharisees and scribes asked him, Why walk not thy disciples according to the tradition of the elders, but eat bread with unwashen hands?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "He answered and said unto them,\nWell hath Esaias prophesied of you hypocrites, as it is written, This people honoureth me with\ntheir\n lips, but their heart is far from me."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "Howbeit in vain do they worship me, teaching\nfor doctrines the commandments of men."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "For laying aside the commandment of God, ye hold the tradition of men,\nas the washing of pots and cups: and many other such like things ye do."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "And he said unto them,\nFull well ye reject the commandment of God, that ye may keep your own tradition."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "For Moses said, Honour thy father and thy mother; and, Whoso curseth father or mother, let him die the death:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "But ye say, If a man shall say to his father or mother,\nIt is\n Corban, that is to say, a gift, by whatsoever thou mightest be profited by me;\nhe shall be free."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "And ye suffer him no more to do ought for his father or his mother;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "Making the word of God of none effect through your tradition, which ye have delivered: and many such like things do ye."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "And when he had called all the people\nunto him, he said unto them,\nHearken unto me every one\nof you, and understand:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "There is nothing from without a man, that entering into him can defile him: but the things which come out of him, those are they that defile the man."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "If any man have ears to hear, let him hear."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "And when he was entered into the house from the people, his disciples asked him concerning the parable."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "And he saith unto them,\nAre ye so without understanding also? Do ye not perceive, that whatsoever thing from without entereth into the man,\nit cannot defile him;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "Because it entereth not into his heart, but into the belly, and goeth out into the draught, purging all meats?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "And he said,\nThat which cometh out of the man, that defileth the man."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "For from within, out of the heart of men, proceed evil thoughts, adulteries, fornications, murders,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "Thefts, covetousness, wickedness, deceit, lasciviousness, an evil eye, blasphemy, pride, foolishness:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "All these evil things come from within, and defile the man."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "And from thence he arose, and went into the borders of Tyre and Sidon, and entered into an house, and would have no man know\nit:\n but he could not be hid."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 25,
    "text": "For a\ncertain woman, whose young daughter had an unclean spirit, heard of him, and came and fell at his feet:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 26,
    "text": "The woman was a Greek, a Syrophenician by nation; and she besought him that he would cast forth the devil out of her daughter."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 27,
    "text": "But Jesus said unto her,\nLet the children first be filled: for it is not meet to take the children’s bread, and to cast\nit unto the dogs."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 28,
    "text": "And she answered and said unto him, Yes, Lord: yet the dogs under the table eat of the children’s crumbs."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 29,
    "text": "And he said unto her,\nFor this saying go thy way; the devil is gone out of thy daughter."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 30,
    "text": "And when she was come to her house, she found the devil gone out, and her daughter laid upon the bed."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 31,
    "text": "And again, departing from the coasts of Tyre and Sidon, he came unto the sea of Galilee, through the midst of the coasts of Decapolis."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 32,
    "text": "And they bring unto him one that was deaf, and had an impediment in his speech; and they beseech him to put his hand upon him."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 33,
    "text": "And he took him aside from the multitude, and put his fingers into his ears, and he spit, and touched his tongue;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 34,
    "text": "And looking up to heaven, he sighed, and saith unto him,\nEphphatha,\n that is,\nBe opened."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 35,
    "text": "And straightway his ears were opened, and the string of his tongue was loosed, and he spake plain."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 36,
    "text": "And he charged them that they should tell no man: but the more he charged them, so much the more a great deal they published\nit;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 37,
    "text": "And were beyond measure astonished, saying, He hath done all things well: he maketh both the deaf to hear, and the dumb to speak."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "In those days the multitude being very great, and having nothing to eat, Jesus called his disciples\nunto him, and saith unto them,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "I have compassion on the multitude, because they have now been with me three days, and have nothing to eat:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "And if I send them away fasting to their own houses, they will faint by the way: for divers of them came from far."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "And his disciples answered him, From whence can a man satisfy these\nmen with bread here in the wilderness?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "And he asked them,\nHow many loaves have ye? And they said, Seven."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "And he commanded the people to sit down on the ground: and he took the seven loaves, and gave thanks, and brake, and gave to his disciples to set before\nthem; and they did set\nthem before the people."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "And they had a few small fishes: and he blessed, and commanded to set them also before\nthem."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "So they did eat, and were filled: and they took up of the broken\nmeat that was left seven baskets."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "And they that had eaten were about four thousand: and he sent them away."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "And straightway he entered into a ship with his disciples, and came into the parts of Dalmanutha."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "And the Pharisees came forth, and began to question with him, seeking of him a sign from heaven, tempting him."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "And he sighed deeply in his spirit, and saith,\nWhy doth this generation seek after a sign? verily I say unto you, There shall no sign be given unto this generation."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "And he left them, and entering into the ship again departed to the other side."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "Now\nthe disciples had forgotten to take bread, neither had they in the ship with them more than one loaf."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "And he charged them, saying,\nTake heed, beware of the leaven of the Pharisees, and\nof the leaven of Herod."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "And they reasoned among themselves, saying,\nIt is because we have no bread."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "And when Jesus knew\nit, he saith unto them,\nWhy reason ye, because ye have no bread? perceive ye not yet, neither understand? have ye your heart yet hardened?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "Having eyes, see ye not? and having ears, hear ye not? and do ye not remember?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "When I brake the five loaves among five thousand, how many baskets full of fragments took ye up? They say unto him, Twelve."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "And when the seven among four thousand, how many baskets full of fragments took ye up? And they said, Seven."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "And he said unto them,\nHow is it that ye do not understand?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "And he cometh to Bethsaida; and they bring a blind man unto him, and besought him to touch him."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "And he took the blind man by the hand, and led him out of the town; and when he had spit on his eyes, and put his hands upon him, he asked him if he saw ought."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "And he looked up, and said, I see men as trees, walking."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 25,
    "text": "After that he put\nhis hands again upon his eyes, and made him look up: and he was restored, and saw every man clearly."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 26,
    "text": "And he sent him away to his house, saying, Neither go into the town, nor tell\nit to any in the town."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 27,
    "text": "And Jesus went out, and his disciples, into the towns of Caesarea Philippi: and by the way he asked his disciples, saying unto them, Whom do men say that I am?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 28,
    "text": "And they answered, John the Baptist: but some\nsay, Elias; and others, One of the prophets."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 29,
    "text": "And he saith unto them,\nBut whom say ye that I am? And Peter answereth and saith unto him, Thou art the Christ."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 30,
    "text": "And he charged them that they should tell no man of him."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 31,
    "text": "And he began to teach them, that the Son of man must suffer many things, and be rejected of the elders, and\nof the chief priests, and scribes, and be killed, and after three days rise again."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 32,
    "text": "And he spake that saying openly. And Peter took him, and began to rebuke him."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 33,
    "text": "But when he had turned about and looked on his disciples, he rebuked Peter, saying,\nGet thee behind me, Satan: for thou savourest not the things that be of God, but the things that be of men."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 34,
    "text": "And when he had called the people\nunto him with his disciples also, he said unto them, Whosoever will come after me, let him deny himself, and take up his cross, and follow me."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 35,
    "text": "For whosoever will save his life shall lose it; but whosoever shall lose his life for my sake and the gospel’s, the same shall save it."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 36,
    "text": "For what shall it profit a man, if he shall gain the whole world, and lose his own soul?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 37,
    "text": "Or what shall a man give in exchange for his soul?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 38,
    "text": "Whosoever therefore shall be ashamed of me and of my words in this adulterous and sinful generation; of him also shall the Son of man be ashamed, when he cometh in the glory of his Father with the holy angels."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "And he said unto them,\nVerily I say unto you, That there be some of them that stand here, which shall not taste of death, till they have seen the kingdom of God come with power."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "And after six days Jesus taketh\nwith him Peter, and James, and John, and leadeth them up into an high mountain apart by themselves: and he was transfigured before them."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "And his raiment became shining, exceeding white as snow; so as no fuller on earth can white them."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "And there appeared unto them Elias with Moses: and they were talking with Jesus."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "And Peter answered and said to Jesus, Master, it is good for us to be here: and let us make three tabernacles; one for thee, and one for Moses, and one for Elias."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "For he wist not what to say; for they were sore afraid."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "And there was a cloud that overshadowed them: and a voice came out of the cloud, saying, This is my beloved Son: hear him."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "And suddenly, when they had looked round about, they saw no man any more, save Jesus only with themselves."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "And as they came down from the mountain, he charged them that they should tell no man what things they had seen, till the Son of man were risen from the dead."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "And they kept that saying with themselves, questioning one with another what the rising from the dead should mean."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "And they asked him, saying, Why say the scribes that Elias must first come?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "And he answered and told them,\nElias verily cometh first, and restoreth all things; and how it is written of the Son of man, that he must suffer many things, and be set at nought."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "But I say unto you, That Elias is indeed come, and they have done unto him whatsoever they listed, as it is written of him."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "And when he came to\nhis disciples, he saw a great multitude about them, and the scribes questioning with them."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "And straightway all the people, when they beheld him, were greatly amazed, and running to\nhim saluted him."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "And he asked the scribes,\nWhat question ye with them?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "And one of the multitude answered and said, Master, I have brought unto thee my son, which hath a dumb spirit;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "And wheresoever he taketh him, he teareth him: and he foameth, and gnasheth with his teeth, and pineth away: and I spake to thy disciples that they should cast him out; and they could not."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "He answereth him, and saith,\nO faithless generation, how long shall I be with you? how long shall I suffer you? bring him unto me."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "And they brought him unto him: and when he saw him, straightway the spirit tare him; and he fell on the ground, and wallowed foaming."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "And he asked his father,\nHow long is it ago since this came unto him? And he said, Of a child."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "And ofttimes it hath cast him into the fire, and into the waters, to destroy him: but if thou canst do any thing, have compassion on us, and help us."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "Jesus said unto him,\nIf thou canst believe, all things\nare\n possible to him that believeth."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "And straightway the father of the child cried out, and said with tears, Lord, I believe; help thou mine unbelief."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 25,
    "text": "When Jesus saw that the people came running together, he rebuked the foul spirit, saying unto him,\nThou dumb and deaf spirit, I charge thee, come out of him, and enter no more into him."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 26,
    "text": "And\nthe spirit cried, and rent him sore, and came out of him: and he was as one dead; insomuch that many said, He is dead."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 27,
    "text": "But Jesus took him by the hand, and lifted him up; and he arose."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 28,
    "text": "And when he was come into the house, his disciples asked him privately, Why could not we cast him out?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 29,
    "text": "And he said unto them,\nThis kind can come forth by nothing, but by prayer and fasting."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 30,
    "text": "And they departed thence, and passed through Galilee; and he would not that any man should know\nit."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 31,
    "text": "For he taught his disciples, and said unto them,\nThe Son of man is delivered into the hands of men, and they shall kill him; and after that he is killed, he shall rise the third day."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 32,
    "text": "But they understood not that saying, and were afraid to ask him."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 33,
    "text": "And he came to Capernaum: and being in the house he asked them,\nWhat was it that ye disputed among yourselves by the way?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 34,
    "text": "But they held their peace: for by the way they had disputed among themselves, who\nshould be the greatest."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 35,
    "text": "And he sat down, and called the twelve, and saith unto them,\nIf any man desire to be first,\nthe same shall be last of all, and servant of all."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 36,
    "text": "And he took a child, and set him in the midst of them: and when he had taken him in his arms, he said unto them,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 37,
    "text": "Whosoever shall receive one of such children in my name, receiveth me: and whosoever shall receive me, receiveth not me, but him that sent me."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 38,
    "text": "And John answered him, saying, Master, we saw one casting out devils in thy name, and he followeth not us: and we forbad him, because he followeth not us."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 39,
    "text": "But Jesus said,\nForbid him not: for there is no man which shall do a miracle in my name, that can lightly speak evil of me."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 40,
    "text": "For he that is not against us is on our part."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 41,
    "text": "For whosoever shall give you a cup of water to drink in my name, because ye belong to Christ, verily I say unto you, he shall not lose his reward."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 42,
    "text": "And whosoever shall offend one of\nthese little ones that believe in me, it is better for him that a millstone were hanged about his neck, and he were cast into the sea."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 43,
    "text": "And if thy hand offend thee, cut it off: it is better for thee to enter into life maimed, than having two hands to go into hell, into the fire that never shall be quenched:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 44,
    "text": "Where their worm dieth not, and the fire is not quenched."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 45,
    "text": "And if thy foot offend thee, cut it off: it is better for thee to enter halt into life, than having two feet to be cast into hell, into the fire that never shall be quenched:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 46,
    "text": "Where their worm dieth not, and the fire is not quenched."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 47,
    "text": "And if thine eye offend thee, pluck it out: it is better for thee to enter into the kingdom of God with one eye, than having two eyes to be cast into hell fire:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 48,
    "text": "Where their worm dieth not, and the fire is not quenched."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 49,
    "text": "For every one shall be salted with fire, and every sacrifice shall be salted with salt."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 50,
    "text": "Salt\nis good: but if the salt have lost his saltness, wherewith will ye season it? Have salt in yourselves, and have peace one with another."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "And he arose from thence, and cometh into the coasts of Judaea by the farther side of Jordan: and the people resort unto him again; and, as he was wont, he taught them again."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "And the Pharisees came to him, and asked him, Is it lawful for a man to put away\nhis wife? tempting him."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "And he answered and said unto them,\nWhat did Moses command you?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "And they said, Moses suffered to write a bill of divorcement, and to put\nher away."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "And Jesus answered and said unto them,\nFor the hardness of your heart he wrote you this precept."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "But from the beginning of the creation God made them male and female."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "For this cause shall a man leave his father and mother, and cleave to his wife;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "And they twain shall be one flesh: so then they are no more twain, but one flesh."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "What therefore God hath joined together, let not man put asunder."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "And in the house his disciples asked him again of the same\nmatter."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "And he saith unto them,\nWhosoever shall put away his wife, and marry another, committeth adultery against her."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "And if a woman shall put away her husband, and be married to another, she committeth adultery."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "And they brought young children to him, that he should touch them: and\nhis disciples rebuked those that brought\nthem."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "But when Jesus saw\nit, he was much displeased, and said unto them,\nSuffer the little children to come unto me, and forbid them not: for of such is the kingdom of God."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "Verily I say unto you, Whosoever shall not receive the kingdom of God as a little child, he shall not enter therein."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "And he took them up in his arms, put\nhis hands upon them, and blessed them."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "And when he was gone forth into the way, there came one running, and kneeled to him, and asked him, Good Master, what shall I do that I may inherit eternal life?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "And Jesus said unto him,\nWhy callest thou me good?\nthere is\n none good but one,\nthat is, God."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "Thou knowest the commandments, Do not commit adultery, Do not kill, Do not steal, Do not bear false witness, Defraud not, Honour thy father and mother."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "And he answered and said unto him, Master, all these have I observed from my youth."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "Then Jesus beholding him loved him, and said unto him,\nOne thing thou lackest: go thy way, sell whatsoever thou hast, and give to the poor, and thou shalt have treasure in heaven: and come, take up the cross, and follow me."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "And he was sad at that saying, and went away grieved: for he had great possessions."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "And Jesus looked round about, and saith unto his disciples,\nHow hardly shall they that have riches enter into the kingdom of God!"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "And the disciples were astonished at his words. But Jesus answereth again, and saith unto them,\nChildren, how hard is it for them that trust in riches to enter into the kingdom of God!"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 25,
    "text": "It is easier for a camel to go through the eye of a needle, than for a rich man to enter into the kingdom of God."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 26,
    "text": "And they were astonished out of measure, saying among themselves, Who then can be saved?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 27,
    "text": "And Jesus looking upon them saith,\nWith men\nit is impossible, but not with God: for with God all things are possible."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 28,
    "text": "Then Peter began to say unto him, Lo, we have left all, and have followed thee."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 29,
    "text": "And Jesus answered and said,\nVerily I say unto you, There is no man that hath left house, or brethren, or sisters, or father, or mother, or wife, or children, or lands, for my sake, and the gospel’s,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 30,
    "text": "But he shall receive an hundredfold now in this time, houses, and brethren, and sisters, and mothers, and children, and lands, with persecutions; and in the world to come eternal life."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 31,
    "text": "But many\nthat are first shall be last; and the last first."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 32,
    "text": "And they were in the way going up to Jerusalem; and Jesus went before them: and they were amazed; and as they followed, they were afraid. And he took again the twelve, and began to tell them what things should happen unto him,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 33,
    "text": "Saying,Behold, we go up to Jerusalem; and the Son of man shall be delivered unto the chief priests, and unto the scribes; and they shall condemn him to death, and shall deliver him to the Gentiles:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 34,
    "text": "And they shall mock him, and shall scourge him, and shall spit upon him, and shall kill him: and the third day he shall rise again."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 35,
    "text": "And James and John, the sons of Zebedee, come unto him, saying, Master, we would that thou shouldest do for us whatsoever we shall desire."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 36,
    "text": "And he said unto them,\nWhat would ye that I should do for you?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 37,
    "text": "They said unto him, Grant unto us that we may sit, one on thy right hand, and the other on thy left hand, in thy glory."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 38,
    "text": "But Jesus said unto them,\nYe know not what ye ask: can ye drink of the cup that I drink of? and be baptized with the baptism that I am baptized with?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 39,
    "text": "And they said unto him, We can. And Jesus said unto them,\nYe shall indeed drink of the cup that I drink of; and with the baptism that I am baptized withal shall ye be baptized:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 40,
    "text": "But to sit on my right hand and on my left hand is not mine to give; but\nit shall be given to them for whom it is prepared."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 41,
    "text": "And when the ten heard\nit, they began to be much displeased with James and John."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 42,
    "text": "But Jesus called them\nto him, and saith unto them,\nYe know that they which are accounted to rule over the Gentiles exercise lordship over them; and their great ones exercise authority upon them."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 43,
    "text": "But so shall it not be among you: but whosoever will be great among you, shall be your minister:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 44,
    "text": "And whosoever of you will be the chiefest, shall be servant of all."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 45,
    "text": "For even the Son of man came not to be ministered unto, but to minister, and to give his life a ransom for many."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 46,
    "text": "And they came to Jericho: and as he went out of Jericho with his disciples and a great number of people, blind Bartimaeus, the son of Timaeus, sat by the highway side begging."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 47,
    "text": "And when he heard that it was Jesus of Nazareth, he began to cry out, and say, Jesus,\nthou Son of David, have mercy on me."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 48,
    "text": "And many charged him that he should hold his peace: but he cried the more a great deal,\nThou Son of David, have mercy on me."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 49,
    "text": "And Jesus stood still, and commanded him to be called. And they call the blind man, saying unto him, Be of good comfort, rise; he calleth thee."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 50,
    "text": "And he, casting away his garment, rose, and came to Jesus."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 51,
    "text": "And Jesus answered and said unto him,\nWhat wilt thou that I should do unto thee? The blind man said unto him, Lord, that I might receive my sight."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 52,
    "text": "And Jesus said unto him,\nGo thy way; thy faith hath made thee whole. And immediately he received his sight, and followed Jesus in the way."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "And when they came nigh to Jerusalem, unto Bethphage and Bethany, at the mount of Olives, he sendeth forth two of his disciples,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "And saith unto them,\nGo your way into the village over against you: and as soon as ye be entered into it, ye shall find a colt tied, whereon never man sat; loose him, and bring\nhim."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "And if any man say unto you, Why do ye this? say ye that the Lord hath need of him; and straightway he will send him hither."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "And they went their way, and found the colt tied by the door without in a place where two ways met; and they loose him."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "And certain of them that stood there said unto them, What do ye, loosing the colt?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "And they said unto them even as Jesus had commanded: and they let them go."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "And they brought the colt to Jesus, and cast their garments on him; and he sat upon him."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "And many spread their garments in the way: and others cut down branches off the trees, and strawed\nthem in the way."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "And they that went before, and they that followed, cried, saying, Hosanna; Blessed\nis he that cometh in the name of the Lord:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "Blessed\nbe the kingdom of our father David, that cometh in the name of the Lord: Hosanna in the highest."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "And Jesus entered into Jerusalem, and into the temple: and when he had looked round about upon all things, and now the eventide was come, he went out unto Bethany with the twelve."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "And on the morrow, when they were come from Bethany, he was hungry:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "And seeing a fig tree afar off having leaves, he came, if haply he might find any thing thereon: and when he came to it, he found nothing but leaves; for the time of figs was not\nyet."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "And Jesus answered and said unto it,\nNo man eat fruit of thee hereafter for ever. And his disciples heard\nit."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "And they come to Jerusalem: and Jesus went into the temple, and began to cast out them that sold and bought in the temple, and overthrew the tables of the moneychangers, and the seats of them that sold doves;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "And would not suffer that any man should carry\nany vessel through the temple."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "And he taught, saying unto them,\nIs it not written, My house shall be called of all nations the house of prayer? but ye have made it a den of thieves."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "And the scribes and chief priests heard\nit, and sought how they might destroy him: for they feared him, because all the people was astonished at his doctrine."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "And when even was come, he went out of the city."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "And in the morning, as they passed by, they saw the fig tree dried up from the roots."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "And Peter calling to remembrance saith unto him, Master, behold, the fig tree which thou cursedst is withered away."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "And Jesus answering saith unto them,\nHave faith in God."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "For verily I say unto you, That whosoever shall say unto this mountain, Be thou removed, and be thou cast into the sea; and shall not doubt in his heart, but shall believe that those things which he saith shall come to pass; he shall have whatsoever he saith."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "Therefore I say unto you, What things soever ye desire, when ye pray, believe that ye receive\nthem, and ye shall havethem."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 25,
    "text": "And when ye stand praying, forgive, if ye have ought against any: that your Father also which is in heaven may forgive you your trespasses."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 26,
    "text": "But if ye do not forgive, neither will your Father which is in heaven forgive your trespasses."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 27,
    "text": "And they come again to Jerusalem: and as he was walking in the temple, there come to him the chief priests, and the scribes, and the elders,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 28,
    "text": "And say unto him, By what authority doest thou these things? and who gave thee this authority to do these things?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 29,
    "text": "And Jesus answered and said unto them,\nI will also ask of you one question, and answer me, and I will tell you by what authority I do these things."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 30,
    "text": "The baptism of John, was\nit from heaven, or of men? answer me."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 31,
    "text": "And they reasoned with themselves, saying, If we shall say, From heaven; he will say, Why then did ye not believe him?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 32,
    "text": "But if we shall say, Of men; they feared the people: for all\nmen\n counted John, that he was a prophet indeed."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 33,
    "text": "And they answered and said unto Jesus, We cannot tell. And Jesus answering saith unto them,\nNeither do I tell you by what authority I do these things."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "And he began to speak unto them by parables.\nA\ncertain\n man planted a vineyard, and set an hedge about\nit,\n and digged\na place for the winefat, and built a tower, and let it out to husbandmen, and went into a far country."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "And at the season he sent to the husbandmen a servant, that he might receive from the husbandmen of the fruit of the vineyard."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "And they caught\nhim, and beat him, and sent\nhim away empty."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "And again he sent unto them another servant; and at him they cast stones, and wounded\nhim in the head, and sent\nhim\n away shamefully handled."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "And again he sent another; and him they killed, and many others; beating some, and killing some."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "Having yet therefore one son, his wellbeloved, he sent him also last unto them, saying, They will reverence my son."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "But those husbandmen said among themselves, This is the heir; come, let us kill him, and the inheritance shall be ours."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "And they took him, and killed\nhim, and cast\nhim out of the vineyard."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "What shall therefore the lord of the vineyard do? he will come and destroy the husbandmen, and will give the vineyard unto others."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "And have ye not read this scripture; The stone which the builders rejected is become the head of the corner:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "This was the Lord’s doing, and it is marvellous in our eyes?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "And they sought to lay hold on him, but feared the people: for they knew that he had spoken the parable against them: and they left him, and went their way."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "And they send unto him certain of the Pharisees and of the Herodians, to catch him in\nhis words."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "And when they were come, they say unto him, Master, we know that thou art true, and carest for no man: for thou regardest not the person of men, but teachest the way of God in truth: Is it lawful to give tribute to Caesar, or not?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "Shall we give, or shall we not give? But he, knowing their hypocrisy, said unto them,\nWhy tempt ye me? bring me a penny, that I may seeit."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "And they brought\nit. And he saith unto them,\nWhose\nis this image and superscription? And they said unto him, Caesar’s."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "And Jesus answering said unto them,\nRender to Caesar the things that are Caesar’s, and to God the things that are God’s. And they marvelled at him."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "Then come unto him the Sadducees, which say there is no resurrection; and they asked him, saying,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "Master, Moses wrote unto us, If a man’s brother die, and leave\nhis wife\nbehind him, and leave no children, that his brother should take his wife, and raise up seed unto his brother."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "Now there were seven brethren: and the first took a wife, and dying left no seed."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "And the second took her, and died, neither left he any seed: and the third likewise."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "And the seven had her, and left no seed: last of all the woman died also."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "In the resurrection therefore, when they shall rise, whose wife shall she be of them? for the seven had her to wife."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "And Jesus answering said unto them,\nDo ye not therefore err, because ye know not the scriptures, neither the power of God?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 25,
    "text": "For when they shall rise from the dead, they neither marry, nor are given in marriage; but are as the angels which are in heaven."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 26,
    "text": "And as touching the dead, that they rise: have ye not read in the book of Moses, how in the bush God spake unto him, saying, I\nam\n the God of Abraham, and the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 27,
    "text": "He is not the God of the dead, but the God of the living: ye therefore do greatly err."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 28,
    "text": "And one of the scribes came, and having heard them reasoning together, and perceiving that he had answered them well, asked him, Which is the first commandment of all?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 29,
    "text": "And Jesus answered him,\nThe first of all the commandments\nis, Hear, O Israel; The Lord our God is one Lord:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 30,
    "text": "And thou shalt love the Lord thy God with all thy heart, and with all thy soul, and with all thy mind, and with all thy strength: this is the first commandment."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 31,
    "text": "And the second\nis like,\nnamely this, Thou shalt love thy neighbour as thyself. There is none other commandment greater than these."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 32,
    "text": "And the scribe said unto him, Well, Master, thou hast said the truth: for there is one God; and there is none other but he:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 33,
    "text": "And to love him with all the heart, and with all the understanding, and with all the soul, and with all the strength, and to love\nhis neighbour as himself, is more than all whole burnt offerings and sacrifices."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 34,
    "text": "And when Jesus saw that he answered discreetly, he said unto him,\nThou art not far from the kingdom of God. And no man after that durst ask him\nany question."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 35,
    "text": "And Jesus answered and said, while he taught in the temple,\nHow say the scribes that Christ is the Son of David?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 36,
    "text": "For David himself said by the Holy Ghost, The Lord said to my Lord, Sit thou on my right hand, till I make thine enemies thy footstool."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 37,
    "text": "David therefore himself calleth him Lord; and whence is he\nthen his son? And the common people heard him gladly."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 38,
    "text": "And he said unto them in his doctrine,\nBeware of the scribes, which love to go in long clothing, and\nlove salutations in the marketplaces,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 39,
    "text": "And the chief seats in the synagogues, and the uppermost rooms at feasts:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 40,
    "text": "Which devour widows’ houses, and for a pretence make long prayers: these shall receive greater damnation."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 41,
    "text": "And Jesus sat over against the treasury, and beheld how the people cast money into the treasury: and many that were rich cast in much."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 42,
    "text": "And there came a certain poor widow, and she threw in two mites, which make a farthing."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 43,
    "text": "And he called\nunto him his disciples, and saith unto them,\nVerily I say unto you, That this poor widow hath cast more in, than all they which have cast into the treasury:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 44,
    "text": "For all\nthey did cast in of their abundance; but she of her want did cast in all that she had,\neven all her living."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "And as he went out of the temple, one of his disciples saith unto him, Master, see what manner of stones and what buildings\nare here!"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "And Jesus answering said unto him,\nSeest thou these great buildings? there shall not be left one stone upon another, that shall not be thrown down."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "And as he sat upon the mount of Olives over against the temple, Peter and James and John and Andrew asked him privately,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "Tell us, when shall these things be? and what\nshall be the sign when all these things shall be fulfilled?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "And Jesus answering them began to say,\nTake heed lest any\nman\n deceive you:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "For many shall come in my name, saying, I am\nChrist; and shall deceive many."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "And when ye shall hear of wars and rumours of wars, be ye not troubled: for\nsuch things must needs be; but the end\nshall not\nbe yet."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "For nation shall rise against nation, and kingdom against kingdom: and there shall be earthquakes in divers places, and there shall be famines and troubles: these\nare the beginnings of sorrows."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "But take heed to yourselves: for they shall deliver you up to councils; and in the synagogues ye shall be beaten: and ye shall be brought before rulers and kings for my sake, for a testimony against them."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "And the gospel must first be published among all nations."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "But when they shall lead\nyou, and deliver you up, take no thought beforehand what ye shall speak, neither do ye premeditate: but whatsoever shall be given you in that hour, that speak ye: for it is not ye that speak, but the Holy Ghost."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "Now the brother shall betray the brother to death, and the father the son; and children shall rise up against\ntheir parents, and shall cause them to be put to death."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "And ye shall be hated of all\nmen for my name’s sake: but he that shall endure unto the end, the same shall be saved."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "But when ye shall see the abomination of desolation, spoken of by Daniel the prophet, standing where it ought not, (let him that readeth understand,) then let them that be in Judaea flee to the mountains:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "And let him that is on the housetop not go down into the house, neither enter\ntherein, to take any thing out of his house:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "And let him that is in the field not turn back again for to take up his garment."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "But woe to them that are with child, and to them that give suck in those days!"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "And pray ye that your flight be not in the winter."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "For\nin those days shall be affliction, such as was not from the beginning of the creation which God created unto this time, neither shall be."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "And except that the Lord had shortened those days, no flesh should be saved: but for the elect’s sake, whom he hath chosen, he hath shortened the days."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "And then if any man shall say to you, Lo, here\nis Christ; or, lo,\nhe is there; believe\nhim\n not:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "For false Christs and false prophets shall rise, and shall shew signs and wonders, to seduce, if\nit were possible, even the elect."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "But take ye heed: behold, I have foretold you all things."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "But in those days, after that tribulation, the sun shall be darkened, and the moon shall not give her light,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 25,
    "text": "And the stars of heaven shall fall, and the powers that are in heaven shall be shaken."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 26,
    "text": "And then shall they see the Son of man coming in the clouds with great power and glory."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 27,
    "text": "And then shall he send his angels, and shall gather together his elect from the four winds, from the uttermost part of the earth to the uttermost part of heaven."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 28,
    "text": "Now learn a parable of the fig tree; When her branch is yet tender, and putteth forth leaves, ye know that summer is near:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 29,
    "text": "So ye in like manner, when ye shall see these things come to pass, know that it is nigh,\neven at the doors."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 30,
    "text": "Verily I say unto you, that this generation shall not pass, till all these things be done."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 31,
    "text": "Heaven and earth shall pass away: but my words shall not pass away."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 32,
    "text": "But of that day and\nthat hour knoweth no man, no, not the angels which are in heaven, neither the Son, but the Father."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 33,
    "text": "Take ye heed, watch and pray: for ye know not when the time is."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 34,
    "text": "For the Son of man is as a man taking a far journey, who left his house, and gave authority to his servants, and to every man his work, and commanded the porter to watch."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 35,
    "text": "Watch ye therefore: for ye know not when the master of the house cometh, at even, or at midnight, or at the cockcrowing, or in the morning:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 36,
    "text": "Lest coming suddenly he find you sleeping."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 37,
    "text": "And what I say unto you I say unto all, Watch."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "After two days was\nthe feast of the passover, and of unleavened bread: and the chief priests and the scribes sought how they might take him by craft, and put\nhim to death."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "But they said, Not on the feast\nday, lest there be an uproar of the people."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "And being in Bethany in the house of Simon the leper, as he sat at meat, there came a woman having an alabaster box of ointment of spikenard very precious; and she brake the box, and poured\nit on his head."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "And there were some that had indignation within themselves, and said, Why was this waste of the ointment made?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "For it might have been sold for more than three hundred pence, and have been given to the poor. And they murmured against her."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "And Jesus said,\nLet her alone; why trouble ye her? she hath wrought a good work on me."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "For ye have the poor with you always, and whensoever ye will ye may do them good: but me ye have not always."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "She hath done what she could: she is come aforehand to anoint my body to the burying."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "Verily I say unto you, Wheresoever this gospel shall be preached throughout the whole world,\nthis also that she hath done shall be spoken of for a memorial of her."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "And Judas Iscariot, one of the twelve, went unto the chief priests, to betray him unto them."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "And when they heard\nit, they were glad, and promised to give him money. And he sought how he might conveniently betray him."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "And the first day of unleavened bread, when they killed the passover, his disciples said unto him, Where wilt thou that we go and prepare that thou mayest eat the passover?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "And he sendeth forth two of his disciples, and saith unto them,\nGo ye into the city, and there shall meet you a man bearing a pitcher of water: follow him."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "And wheresoever he shall go in, say ye to the goodman of the house, The Master saith, Where is the guestchamber, where I shall eat the passover with my disciples?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "And he will shew you a large upper room furnished\nand\n prepared: there make ready for us."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "And his disciples went forth, and came into the city, and found as he had said unto them: and they made ready the passover."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "And in the evening he cometh with the twelve."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "And as they sat and did eat, Jesus said,\nVerily I say unto you, One of you which eateth with me shall betray me."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "And they began to be sorrowful, and to say unto him one by one,\nIs it I? and another\nsaid, Is it I?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "And he answered and said unto them,\nIt is one of the twelve, that dippeth with me in the dish."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "The Son of man indeed goeth, as it is written of him: but woe to that man by whom the Son of man is betrayed! good were it for that man if he had never been born."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "And as they did eat, Jesus took bread, and blessed, and brake\nit, and gave to them, and said,\nTake, eat: this is my body."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "And he took the cup, and when he had given thanks, he gave\nit\n to them: and they all drank of it."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "And he said unto them,\nThis is my blood of the new testament, which is shed for many."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 25,
    "text": "Verily I say unto you, I will drink no more of the fruit of the vine, until that day that I drink it new in the kingdom of God."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 26,
    "text": "And when they had sung an hymn, they went out into the mount of Olives."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 27,
    "text": "And Jesus saith unto them,\nAll ye shall be offended because of me this night: for it is written, I will smite the shepherd, and the sheep shall be scattered."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 28,
    "text": "But after that I am risen, I will go before you into Galilee."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 29,
    "text": "But Peter said unto him, Although all shall be offended, yet\nwill\n not I."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 30,
    "text": "And Jesus saith unto him,\nVerily I say unto thee, That this day,\neven in this night, before the cock crow twice, thou shalt deny me thrice."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 31,
    "text": "But he spake the more vehemently, If I should die with thee, I will not deny thee in any wise. Likewise also said they all."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 32,
    "text": "And they came to a place which was named Gethsemane: and he saith to his disciples,\nSit ye here, while I shall pray."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 33,
    "text": "And he taketh with him Peter and James and John, and began to be sore amazed, and to be very heavy;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 34,
    "text": "And saith unto them,\nMy soul is exceeding sorrowful unto death: tarry ye here, and watch."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 35,
    "text": "And he went forward a little, and fell on the ground, and prayed that, if it were possible, the hour might pass from him."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 36,
    "text": "And he said,\nAbba, Father, all things\nare possible unto thee; take away this cup from me: nevertheless not what I will, but what thou wilt."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 37,
    "text": "And he cometh, and findeth them sleeping, and saith unto Peter,\nSimon, sleepest thou? couldest not thou watch one hour?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 38,
    "text": "Watch ye and pray, lest ye enter into temptation. The spirit truly\nis ready, but the flesh\nis weak."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 39,
    "text": "And again he went away, and prayed, and spake the same words."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 40,
    "text": "And when he returned, he found them asleep again, (for their eyes were heavy,) neither wist they what to answer him."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 41,
    "text": "And he cometh the third time, and saith unto them,\nSleep on now, and take\nyour rest: it is enough, the hour is come; behold, the Son of man is betrayed into the hands of sinners."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 42,
    "text": "Rise up, let us go; lo, he that betrayeth me is at hand."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 43,
    "text": "And immediately, while he yet spake, cometh Judas, one of the twelve, and with him a great multitude with swords and staves, from the chief priest and the scribes and the elders."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 44,
    "text": "And he that betrayed him had given them a token, saying, Whomsoever I shall kiss, that same is he; take him, and lead\nhim away safely."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 45,
    "text": "And as soon as he was come, he goeth straightway to him, and saith, Master, master; and kissed him."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 46,
    "text": "And they laid their hands on him, and took him."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 47,
    "text": "And one of them that stood by drew a sword, and smote a servant of the high priest, and cut off his ear."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 48,
    "text": "And Jesus answered and said unto them,\nAre ye come out, as against a thief, with swords and\nwith staves to take me?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 49,
    "text": "I was daily with you in the temple teaching, and ye took me not: but the scriptures must be fulfilled."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 50,
    "text": "And they all forsook him, and fled."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 51,
    "text": "And there followed him a certain young man, having a linen cloth cast about\nhis naked\nbody; and the young men laid hold on him:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 52,
    "text": "And he left the linen cloth, and fled from them naked."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 53,
    "text": "And they led Jesus away to the high priest: and with him were assembled all the chief priests and the elders and the scribes."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 54,
    "text": "And Peter followed him afar off, even into the palace of the high priest: and he sat with the servants, and warmed himself at the fire."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 55,
    "text": "And the chief priests and all the council sought for witness against Jesus to put him to death; and found none."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 56,
    "text": "For many bare false witness against him, but their witness agreed not together."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 57,
    "text": "And there arose certain, and bare false witness against him, saying,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 58,
    "text": "We heard him say, I will destroy this temple that is made with hands, and within three days I will build another made without hands."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 59,
    "text": "But neither so did their witness agree together."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 60,
    "text": "And the high priest stood up in the midst, and asked Jesus, saying, Answerest thou nothing? what\nis it which these witness against thee?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 61,
    "text": "But he held his peace, and answered nothing. Again the high priest asked him, and said unto him, Art thou the Christ, the Son of the Blessed?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 62,
    "text": "And Jesus said,\nI am: and ye shall see the Son of man sitting on the right hand of power, and coming in the clouds of heaven."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 63,
    "text": "Then the high priest rent his clothes, and saith, What need we any further witnesses?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 64,
    "text": "Ye have heard the blasphemy: what think ye? And they all condemned him to be guilty of death."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 65,
    "text": "And some began to spit on him, and to cover his face, and to buffet him, and to say unto him, Prophesy: and the servants did strike him with the palms of their hands."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 66,
    "text": "And as Peter was beneath in the palace, there cometh one of the maids of the high priest:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 67,
    "text": "And when she saw Peter warming himself, she looked upon him, and said, And thou also wast with Jesus of Nazareth."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 68,
    "text": "But he denied, saying, I know not, neither understand I what thou sayest. And he went out into the porch; and the cock crew."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 69,
    "text": "And a maid saw him again, and began to say to them that stood by, This is\none of them."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 70,
    "text": "And he denied it again. And a little after, they that stood by said again to Peter, Surely thou art\none of them: for thou art a Galilaean, and thy speech agreeth\nthereto."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 71,
    "text": "But he began to curse and to swear,\nsaying, I know not this man of whom ye speak."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 72,
    "text": "And the second time the cock crew. And Peter called to mind the word that Jesus said unto him,\nBefore the cock crow twice, thou shalt deny me thrice. And when he thought thereon, he wept."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "And straightway in the morning the chief priests held a consultation with the elders and scribes and the whole council, and bound Jesus, and carried\nhim away, and delivered\nhim to Pilate."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "And Pilate asked him, Art thou the King of the Jews? And he answering said unto him,\nThou sayest\nit."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "And the chief priests accused him of many things: but he answered nothing."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "And Pilate asked him again, saying, Answerest thou nothing? behold how many things they witness against thee."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "But Jesus yet answered nothing; so that Pilate marvelled."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "Now at\nthat feast he released unto them one prisoner, whomsoever they desired."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "And there was\none named Barabbas,\nwhich lay\n bound with them that had made insurrection with him, who had committed murder in the insurrection."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "And the multitude crying aloud began to desire\nhim to do\n as he had ever done unto them."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "But Pilate answered them, saying, Will ye that I release unto you the King of the Jews?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "For he knew that the chief priests had delivered him for envy."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "But the chief priests moved the people, that he should rather release Barabbas unto them."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "And Pilate answered and said again unto them, What will ye then that I shall do\nunto him whom ye call the King of the Jews?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "And they cried out again, Crucify him."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "Then Pilate said unto them, Why, what evil hath he done? And they cried out the more exceedingly, Crucify him."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "And\nso Pilate, willing to content the people, released Barabbas unto them, and delivered Jesus, when he had scourged\nhim, to be crucified."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "And the soldiers led him away into the hall, called Praetorium; and they call together the whole band."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "And they clothed him with purple, and platted a crown of thorns, and put it about his\nhead,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "And began to salute him, Hail, King of the Jews!"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "And they smote him on the head with a reed, and did spit upon him, and bowing\ntheir knees worshipped him."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "And when they had mocked him, they took off the purple from him, and put his own clothes on him, and led him out to crucify him."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "And they compel one Simon a Cyrenian, who passed by, coming out of the country, the father of Alexander and Rufus, to bear his cross."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "And they bring him unto the place Golgotha, which is, being interpreted, The place of a skull."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "And they gave him to drink wine mingled with myrrh: but he received\nit not."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "And when they had crucified him, they parted his garments, casting lots upon them, what every man should take."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 25,
    "text": "And it was the third hour, and they crucified him."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 26,
    "text": "And the superscription of his accusation was written over, THE KING OF THE JEWS."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 27,
    "text": "And with him they crucify two thieves; the one on his right hand, and the other on his left."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 28,
    "text": "And the scripture was fulfilled, which saith, And he was numbered with the transgressors."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 29,
    "text": "And they that passed by railed on him, wagging their heads, and saying, Ah, thou that destroyest the temple, and buildest\nit in three days,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 30,
    "text": "Save thyself, and come down from the cross."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 31,
    "text": "Likewise also the chief priests mocking said among themselves with the scribes, He saved others; himself he cannot save."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 32,
    "text": "Let Christ the King of Israel descend now from the cross, that we may see and believe. And they that were crucified with him reviled him."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 33,
    "text": "And when the sixth hour was come, there was darkness over the whole land until the ninth hour."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 34,
    "text": "And at the ninth hour Jesus cried with a loud voice, saying,\nEloi, Eloi, lama sabachthani? which is, being interpreted,\nMy God, my God, why hast thou forsaken me?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 35,
    "text": "And some of them that stood by, when they heard\nit, said, Behold, he calleth Elias."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 36,
    "text": "And one ran and filled a spunge full of vinegar, and put\nit\n on a reed, and gave him to drink, saying, Let alone; let us see whether Elias will come to take him down."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 37,
    "text": "And Jesus cried with a loud voice, and gave up the ghost."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 38,
    "text": "And the veil of the temple was rent in twain from the top to the bottom."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 39,
    "text": "And when the centurion, which stood over against him, saw that he so cried out, and gave up the ghost, he said, Truly this man was the Son of God."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 40,
    "text": "There were also women looking on afar off: among whom was Mary Magdalene, and Mary the mother of James the less and of Joses, and Salome;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 41,
    "text": "(Who also, when he was in Galilee, followed him, and ministered unto him;) and many other women which came up with him unto Jerusalem."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 42,
    "text": "And now when the even was come, because it was the preparation, that is, the day before the sabbath,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 43,
    "text": "Joseph of Arimathaea, an honourable counsellor, which also waited for the kingdom of God, came, and went in boldly unto Pilate, and craved the body of Jesus."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 44,
    "text": "And Pilate marvelled if he were already dead: and calling\nunto him\n the centurion, he asked him whether he had been any while dead."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 45,
    "text": "And when he knew\nit of the centurion, he gave the body to Joseph."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 46,
    "text": "And he bought fine linen, and took him down, and wrapped him in the linen, and laid him in a sepulchre which was hewn out of a rock, and rolled a stone unto the door of the sepulchre."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 47,
    "text": "And Mary Magdalene and Mary\nthe mother of Joses beheld where he was laid."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 16,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "And when the sabbath was past, Mary Magdalene, and Mary the\nmother\n of James, and Salome, had bought sweet spices, that they might come and anoint him."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 16,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "And very early in the morning the first\nday of the week, they came unto the sepulchre at the rising of the sun."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 16,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "And they said among themselves, Who shall roll us away the stone from the door of the sepulchre?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 16,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "And when they looked, they saw that the stone was rolled away: for it was very great."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 16,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "And entering into the sepulchre, they saw a young man sitting on the right side, clothed in a long white garment; and they were affrighted."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 16,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "And he saith unto them, Be not affrighted: Ye seek Jesus of Nazareth, which was crucified: he is risen; he is not here: behold the place where they laid him."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 16,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "But go your way, tell his disciples and Peter that he goeth before you into Galilee: there shall ye see him, as he said unto you."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 16,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "And they went out quickly, and fled from the sepulchre; for they trembled and were amazed: neither said they any thing to any\nman; for they were afraid."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 16,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "Now when\nJesus was risen early the first\nday of the week, he appeared first to Mary Magdalene, out of whom he had cast seven devils."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 16,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "And she went and told them that had been with him, as they mourned and wept."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 16,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "And they, when they had heard that he was alive, and had been seen of her, believed not."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 16,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "After that he appeared in another form unto two of them, as they walked, and went into the country."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 16,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "And they went and told\nit unto the residue: neither believed they them."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 16,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "Afterward he appeared unto the eleven as they sat at meat, and upbraided them with their unbelief and hardness of heart, because they believed not them which had seen him after he was risen."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 16,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "And he said unto them,\nGo ye into all the world, and preach the gospel to every creature."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 16,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "He that believeth and is baptized shall be saved; but he that believeth not shall be damned."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 16,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "And these signs shall follow them that believe; In my name shall they cast out devils; they shall speak with new tongues;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 16,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "They shall take up serpents; and if they drink any deadly thing, it shall not hurt them; they shall lay hands on the sick, and they shall recover."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 16,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "So then after the Lord had spoken unto them, he was received up into heaven, and sat on the right hand of God."
  },
  {
    "book": "Mark",
    "chapter": 16,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "And they went forth, and preached every where, the Lord working with\nthem, and confirming the word with signs following. Amen."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "Forasmuch as many have taken in hand to set forth in order a declaration of those things which are most surely believed among us,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "Even as they delivered them unto us, which from the beginning were eyewitnesses, and ministers of the word;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "It seemed good to me also, having had perfect understanding of all things from the very first, to write unto thee in order, most excellent Theophilus,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "That thou mightest know the certainty of those things, wherein thou hast been instructed."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "There was in the days of Herod, the king of Judaea, a certain priest named Zacharias, of the course of Abia: and his wife\nwas of the daughters of Aaron, and her name\nwas Elisabeth."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "And they were both righteous before God, walking in all the commandments and ordinances of the Lord blameless."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "And they had no child, because that Elisabeth was barren, and they both were\nnow well stricken in years."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "And it came to pass, that while he executed the priest’s office before God in the order of his course,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "According to the custom of the priest’s office, his lot was to burn incense when he went into the temple of the Lord."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "And the whole multitude of the people were praying without at the time of incense."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "And there appeared unto him an angel of the Lord standing on the right side of the altar of incense."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "And when Zacharias saw\nhim, he was troubled, and fear fell upon him."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "But the angel said unto him, Fear not, Zacharias: for thy prayer is heard; and thy wife Elisabeth shall bear thee a son, and thou shalt call his name John."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "And thou shalt have joy and gladness; and many shall rejoice at his birth."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "For he shall be great in the sight of the Lord, and shall drink neither wine nor strong drink; and he shall be filled with the Holy Ghost, even from his mother’s womb."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "And many of the children of Israel shall he turn to the Lord their God."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "And he shall go before him in the spirit and power of Elias, to turn the hearts of the fathers to the children, and the disobedient to the wisdom of the just; to make ready a people prepared for the Lord."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "And Zacharias said unto the angel, Whereby shall I know this? for I am an old man, and my wife well stricken in years."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "And the angel answering said unto him, I am Gabriel, that stand in the presence of God; and am sent to speak unto thee, and to shew thee these glad tidings."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "And, behold, thou shalt be dumb, and not able to speak, until the day that these things shall be performed, because thou believest not my words, which shall be fulfilled in their season."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "And the people waited for Zacharias, and marvelled that he tarried so long in the temple."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "And when he came out, he could not speak unto them: and they perceived that he had seen a vision in the temple: for he beckoned unto them, and remained speechless."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "And it came to pass, that, as soon as the days of his ministration were accomplished, he departed to his own house."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "And after those days his wife Elisabeth conceived, and hid herself five months, saying,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 25,
    "text": "Thus hath the Lord dealt with me in the days wherein he looked on\nme, to take away my reproach among men."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 26,
    "text": "And in the sixth month the angel Gabriel was sent from God unto a city of Galilee, named Nazareth,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 27,
    "text": "To a virgin espoused to a man whose name was Joseph, of the house of David; and the virgin’s name\nwas Mary."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 28,
    "text": "And the angel came in unto her, and said, Hail,\nthou that art\n highly favoured, the Lord\nis with thee: blessed\nart\n thou among women."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 29,
    "text": "And when she saw\nhim, she was troubled at his saying, and cast in her mind what manner of salutation this should be."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 30,
    "text": "And the angel said unto her, Fear not, Mary: for thou hast found favour with God."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 31,
    "text": "And, behold, thou shalt conceive in thy womb, and bring forth a son, and shalt call his name JESUS."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 32,
    "text": "He shall be great, and shall be called the Son of the Highest: and the Lord God shall give unto him the throne of his father David:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 33,
    "text": "And he shall reign over the house of Jacob for ever; and of his kingdom there shall be no end."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 34,
    "text": "Then said Mary unto the angel, How shall this be, seeing I know not a man?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 35,
    "text": "And the angel answered and said unto her, The Holy Ghost shall come upon thee, and the power of the Highest shall overshadow thee: therefore also that holy thing which shall be born of thee shall be called the Son of God."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 36,
    "text": "And, behold, thy cousin Elisabeth, she hath also conceived a son in her old age: and this is the sixth month with her, who was called barren."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 37,
    "text": "For with God nothing shall be impossible."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 38,
    "text": "And Mary said, Behold the handmaid of the Lord; be it unto me according to thy word. And the angel departed from her."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 39,
    "text": "And Mary arose in those days, and went into the hill country with haste, into a city of Juda;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 40,
    "text": "And entered into the house of Zacharias, and saluted Elisabeth."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 41,
    "text": "And it came to pass, that, when Elisabeth heard the salutation of Mary, the babe leaped in her womb; and Elisabeth was filled with the Holy Ghost:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 42,
    "text": "And she spake out with a loud voice, and said, Blessed\nart\n thou among women, and blessed\nis the fruit of thy womb."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 43,
    "text": "And whence\nis this to me, that the mother of my Lord should come to me?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 44,
    "text": "For, lo, as soon as the voice of thy salutation sounded in mine ears, the babe leaped in my womb for joy."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 45,
    "text": "And blessed\nis she that believed: for there shall be a performance of those things which were told her from the Lord."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 46,
    "text": "And Mary said, My soul doth magnify the Lord,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 47,
    "text": "And my spirit hath rejoiced in God my Saviour."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 48,
    "text": "For he hath regarded the low estate of his handmaiden: for, behold, from henceforth all generations shall call me blessed."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 49,
    "text": "For he that is mighty hath done to me great things; and holy\nis\n his name."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 50,
    "text": "And his mercy\nis on them that fear him from generation to generation."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 51,
    "text": "He hath shewed strength with his arm; he hath scattered the proud in the imagination of their hearts."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 52,
    "text": "He hath put down the mighty from\ntheir seats, and exalted them of low degree."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 53,
    "text": "He hath filled the hungry with good things; and the rich he hath sent empty away."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 54,
    "text": "He hath holpen his servant Israel, in remembrance of\nhis\n mercy;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 55,
    "text": "As he spake to our fathers, to Abraham, and to his seed for ever."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 56,
    "text": "And Mary abode with her about three months, and returned to her own house."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 57,
    "text": "Now Elisabeth’s full time came that she should be delivered; and she brought forth a son."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 58,
    "text": "And her neighbours and her cousins heard how the Lord had shewed great mercy upon her; and they rejoiced with her."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 59,
    "text": "And it came to pass, that on the eighth day they came to circumcise the child; and they called him Zacharias, after the name of his father."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 60,
    "text": "And his mother answered and said, Not\nso; but he shall be called John."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 61,
    "text": "And they said unto her, There is none of thy kindred that is called by this name."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 62,
    "text": "And they made signs to his father, how he would have him called."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 63,
    "text": "And he asked for a writing table, and wrote, saying, His name is John. And they marvelled all."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 64,
    "text": "And his mouth was opened immediately, and his tongue\nloosed,\n and he spake, and praised God."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 65,
    "text": "And fear came on all that dwelt round about them: and all these sayings were noised abroad throughout all the hill country of Judaea."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 66,
    "text": "And all they that heard\nthem laid\nthem up in their hearts, saying, What manner of child shall this be! And the hand of the Lord was with him."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 67,
    "text": "And his father Zacharias was filled with the Holy Ghost, and prophesied, saying,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 68,
    "text": "Blessed\nbe the Lord God of Israel; for he hath visited and redeemed his people,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 69,
    "text": "And hath raised up an horn of salvation for us in the house of his servant David;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 70,
    "text": "As he spake by the mouth of his holy prophets, which have been since the world began:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 71,
    "text": "That we should be saved from our enemies, and from the hand of all that hate us;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 72,
    "text": "To perform the mercy\npromised to our fathers, and to remember his holy covenant;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 73,
    "text": "The oath which he sware to our father Abraham,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 74,
    "text": "That he would grant unto us, that we being delivered out of the hand of our enemies might serve him without fear,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 75,
    "text": "In holiness and righteousness before him, all the days of our life."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 76,
    "text": "And thou, child, shalt be called the prophet of the Highest: for thou shalt go before the face of the Lord to prepare his ways;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 77,
    "text": "To give knowledge of salvation unto his people by the remission of their sins,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 78,
    "text": "Through the tender mercy of our God; whereby the dayspring from on high hath visited us,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 79,
    "text": "To give light to them that sit in darkness and\nin the shadow of death, to guide our feet into the way of peace."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 80,
    "text": "And the child grew, and waxed strong in spirit, and was in the deserts till the day of his shewing unto Israel."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "And it came to pass in those days, that there went out a decree from Caesar Augustus, that all the world should be taxed."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "(And this taxing was first made when Cyrenius was governor of Syria.)"
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "And all went to be taxed, every one into his own city."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "And Joseph also went up from Galilee, out of the city of Nazareth, into Judaea, unto the city of David, which is called Bethlehem; (because he was of the house and lineage of David:)"
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "To be taxed with Mary his espoused wife, being great with child."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "And so it was, that, while they were there, the days were accomplished that she should be delivered."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "And she brought forth her firstborn son, and wrapped him in swaddling clothes, and laid him in a manger; because there was no room for them in the inn."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "And there were in the same country shepherds abiding in the field, keeping watch over their flock by night."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "And, lo, the angel of the Lord came upon them, and the glory of the Lord shone round about them: and they were sore afraid."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "And the angel said unto them, Fear not: for, behold, I bring you good tidings of great joy, which shall be to all people."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "For unto you is born this day in the city of David a Saviour, which is Christ the Lord."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "And this\nshall be a sign unto you; Ye shall find the babe wrapped in swaddling clothes, lying in a manger."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "And suddenly there was with the angel a multitude of the heavenly host praising God, and saying,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "Glory to God in the highest, and on earth peace, good will toward men."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "And it came to pass, as the angels were gone away from them into heaven, the shepherds said one to another, Let us now go even unto Bethlehem, and see this thing which is come to pass, which the Lord hath made known unto us."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "And they came with haste, and found Mary, and Joseph, and the babe lying in a manger."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "And when they had seen\nit, they made known abroad the saying which was told them concerning this child."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "And all they that heard\nit wondered at those things which were told them by the shepherds."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "But Mary kept all these things, and pondered\nthem in her heart."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "And the shepherds returned, glorifying and praising God for all the things that they had heard and seen, as it was told unto them."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "And when eight days were accomplished for the circumcising of the child, his name was called JESUS, which was so named of the angel before he was conceived in the womb."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "And when the days of her purification according to the law of Moses were accomplished, they brought him to Jerusalem, to present\nhim to the Lord;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "(As it is written in the law of the Lord, Every male that openeth the womb shall be called holy to the Lord;)"
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "And to offer a sacrifice according to that which is said in the law of the Lord, A pair of turtledoves, or two young pigeons."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 25,
    "text": "And, behold, there was a man in Jerusalem, whose name\nwas\n Simeon; and the same man\nwas just and devout, waiting for the consolation of Israel: and the Holy Ghost was upon him."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 26,
    "text": "And it was revealed unto him by the Holy Ghost, that he should not see death, before he had seen the Lord’s Christ."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 27,
    "text": "And he came by the Spirit into the temple: and when the parents brought in the child Jesus, to do for him after the custom of the law,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 28,
    "text": "Then took he him up in his arms, and blessed God, and said,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 29,
    "text": "Lord, now lettest thou thy servant depart in peace, according to thy word:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 30,
    "text": "For mine eyes have seen thy salvation,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 31,
    "text": "Which thou hast prepared before the face of all people;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 32,
    "text": "A light to lighten the Gentiles, and the glory of thy people Israel."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 33,
    "text": "And Joseph and his mother marvelled at those things which were spoken of him."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 34,
    "text": "And Simeon blessed them, and said unto Mary his mother, Behold, this\nchild is set for the fall and rising again of many in Israel; and for a sign which shall be spoken against;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 35,
    "text": "(Yea, a sword shall pierce through thy own soul also,) that the thoughts of many hearts may be revealed."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 36,
    "text": "And there was one Anna, a prophetess, the daughter of Phanuel, of the tribe of Aser: she was of a great age, and had lived with an husband seven years from her virginity;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 37,
    "text": "And she\nwas a widow of about fourscore and four years, which departed not from the temple, but served\nGod with fastings and prayers night and day."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 38,
    "text": "And she coming in that instant gave thanks likewise unto the Lord, and spake of him to all them that looked for redemption in Jerusalem."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 39,
    "text": "And when they had performed all things according to the law of the Lord, they returned into Galilee, to their own city Nazareth."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 40,
    "text": "And the child grew, and waxed strong in spirit, filled with wisdom: and the grace of God was upon him."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 41,
    "text": "Now his parents went to Jerusalem every year at the feast of the passover."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 42,
    "text": "And when he was twelve years old, they went up to Jerusalem after the custom of the feast."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 43,
    "text": "And when they had fulfilled the days, as they returned, the child Jesus tarried behind in Jerusalem; and Joseph and his mother knew not\nof it."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 44,
    "text": "But they, supposing him to have been in the company, went a day’s journey; and they sought him among\ntheir kinsfolk and acquaintance."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 45,
    "text": "And when they found him not, they turned back again to Jerusalem, seeking him."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 46,
    "text": "And it came to pass, that after three days they found him in the temple, sitting in the midst of the doctors, both hearing them, and asking them questions."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 47,
    "text": "And all that heard him were astonished at his understanding and answers."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 48,
    "text": "And when they saw him, they were amazed: and his mother said unto him, Son, why hast thou thus dealt with us? behold, thy father and I have sought thee sorrowing."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 49,
    "text": "And he said unto them,\nHow is it that ye sought me? wist ye not that I must be about my Father’s business?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 50,
    "text": "And they understood not the saying which he spake unto them."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 51,
    "text": "And he went down with them, and came to Nazareth, and was subject unto them: but his mother kept all these sayings in her heart."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 52,
    "text": "And Jesus increased in wisdom and stature, and in favour with God and man."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "Now in the fifteenth year of the reign of Tiberius Caesar, Pontius Pilate being governor of Judaea, and Herod being tetrarch of Galilee, and his brother Philip tetrarch of Ituraea and of the region of Trachonitis, and Lysanias the tetrarch of Abilene,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "Annas and Caiaphas being the high priests, the word of God came unto John the son of Zacharias in the wilderness."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "And he came into all the country about Jordan, preaching the baptism of repentance for the remission of sins;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "As it is written in the book of the words of Esaias the prophet, saying, The voice of one crying in the wilderness, Prepare ye the way of the Lord, make his paths straight."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "Every valley shall be filled, and every mountain and hill shall be brought low; and the crooked shall be made straight, and the rough ways\nshall be made smooth;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "And all flesh shall see the salvation of God."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "Then said he to the multitude that came forth to be baptized of him, O generation of vipers, who hath warned you to flee from the wrath to come?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "Bring forth therefore fruits worthy of repentance, and begin not to say within yourselves, We have Abraham to\nour father: for I say unto you, That God is able of these stones to raise up children unto Abraham."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "And now also the axe is laid unto the root of the trees: every tree therefore which bringeth not forth good fruit is hewn down, and cast into the fire."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "And the people asked him, saying, What shall we do then?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "He answereth and saith unto them, He that hath two coats, let him impart to him that hath none; and he that hath meat, let him do likewise."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "Then came also publicans to be baptized, and said unto him, Master, what shall we do?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "And he said unto them, Exact no more than that which is appointed you."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "And the soldiers likewise demanded of him, saying, And what shall we do? And he said unto them, Do violence to no man, neither accuse\nany\n falsely; and be content with your wages."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "And as the people were in expectation, and all men mused in their hearts of John, whether he were the Christ, or not;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "John answered, saying unto\nthem all, I indeed baptize you with water; but one mightier than I cometh, the latchet of whose shoes I am not worthy to unloose: he shall baptize you with the Holy Ghost and with fire:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "Whose fan\nis in his hand, and he will throughly purge his floor, and will gather the wheat into his garner; but the chaff he will burn with fire unquenchable."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "And many other things in his exhortation preached he unto the people."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "But Herod the tetrarch, being reproved by him for Herodias his brother Philip’s wife, and for all the evils which Herod had done,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "Added yet this above all, that he shut up John in prison."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "Now when all the people were baptized, it came to pass, that Jesus also being baptized, and praying, the heaven was opened,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "And the Holy Ghost descended in a bodily shape like a dove upon him, and a voice came from heaven, which said, Thou art my beloved Son; in thee I am well pleased."
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "And Jesus himself began to be about thirty years of age, being (as was supposed) the son of Joseph, which was\nthe son of Heli,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "Which was\nthe son of Matthat, which was\nthe son\n of Levi, which was\nthe son of Melchi, which was\nthe son\n of Janna, which was\nthe son of Joseph,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 25,
    "text": "Which was\nthe son of Mattathias, which was\nthe son\n of Amos, which was\nthe son of Naum, which was\nthe son\n of Esli, which was\nthe son of Nagge,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 26,
    "text": "Which was\nthe son of Maath, which was\nthe son of Mattathias, which was\nthe son of Semei, which was\nthe son\n of Joseph, which was\nthe son of Juda,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 27,
    "text": "Which was\nthe son of Joanna, which was\nthe son\n of Rhesa, which was\nthe son of Zorobabel, which was\nthe son of Salathiel, which was\nthe son of Neri,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 28,
    "text": "Which was\nthe son of Melchi, which was\nthe son\n of Addi, which was\nthe son of Cosam, which was\nthe son\n of Elmodam, which was\nthe son of Er,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 29,
    "text": "Which was\nthe son of Jose, which was\nthe son of Eliezer, which was\nthe son of Jorim, which was\nthe son\n of Matthat, which was\nthe son of Levi,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 30,
    "text": "Which was\nthe son of Simeon, which was\nthe son\n of Juda, which was\nthe son of Joseph, which was\nthe son\n of Jonan, which was\nthe son of Eliakim,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 31,
    "text": "Which was\nthe son of Melea, which was\nthe son of Menan, which was\nthe son of Mattatha, which was\nthe son\n of Nathan, which was\nthe son of David,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 32,
    "text": "Which was\nthe son of Jesse, which was\nthe son of Obed, which was\nthe son of Booz, which was\nthe son of Salmon, which was\nthe son of Naasson,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 33,
    "text": "Which was\nthe son of Aminadab, which was\nthe son\n of Aram, which was\nthe son of Esrom, which was\nthe son\n of Phares, which was\nthe son of Juda,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 34,
    "text": "Which was\nthe son of Jacob, which was\nthe son of Isaac, which was\nthe son of Abraham, which was\nthe son\n of Thara, which was\nthe son of Nachor,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Luke",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 35,
    "text": "Which was\nthe son of Saruch, which was\nthe son\n of Ragau, which was\nthe son of Phalec, which was\nthe son\n of Heber, which was\nthe son of Sala,"
  },
  {
