    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 26,
    "text": "And they gave forth their lots; and the lot fell upon Matthias; and he was numbered with the eleven apostles."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "Paul, a servant of Jesus Christ, called\nto be an apostle, separated unto the gospel of God,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "(Which he had promised afore by his prophets in the holy scriptures,)"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "Concerning his Son Jesus Christ our Lord, which was made of the seed of David according to the flesh;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "And declared\nto be the Son of God with power, according to the spirit of holiness, by the resurrection from the dead:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "By whom we have received grace and apostleship, for obedience to the faith among all nations, for his name:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "Among whom are ye also the called of Jesus Christ:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "To all that be in Rome, beloved of God, called\nto be saints: Grace to you and peace from God our Father, and the Lord Jesus Christ."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "First, I thank my God through Jesus Christ for you all, that your faith is spoken of throughout the whole world."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "For God is my witness, whom I serve with my spirit in the gospel of his Son, that without ceasing I make mention of you always in my prayers;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "Making request, if by any means now at length I might have a prosperous journey by the will of God to come unto you."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "For I long to see you, that I may impart unto you some spiritual gift, to the end ye may be established;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "That is, that I may be comforted together with you by the mutual faith both of you and me."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "Now I would not have you ignorant, brethren, that oftentimes I purposed to come unto you, (but was let hitherto,) that I might have some fruit among you also, even as among other Gentiles."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "I am debtor both to the Greeks, and to the Barbarians; both to the wise, and to the unwise."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "So, as much as in me is, I am ready to preach the gospel to you that are at Rome also."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "For I am not ashamed of the gospel of Christ: for it is the power of God unto salvation to every one that believeth; to the Jew first, and also to the Greek."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "For therein is the righteousness of God revealed from faith to faith: as it is written, The just shall live by faith."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "For the wrath of God is revealed from heaven against all ungodliness and unrighteousness of men, who hold the truth in unrighteousness;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "Because that which may be known of God is manifest in them; for God hath shewed\nit unto them."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "For the invisible things of him from the creation of the world are clearly seen, being understood by the things that are made,\neven\n his eternal power and Godhead; so that they are without excuse:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "Because that, when they knew God, they glorified\nhim not as God, neither were thankful; but became vain in their imaginations, and their foolish heart was darkened."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "Professing themselves to be wise, they became fools,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "And changed the glory of the uncorruptible God into an image made like to corruptible man, and to birds, and fourfooted beasts, and creeping things."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "Wherefore God also gave them up to uncleanness through the lusts of their own hearts, to dishonour their own bodies between themselves:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 25,
    "text": "Who changed the truth of God into a lie, and worshipped and served the creature more than the Creator, who is blessed for ever. Amen."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 26,
    "text": "For this cause God gave them up unto vile affections: for even their women did change the natural use into that which is against nature:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 27,
    "text": "And likewise also the men, leaving the natural use of the woman, burned in their lust one toward another; men with men working that which is unseemly, and receiving in themselves that recompence of their error which was meet."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 28,
    "text": "And even as they did not like to retain God in\ntheir knowledge, God gave them over to a reprobate mind, to do those things which are not convenient;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 29,
    "text": "Being filled with all unrighteousness, fornication, wickedness, covetousness, maliciousness; full of envy, murder, debate, deceit, malignity; whisperers,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 30,
    "text": "Backbiters, haters of God, despiteful, proud, boasters, inventors of evil things, disobedient to parents,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 31,
    "text": "Without understanding, covenantbreakers, without natural affection, implacable, unmerciful:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 32,
    "text": "Who knowing the judgment of God, that they which commit such things are worthy of death, not only do the same, but have pleasure in them that do them."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "Therefore thou art inexcusable, O man, whosoever thou art that judgest: for wherein thou judgest another, thou condemnest thyself; for thou that judgest doest the same things."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "But we are sure that the judgment of God is according to truth against them which commit such things."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "And thinkest thou this, O man, that judgest them which do such things, and doest the same, that thou shalt escape the judgment of God?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "Or despisest thou the riches of his goodness and forbearance and longsuffering; not knowing that the goodness of God leadeth thee to repentance?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "But after thy hardness and impenitent heart treasurest up unto thyself wrath against the day of wrath and revelation of the righteous judgment of God;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "Who will render to every man according to his deeds:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "To them who by patient continuance in well doing seek for glory and honour and immortality, eternal life:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "But unto them that are contentious, and do not obey the truth, but obey unrighteousness, indignation and wrath,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "Tribulation and anguish, upon every soul of man that doeth evil, of the Jew first, and also of the Gentile;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "But glory, honour, and peace, to every man that worketh good, to the Jew first, and also to the Gentile:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "For there is no respect of persons with God."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "For as many as have sinned without law shall also perish without law: and as many as have sinned in the law shall be judged by the law;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "(For not the hearers of the law\nare just before God, but the doers of the law shall be justified."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "For when the Gentiles, which have not the law, do by nature the things contained in the law, these, having not the law, are a law unto themselves:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "Which shew the work of the law written in their hearts, their conscience also bearing witness, and\ntheir thoughts the mean while accusing or else excusing one another;)"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "In the day when God shall judge the secrets of men by Jesus Christ according to my gospel."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "Behold, thou art called a Jew, and restest in the law, and makest thy boast of God,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "And knowest\nhis will, and approvest the things that are more excellent, being instructed out of the law;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "And art confident that thou thyself art a guide of the blind, a light of them which are in darkness,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "An instructor of the foolish, a teacher of babes, which hast the form of knowledge and of the truth in the law."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "Thou therefore which teachest another, teachest thou not thyself? thou that preachest a man should not steal, dost thou steal?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "Thou that sayest a man should not commit adultery, dost thou commit adultery? thou that abhorrest idols, dost thou commit sacrilege?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "Thou that makest thy boast of the law, through breaking the law dishonourest thou God?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "For the name of God is blasphemed among the Gentiles through you, as it is written."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 25,
    "text": "For circumcision verily profiteth, if thou keep the law: but if thou be a breaker of the law, thy circumcision is made uncircumcision."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 26,
    "text": "Therefore if the uncircumcision keep the righteousness of the law, shall not his uncircumcision be counted for circumcision?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 27,
    "text": "And shall not uncircumcision which is by nature, if it fulfil the law, judge thee, who by the letter and circumcision dost transgress the law?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 28,
    "text": "For he is not a Jew, which is one outwardly; neither\nis that\n circumcision, which is outward in the flesh:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 29,
    "text": "But he\nis a Jew, which is one inwardly; and circumcision\nis that of the heart, in the spirit,\nand not in the letter; whose praise\nis not of men, but of God."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "What advantage then hath the Jew? or what profit\nis there\n of circumcision?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "Much every way: chiefly, because that unto them were committed the oracles of God."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "For what if some did not believe? shall their unbelief make the faith of God without effect?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "God forbid: yea, let God be true, but every man a liar; as it is written, That thou mightest be justified in thy sayings, and mightest overcome when thou art judged."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "But if our unrighteousness commend the righteousness of God, what shall we say?\nIs God unrighteous who taketh vengeance? (I speak as a man)"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "God forbid: for then how shall God judge the world?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "For if the truth of God hath more abounded through my lie unto his glory; why yet am I also judged as a sinner?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "And not\nrather, (as we be slanderously reported, and as some affirm that we say,) Let us do evil, that good may come? whose damnation is just."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "What then? are we better\nthan they? No, in no wise: for we have before proved both Jews and Gentiles, that they are all under sin;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "As it is written, There is none righteous, no, not one:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "There is none that understandeth, there is none that seeketh after God."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "They are all gone out of the way, they are together become unprofitable; there is none that doeth good, no, not one."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "Their throat\nis an open sepulchre; with their tongues they have used deceit; the poison of asps\nis under their lips:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "Whose mouth\nis full of cursing and bitterness:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "Their feet\nare swift to shed blood:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "Destruction and misery\nare in their ways:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "And the way of peace have they not known:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "There is no fear of God before their eyes."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "Now we know that what things soever the law saith, it saith to them who are under the law: that every mouth may be stopped, and all the world may become guilty before God."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "Therefore by the deeds of the law there shall no flesh be justified in his sight: for by the law\nis the knowledge of sin."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "But now the righteousness of God without the law is manifested, being witnessed by the law and the prophets;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "Even the righteousness of God\nwhich is by faith of Jesus Christ unto all and upon all them that believe: for there is no difference:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "For all have sinned, and come short of the glory of God;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "Being justified freely by his grace through the redemption that is in Christ Jesus:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 25,
    "text": "Whom God hath set forth\nto be a propitiation through faith in his blood, to declare his righteousness for the remission of sins that are past, through the forbearance of God;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 26,
    "text": "To declare,\nI say, at this time his righteousness: that he might be just, and the justifier of him which believeth in Jesus."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 27,
    "text": "Where\nis boasting then? It is excluded. By what law? of works? Nay: but by the law of faith."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 28,
    "text": "Therefore we conclude that a man is justified by faith without the deeds of the law."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 29,
    "text": "Is he the God of the Jews only?\nis he not also of the Gentiles? Yes, of the Gentiles also:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 30,
    "text": "Seeing\nit is one God, which shall justify the circumcision by faith, and uncircumcision through faith."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 31,
    "text": "Do we then make void the law through faith? God forbid: yea, we establish the law."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "What shall we say then that Abraham our father, as pertaining to the flesh, hath found?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "For if Abraham were justified by works, he hath\nwhereof to glory; but not before God."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "For what saith the scripture? Abraham believed God, and it was counted unto him for righteousness."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "Now to him that worketh is the reward not reckoned of grace, but of debt."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "But to him that worketh not, but believeth on him that justifieth the ungodly, his faith is counted for righteousness."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "Even as David also describeth the blessedness of the man, unto whom God imputeth righteousness without works,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "Saying, Blessed\nare they whose iniquities are forgiven, and whose sins are covered."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "Blessed\nis the man to whom the Lord will not impute sin."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "Cometh this blessedness then upon the circumcision\nonly,\n or upon the uncircumcision also? for we say that faith was reckoned to Abraham for righteousness."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "How was it then reckoned? when he was in circumcision, or in uncircumcision? Not in circumcision, but in uncircumcision."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "And he received the sign of circumcision, a seal of the righteousness of the faith which\nhe had yet being uncircumcised: that he might be the father of all them that believe, though they be not circumcised; that righteousness might be imputed unto them also:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "And the father of circumcision to them who are not of the circumcision only, but who also walk in the steps of that faith of our father Abraham, which\nhe had being\nyet uncircumcised."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "For the promise, that he should be the heir of the world,\nwas\n not to Abraham, or to his seed, through the law, but through the righteousness of faith."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "For if they which are of the law\nbe heirs, faith is made void, and the promise made of none effect:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "Because the law worketh wrath: for where no law is,\nthere is\n no transgression."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "Therefore\nit is of faith, that\nit might be by grace; to the end the promise might be sure to all the seed; not to that only which is of the law, but to that also which is of the faith of Abraham; who is the father of us all,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "(As it is written, I have made thee a father of many nations,) before him whom he believed,\neven God, who quickeneth the dead, and calleth those things which be not as though they were."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "Who against hope believed in hope, that he might become the father of many nations, according to that which was spoken, So shall thy seed be."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "And being not weak in faith, he considered not his own body now dead, when he was about an hundred years old, neither yet the deadness of Sarah’s womb:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "He staggered not at the promise of God through unbelief; but was strong in faith, giving glory to God;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "And being fully persuaded that, what he had promised, he was able also to perform."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "And therefore it was imputed to him for righteousness."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "Now it was not written for his sake alone, that it was imputed to him;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "But for us also, to whom it shall be imputed, if we believe on him that raised up Jesus our Lord from the dead;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 25,
    "text": "Who was delivered for our offences, and was raised again for our justification."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "Therefore being justified by faith, we have peace with God through our Lord Jesus Christ:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "By whom also we have access by faith into this grace wherein we stand, and rejoice in hope of the glory of God."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "And not only\nso, but we glory in tribulations also: knowing that tribulation worketh patience;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "And patience, experience; and experience, hope:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "And hope maketh not ashamed; because the love of God is shed abroad in our hearts by the Holy Ghost which is given unto us."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "For when we were yet without strength, in due time Christ died for the ungodly."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "For scarcely for a righteous man will one die: yet peradventure for a good man some would even dare to die."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "But God commendeth his love toward us, in that, while we were yet sinners, Christ died for us."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "Much more then, being now justified by his blood, we shall be saved from wrath through him."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "For if, when we were enemies, we were reconciled to God by the death of his Son, much more, being reconciled, we shall be saved by his life."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "And not only\nso, but we also joy in God through our Lord Jesus Christ, by whom we have now received the atonement."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "Wherefore, as by one man sin entered into the world, and death by sin; and so death passed upon all men, for that all have sinned:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "(For until the law sin was in the world: but sin is not imputed when there is no law."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "Nevertheless death reigned from Adam to Moses, even over them that had not sinned after the similitude of Adam’s transgression, who is the figure of him that was to come."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "But not as the offence, so also\nis the free gift. For if through the offence of one many be dead, much more the grace of God, and the gift by grace,\nwhich is by one man, Jesus Christ, hath abounded unto many."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "And not as\nit was by one that sinned,\nso is the gift: for the judgment\nwas by one to condemnation, but the free gift\nis of many offences unto justification."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "For if by one man’s offence death reigned by one; much more they which receive abundance of grace and of the gift of righteousness shall reign in life by one, Jesus Christ.)"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "Therefore as by the offence of one\njudgment came upon all men to condemnation; even so by the righteousness of one\nthe free gift came\n upon all men unto justification of life."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "For as by one man’s disobedience many were made sinners, so by the obedience of one shall many be made righteous."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "Moreover the law entered, that the offence might abound. But where sin abounded, grace did much more abound:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "That as sin hath reigned unto death, even so might grace reign through righteousness unto eternal life by Jesus Christ our Lord."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "What shall we say then? Shall we continue in sin, that grace may abound?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "God forbid. How shall we, that are dead to sin, live any longer therein?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "Know ye not, that so many of us as were baptized into Jesus Christ were baptized into his death?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "Therefore we are buried with him by baptism into death: that like as Christ was raised up from the dead by the glory of the Father, even so we also should walk in newness of life."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "For if we have been planted together in the likeness of his death, we shall be also\nin the likeness of his resurrection:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "Knowing this, that our old man is crucified with\nhim, that the body of sin might be destroyed, that henceforth we should not serve sin."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "For he that is dead is freed from sin."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "Now if we be dead with Christ, we believe that we shall also live with him:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "Knowing that Christ being raised from the dead dieth no more; death hath no more dominion over him."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "For in that he died, he died unto sin once: but in that he liveth, he liveth unto God."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "Likewise reckon ye also yourselves to be dead indeed unto sin, but alive unto God through Jesus Christ our Lord."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "Let not sin therefore reign in your mortal body, that ye should obey it in the lusts thereof."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "Neither yield ye your members\nas instruments of unrighteousness unto sin: but yield yourselves unto God, as those that are alive from the dead, and your members\nas instruments of righteousness unto God."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "For sin shall not have dominion over you: for ye are not under the law, but under grace."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "What then? shall we sin, because we are not under the law, but under grace? God forbid."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "Know ye not, that to whom ye yield yourselves servants to obey, his servants ye are to whom ye obey; whether of sin unto death, or of obedience unto righteousness?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "But God be thanked, that ye were the servants of sin, but ye have obeyed from the heart that form of doctrine which was delivered you."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "Being then made free from sin, ye became the servants of righteousness."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "I speak after the manner of men because of the infirmity of your flesh: for as ye have yielded your members servants to uncleanness and to iniquity unto iniquity; even so now yield your members servants to righteousness unto holiness."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "For when ye were the servants of sin, ye were free from righteousness."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "What fruit had ye then in those things whereof ye are now ashamed? for the end of those things\nis death."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "But now being made free from sin, and become servants to God, ye have your fruit unto holiness, and the end everlasting life."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "For the wages of sin\nis death; but the gift of God\nis\n eternal life through Jesus Christ our Lord."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "Know ye not, brethren, (for I speak to them that know the law,) how that the law hath dominion over a man as long as he liveth?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "For the woman which hath an husband is bound by the law to\nher\n husband so long as he liveth; but if the husband be dead, she is loosed from the law of\nher husband."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "So then if, while\nher husband liveth, she be married to another man, she shall be called an adulteress: but if her husband be dead, she is free from that law; so that she is no adulteress, though she be married to another man."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "Wherefore, my brethren, ye also are become dead to the law by the body of Christ; that ye should be married to another,\neven to him who is raised from the dead, that we should bring forth fruit unto God."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "For when we were in the flesh, the motions of sins, which were by the law, did work in our members to bring forth fruit unto death."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "But now we are delivered from the law, that being dead wherein we were held; that we should serve in newness of spirit, and not\nin the oldness of the letter."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "What shall we say then?\nIs the law sin? God forbid. Nay, I had not known sin, but by the law: for I had not known lust, except the law had said, Thou shalt not covet."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "But sin, taking occasion by the commandment, wrought in me all manner of concupiscence. For without the law sin\nwas dead."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "For I was alive without the law once: but when the commandment came, sin revived, and I died."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "And the commandment, which\nwas ordained to life, I found\nto be unto death."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "For sin, taking occasion by the commandment, deceived me, and by it slew\nme."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "Wherefore the law\nis holy, and the commandment holy, and just, and good."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "Was then that which is good made death unto me? God forbid. But sin, that it might appear sin, working death in me by that which is good; that sin by the commandment might become exceeding sinful."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "For we know that the law is spiritual: but I am carnal, sold under sin."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "For that which I do I allow not: for what I would, that do I not; but what I hate, that do I."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "If then I do that which I would not, I consent unto the law that\nit is good."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "Now then it is no more I that do it, but sin that dwelleth in me."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "For I know that in me (that is, in my flesh,) dwelleth no good thing: for to will is present with me; but\nhow to perform that which is good I find not."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "For the good that I would I do not: but the evil which I would not, that I do."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "Now if I do that I would not, it is no more I that do it, but sin that dwelleth in me."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "I find then a law, that, when I would do good, evil is present with me."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "For I delight in the law of God after the inward man:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "But I see another law in my members, warring against the law of my mind, and bringing me into captivity to the law of sin which is in my members."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "O wretched man that I am! who shall deliver me from the body of this death?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 25,
    "text": "I thank God through Jesus Christ our Lord. So then with the mind I myself serve the law of God; but with the flesh the law of sin."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "There is therefore now no condemnation to them which are in Christ Jesus, who walk not after the flesh, but after the Spirit."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "For the law of the Spirit of life in Christ Jesus hath made me free from the law of sin and death."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "For what the law could not do, in that it was weak through the flesh, God sending his own Son in the likeness of sinful flesh, and for sin, condemned sin in the flesh:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "That the righteousness of the law might be fulfilled in us, who walk not after the flesh, but after the Spirit."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "For they that are after the flesh do mind the things of the flesh; but they that are after the Spirit the things of the Spirit."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "For to be carnally minded\nis death; but to be spiritually minded\nis life and peace."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "Because the carnal mind\nis enmity against God: for it is not subject to the law of God, neither indeed can be."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "So then they that are in the flesh cannot please God."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "But ye are not in the flesh, but in the Spirit, if so be that the Spirit of God dwell in you. Now if any man have not the Spirit of Christ, he is none of his."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "And if Christ\nbe in you, the body\nis dead because of sin; but the Spirit\nis life because of righteousness."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "But if the Spirit of him that raised up Jesus from the dead dwell in you, he that raised up Christ from the dead shall also quicken your mortal bodies by his Spirit that dwelleth in you."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "Therefore, brethren, we are debtors, not to the flesh, to live after the flesh."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "For if ye live after the flesh, ye shall die: but if ye through the Spirit do mortify the deeds of the body, ye shall live."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "For as many as are led by the Spirit of God, they are the sons of God."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "For ye have not received the spirit of bondage again to fear; but ye have received the Spirit of adoption, whereby we cry, Abba, Father."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "The Spirit itself beareth witness with our spirit, that we are the children of God:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "And if children, then heirs; heirs of God, and joint-heirs with Christ; if so be that we suffer with\nhim, that we may be also glorified together."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "For I reckon that the sufferings of this present time\nare\n not worthy\nto be compared with the glory which shall be revealed in us."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "For the earnest expectation of the creature waiteth for the manifestation of the sons of God."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "For the creature was made subject to vanity, not willingly, but by reason of him who hath subjected\nthe same in hope,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "Because the creature itself also shall be delivered from the bondage of corruption into the glorious liberty of the children of God."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "For we know that the whole creation groaneth and travaileth in pain together until now."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "And not only\nthey, but ourselves also, which have the firstfruits of the Spirit, even we ourselves groan within ourselves, waiting for the adoption,\nto wit, the redemption of our body."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "For we are saved by hope: but hope that is seen is not hope: for what a man seeth, why doth he yet hope for?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 25,
    "text": "But if we hope for that we see not,\nthen do we with patience wait for\nit."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 26,
    "text": "Likewise the Spirit also helpeth our infirmities: for we know not what we should pray for as we ought: but the Spirit itself maketh intercession for us with groanings which cannot be uttered."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 27,
    "text": "And he that searcheth the hearts knoweth what\nis the mind of the Spirit, because he maketh intercession for the saints according to\nthe will of God."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 28,
    "text": "And we know that all things work together for good to them that love God, to them who are the called according to\nhis purpose."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 29,
    "text": "For whom he did foreknow, he also did predestinate\nto be\n conformed to the image of his Son, that he might be the firstborn among many brethren."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 30,
    "text": "Moreover whom he did predestinate, them he also called: and whom he called, them he also justified: and whom he justified, them he also glorified."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 31,
    "text": "What shall we then say to these things? If God\nbe for us, who\ncan be against us?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 32,
    "text": "He that spared not his own Son, but delivered him up for us all, how shall he not with him also freely give us all things?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 33,
    "text": "Who shall lay any thing to the charge of God’s elect?\nIt is\n God that justifieth."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 34,
    "text": "Who\nis he that condemneth?\nIt is Christ that died, yea rather, that is risen again, who is even at the right hand of God, who also maketh intercession for us."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 35,
    "text": "Who shall separate us from the love of Christ?\nshall tribulation, or distress, or persecution, or famine, or nakedness, or peril, or sword?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 36,
    "text": "As it is written, For thy sake we are killed all the day long; we are accounted as sheep for the slaughter."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 37,
    "text": "Nay, in all these things we are more than conquerors through him that loved us."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 38,
    "text": "For I am persuaded, that neither death, nor life, nor angels, nor principalities, nor powers, nor things present, nor things to come,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 39,
    "text": "Nor height, nor depth, nor any other creature, shall be able to separate us from the love of God, which is in Christ Jesus our Lord."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "I say the truth in Christ, I lie not, my conscience also bearing me witness in the Holy Ghost,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "That I have great heaviness and continual sorrow in my heart."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "For I could wish that myself were accursed from Christ for my brethren, my kinsmen according to the flesh:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "Who are Israelites; to whom\npertaineth the adoption, and the glory, and the covenants, and the giving of the law, and the service\nof God, and the promises;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "Whose\nare the fathers, and of whom as concerning the flesh Christ\ncame, who is over all, God blessed for ever. Amen."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "Not as though the word of God hath taken none effect. For they\nare not all Israel, which are of Israel:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "Neither, because they are the seed of Abraham,\nare they all children: but, In Isaac shall thy seed be called."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "That is, They which are the children of the flesh, these\nare\n not the children of God: but the children of the promise are counted for the seed."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "For this\nis the word of promise, At this time will I come, and Sarah shall have a son."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "And not only\nthis; but when Rebecca also had conceived by one,\neven by our father Isaac;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "(For\nthe children being not yet born, neither having done any good or evil, that the purpose of God according to election might stand, not of works, but of him that calleth;)"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "It was said unto her, The elder shall serve the younger."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "As it is written, Jacob have I loved, but Esau have I hated."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "What shall we say then?\nIs there unrighteousness with God? God forbid."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "For he saith to Moses, I will have mercy on whom I will have mercy, and I will have compassion on whom I will have compassion."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "So then\nit is not of him that willeth, nor of him that runneth, but of God that sheweth mercy."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "For the scripture saith unto Pharaoh, Even for this same purpose have I raised thee up, that I might shew my power in thee, and that my name might be declared throughout all the earth."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "Therefore hath he mercy on whom he will\nhave mercy, and whom he will he hardeneth."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "Thou wilt say then unto me, Why doth he yet find fault? For who hath resisted his will?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "Nay but, O man, who art thou that repliest against God? Shall the thing formed say to him that formed\nit, Why hast thou made me thus?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "Hath not the potter power over the clay, of the same lump to make one vessel unto honour, and another unto dishonour?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "What if God, willing to shew\nhis wrath, and to make his power known, endured with much longsuffering the vessels of wrath fitted to destruction:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "And that he might make known the riches of his glory on the vessels of mercy, which he had afore prepared unto glory,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "Even us, whom he hath called, not of the Jews only, but also of the Gentiles?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 25,
    "text": "As he saith also in Osee, I will call them my people, which were not my people; and her beloved, which was not beloved."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 26,
    "text": "And it shall come to pass,\nthat in the place where it was said unto them, Ye\nare not my people; there shall they be called the children of the living God."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 27,
    "text": "Esaias also crieth concerning Israel, Though the number of the children of Israel be as the sand of the sea, a remnant shall be saved:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 28,
    "text": "For he will finish the work, and cut\nit short in righteousness: because a short work will the Lord make upon the earth."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 29,
    "text": "And as Esaias said before, Except the Lord of Sabaoth had left us a seed, we had been as Sodoma, and been made like unto Gomorrha."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 30,
    "text": "What shall we say then? That the Gentiles, which followed not after righteousness, have attained to righteousness, even the righteousness which is of faith."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 31,
    "text": "But Israel, which followed after the law of righteousness, hath not attained to the law of righteousness."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 32,
    "text": "Wherefore? Because\nthey sought it not by faith, but as it were by the works of the law. For they stumbled at that stumblingstone;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 33,
    "text": "As it is written, Behold, I lay in Sion a stumblingstone and rock of offence: and whosoever believeth on him shall not be ashamed."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "Brethren, my heart’s desire and prayer to God for Israel is, that they might be saved."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "For I bear them record that they have a zeal of God, but not according to knowledge."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "For they being ignorant of God’s righteousness, and going about to establish their own righteousness, have not submitted themselves unto the righteousness of God."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "For Christ\nis the end of the law for righteousness to every one that believeth."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "For Moses describeth the righteousness which is of the law, That the man which doeth those things shall live by them."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "But the righteousness which is of faith speaketh on this wise, Say not in thine heart, Who shall ascend into heaven? (that is, to bring Christ down\nfrom above:)"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "Or, Who shall descend into the deep? (that is, to bring up Christ again from the dead.)"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "But what saith it? The word is nigh thee,\neven in thy mouth, and in thy heart: that is, the word of faith, which we preach;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "That if thou shalt confess with thy mouth the Lord Jesus, and shalt believe in thine heart that God hath raised him from the dead, thou shalt be saved."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "For with the heart man believeth unto righteousness; and with the mouth confession is made unto salvation."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "For the scripture saith, Whosoever believeth on him shall not be ashamed."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "For there is no difference between the Jew and the Greek: for the same Lord over all is rich unto all that call upon him."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "For whosoever shall call upon the name of the Lord shall be saved."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "How then shall they call on him in whom they have not believed? and how shall they believe in him of whom they have not heard? and how shall they hear without a preacher?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "And how shall they preach, except they be sent? as it is written, How beautiful are the feet of them that preach the gospel of peace, and bring glad tidings of good things!"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "But they have not all obeyed the gospel. For Esaias saith, Lord, who hath believed our report?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "So then faith\ncometh by hearing, and hearing by the word of God."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "But I say, Have they not heard? Yes verily, their sound went into all the earth, and their words unto the ends of the world."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "But I say, Did not Israel know? First Moses saith, I will provoke you to jealousy by\nthem that are no people,\nand by a foolish nation I will anger you."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "But Esaias is very bold, and saith, I was found of them that sought me not; I was made manifest unto them that asked not after me."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "But to Israel he saith, All day long I have stretched forth my hands unto a disobedient and gainsaying people."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "I say then, Hath God cast away his people? God forbid. For I also am an Israelite, of the seed of Abraham,\nof the tribe of Benjamin."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "God hath not cast away his people which he foreknew. Wot ye not what the scripture saith of Elias? how he maketh intercession to God against Israel, saying,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "Lord, they have killed thy prophets, and digged down thine altars; and I am left alone, and they seek my life."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "But what saith the answer of God unto him? I have reserved to myself seven thousand men, who have not bowed the knee to\nthe image of\n Baal."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "Even so then at this present time also there is a remnant according to the election of grace."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "And if by grace, then\nis it no more of works: otherwise grace is no more grace. But if\nit be of works, then is it no more grace: otherwise work is no more work."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "What then? Israel hath not obtained that which he seeketh for; but the election hath obtained it, and the rest were blinded"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "(According as it is written, God hath given them the spirit of slumber, eyes that they should not see, and ears that they should not hear;) unto this day."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "And David saith, Let their table be made a snare, and a trap, and a stumblingblock, and a recompence unto them:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "Let their eyes be darkened, that they may not see, and bow down their back alway."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "I say then, Have they stumbled that they should fall? God forbid: but\nrather through their fall salvation\nis come unto the Gentiles, for to provoke them to jealousy."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "Now if the fall of them\nbe the riches of the world, and the diminishing of them the riches of the Gentiles; how much more their fulness?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "For I speak to you Gentiles, inasmuch as I am the apostle of the Gentiles, I magnify mine office:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "If by any means I may provoke to emulation\nthem which are\n my flesh, and might save some of them."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "For if the casting away of them\nbe the reconciling of the world, what\nshall the receiving\nof them be, but life from the dead?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "For if the firstfruit\nbe holy, the lump\nis also\nholy: and if the root\nbe holy, so\nare the branches."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "And if some of the branches be broken off, and thou, being a wild olive tree, wert graffed in among them, and with them partakest of the root and fatness of the olive tree;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "Boast not against the branches. But if thou boast, thou bearest not the root, but the root thee."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "Thou wilt say then, The branches were broken off, that I might be graffed in."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "Well; because of unbelief they were broken off, and thou standest by faith. Be not highminded, but fear:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "For if God spared not the natural branches,\ntake heed lest he also spare not thee."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "Behold therefore the goodness and severity of God: on them which fell, severity; but toward thee, goodness, if thou continue in\nhis goodness: otherwise thou also shalt be cut off."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "And they also, if they abide not still in unbelief, shall be graffed in: for God is able to graff them in again."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "For if thou wert cut out of the olive tree which is wild by nature, and wert graffed contrary to nature into a good olive tree: how much more shall these, which be the natural\nbranches, be graffed into their own olive tree?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 25,
    "text": "For I would not, brethren, that ye should be ignorant of this mystery, lest ye should be wise in your own conceits; that blindness in part is happened to Israel, until the fulness of the Gentiles be come in."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 26,
    "text": "And so all Israel shall be saved: as it is written, There shall come out of Sion the Deliverer, and shall turn away ungodliness from Jacob:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 27,
    "text": "For this\nis my covenant unto them, when I shall take away their sins."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 28,
    "text": "As concerning the gospel,\nthey are enemies for your sakes: but as touching the election,\nthey are beloved for the fathers’ sakes."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 29,
    "text": "For the gifts and calling of God\nare without repentance."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 30,
    "text": "For as ye in times past have not believed God, yet have now obtained mercy through their unbelief:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 31,
    "text": "Even so have these also now not believed, that through your mercy they also may obtain mercy."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 32,
    "text": "For God hath concluded them all in unbelief, that he might have mercy upon all."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 33,
    "text": "O the depth of the riches both of the wisdom and knowledge of God! how unsearchable\nare his judgments, and his ways past finding out!"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 34,
    "text": "For who hath known the mind of the Lord? or who hath been his counsellor?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 35,
    "text": "Or who hath first given to him, and it shall be recompensed unto him again?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 36,
    "text": "For of him, and through him, and to him,\nare all things: to whom\nbe glory for ever. Amen."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "I beseech you therefore, brethren, by the mercies of God, that ye present your bodies a living sacrifice, holy, acceptable unto God,\nwhich is\n your reasonable service."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "And be not conformed to this world: but be ye transformed by the renewing of your mind, that ye may prove what is that good, and acceptable, and perfect, will of God."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "For I say, through the grace given unto me, to every man that is among you, not to think\nof himself more highly than he ought to think; but to think soberly, according as God hath dealt to every man the measure of faith."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "For as we have many members in one body, and all members have not the same office:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "So we,\nbeing many, are one body in Christ, and every one members one of another."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "Having then gifts differing according to the grace that is given to us, whether prophecy,\nlet us prophesy according to the proportion of faith;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "Or ministry,\nlet us wait on\nour ministering: or he that teacheth, on teaching;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "Or he that exhorteth, on exhortation: he that giveth,\nlet him do it\n with simplicity; he that ruleth, with diligence; he that sheweth mercy, with cheerfulness."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "Let love be without dissimulation. Abhor that which is evil; cleave to that which is good."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "Be kindly affectioned one to another with brotherly love; in honour preferring one another;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "Not slothful in business; fervent in spirit; serving the Lord;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "Rejoicing in hope; patient in tribulation; continuing instant in prayer;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "Distributing to the necessity of saints; given to hospitality."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "Bless them which persecute you: bless, and curse not."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "Rejoice with them that do rejoice, and weep with them that weep."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "Be of the same mind one toward another. Mind not high things, but condescend to men of low estate. Be not wise in your own conceits."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "Recompense to no man evil for evil. Provide things honest in the sight of all men."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "If it be possible, as much as lieth in you, live peaceably with all men."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "Dearly beloved, avenge not yourselves, but\nrather give place unto wrath: for it is written, Vengeance\nis mine; I will repay, saith the Lord."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "Therefore if thine enemy hunger, feed him; if he thirst, give him drink: for in so doing thou shalt heap coals of fire on his head."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "Be not overcome of evil, but overcome evil with good."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "Let every soul be subject unto the higher powers. For there is no power but of God: the powers that be are ordained of God."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "Whosoever therefore resisteth the power, resisteth the ordinance of God: and they that resist shall receive to themselves damnation."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "For rulers are not a terror to good works, but to the evil. Wilt thou then not be afraid of the power? do that which is good, and thou shalt have praise of the same:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "For he is the minister of God to thee for good. But if thou do that which is evil, be afraid; for he beareth not the sword in vain: for he is the minister of God, a revenger to\nexecute wrath upon him that doeth evil."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "Wherefore\nye must needs be subject, not only for wrath, but also for conscience sake."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "For for this cause pay ye tribute also: for they are God’s ministers, attending continually upon this very thing."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "Render therefore to all their dues: tribute to whom tribute\nis due;\n custom to whom custom; fear to whom fear; honour to whom honour."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "Owe no man any thing, but to love one another: for he that loveth another hath fulfilled the law."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "For this, Thou shalt not commit adultery, Thou shalt not kill, Thou shalt not steal, Thou shalt not bear false witness, Thou shalt not covet; and if\nthere be any other commandment, it is briefly comprehended in this saying, namely, Thou shalt love thy neighbour as thyself."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "Love worketh no ill to his neighbour: therefore love\nis the fulfilling of the law."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "And that, knowing the time, that now\nit is high time to awake out of sleep: for now\nis our salvation nearer than when we believed."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "The night is far spent, the day is at hand: let us therefore cast off the works of darkness, and let us put on the armour of light."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "Let us walk honestly, as in the day; not in rioting and drunkenness, not in chambering and wantonness, not in strife and envying."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "But put ye on the Lord Jesus Christ, and make not provision for the flesh, to\nfulfil the lusts\nthereof."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "Him that is weak in the faith receive ye,\nbut not to doubtful disputations."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "For one believeth that he may eat all things: another, who is weak, eateth herbs."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "Let not him that eateth despise him that eateth not; and let not him which eateth not judge him that eateth: for God hath received him."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "Who art thou that judgest another man’s servant? to his own master he standeth or falleth. Yea, he shall be holden up: for God is able to make him stand."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "One man esteemeth one day above another: another esteemeth every day\nalike. Let every man be fully persuaded in his own mind."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "He that regardeth the day, regardeth\nit unto the Lord; and he that regardeth not the day, to the Lord he doth not regard\nit.\n He that eateth, eateth to the Lord, for he giveth God thanks; and he that eateth not, to the Lord he eateth not, and giveth God thanks."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "For none of us liveth to himself, and no man dieth to himself."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "For whether we live, we live unto the Lord; and whether we die, we die unto the Lord: whether we live therefore, or die, we are the Lord’s."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "For to this end Christ both died, and rose, and revived, that he might be Lord both of the dead and living."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "But why dost thou judge thy brother? or why dost thou set at nought thy brother? for we shall all stand before the judgment seat of Christ."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "For it is written,\nAs I live, saith the Lord, every knee shall bow to me, and every tongue shall confess to God."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "So then every one of us shall give account of himself to God."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "Let us not therefore judge one another any more: but judge this rather, that no man put a stumblingblock or an occasion to fall in\nhis\n brother’s way."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "I know, and am persuaded by the Lord Jesus, that\nthere is\n nothing unclean of itself: but to him that esteemeth any thing to be unclean, to him\nit is unclean."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "But if thy brother be grieved with\nthy meat, now walkest thou not charitably. Destroy not him with thy meat, for whom Christ died."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "Let not then your good be evil spoken of:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "For the kingdom of God is not meat and drink; but righteousness, and peace, and joy in the Holy Ghost."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "For he that in these things serveth Christ\nis acceptable to God, and approved of men."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "Let us therefore follow after the things which make for peace, and things wherewith one may edify another."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "For meat destroy not the work of God. All things indeed\nare\n pure; but\nit is evil for that man who eateth with offence."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "It is good neither to eat flesh, nor to drink wine, nor\nany thing whereby thy brother stumbleth, or is offended, or is made weak."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "Hast thou faith? have\nit to thyself before God. Happy\nis he that condemneth not himself in that thing which he alloweth."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "And he that doubteth is damned if he eat, because\nhe eateth\n not of faith: for whatsoever\nis not of faith is sin."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "We then that are strong ought to bear the infirmities of the weak, and not to please ourselves."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "Let every one of us please\nhis neighbour for\nhis\n good to edification."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "For even Christ pleased not himself; but, as it is written, The reproaches of them that reproached thee fell on me."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "For whatsoever things were written aforetime were written for our learning, that we through patience and comfort of the scriptures might have hope."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "Now the God of patience and consolation grant you to be likeminded one toward another according to Christ Jesus:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "That ye may with one mind\nand one mouth glorify God, even the Father of our Lord Jesus Christ."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "Wherefore receive ye one another, as Christ also received us to the glory of God."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "Now I say that Jesus Christ was a minister of the circumcision for the truth of God, to confirm the promises\nmade unto the fathers:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "And that the Gentiles might glorify God for\nhis mercy; as it is written, For this cause I will confess to thee among the Gentiles, and sing unto thy name."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "And again he saith, Rejoice, ye Gentiles, with his people."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "And again, Praise the Lord, all ye Gentiles; and laud him, all ye people."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "And again, Esaias saith, There shall be a root of Jesse, and he that shall rise to reign over the Gentiles; in him shall the Gentiles trust."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "Now the God of hope fill you with all joy and peace in believing, that ye may abound in hope, through the power of the Holy Ghost."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "And I myself also am persuaded of you, my brethren, that ye also are full of goodness, filled with all knowledge, able also to admonish one another."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "Nevertheless, brethren, I have written the more boldly unto you in some sort, as putting you in mind, because of the grace that is given to me of God,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "That I should be the minister of Jesus Christ to the Gentiles, ministering the gospel of God, that the offering up of the Gentiles might be acceptable, being sanctified by the Holy Ghost."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "I have therefore whereof I may glory through Jesus Christ in those things which pertain to God."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "For I will not dare to speak of any of those things which Christ hath not wrought by me, to make the Gentiles obedient, by word and deed,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "Through mighty signs and wonders, by the power of the Spirit of God; so that from Jerusalem, and round about unto Illyricum, I have fully preached the gospel of Christ."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "Yea, so have I strived to preach the gospel, not where Christ was named, lest I should build upon another man’s foundation:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "But as it is written, To whom he was not spoken of, they shall see: and they that have not heard shall understand."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "For which cause also I have been much hindered from coming to you."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "But now having no more place in these parts, and having a great desire these many years to come unto you;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "Whensoever I take my journey into Spain, I will come to you: for I trust to see you in my journey, and to be brought on my way thitherward by you, if first I be somewhat filled with your\ncompany."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 25,
    "text": "But now I go unto Jerusalem to minister unto the saints."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 26,
    "text": "For it hath pleased them of Macedonia and Achaia to make a certain contribution for the poor saints which are at Jerusalem."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 27,
    "text": "It hath pleased them verily; and their debtors they are. For if the Gentiles have been made partakers of their spiritual things, their duty is also to minister unto them in carnal things."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 28,
    "text": "When therefore I have performed this, and have sealed to them this fruit, I will come by you into Spain."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 29,
    "text": "And I am sure that, when I come unto you, I shall come in the fulness of the blessing of the gospel of Christ."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 30,
    "text": "Now I beseech you, brethren, for the Lord Jesus Christ’s sake, and for the love of the Spirit, that ye strive together with me in\nyour\n prayers to God for me;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 31,
    "text": "That I may be delivered from them that do not believe in Judaea; and that my service which\nI have for Jerusalem may be accepted of the saints;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 32,
    "text": "That I may come unto you with joy by the will of God, and may with you be refreshed."
  },
  {
    "book": "Romans",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 33,
    "text": "Now the God of peace\nbe with you all. Amen."
  },
  {
    "book": "2 Corinthians",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "It is not expedient for me doubtless to glory. I will come to visions and revelations of the Lord."
  },
  {
    "book": "2 Corinthians",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "I knew a man in Christ above fourteen years ago, (whether in the body, I cannot tell; or whether out of the body, I cannot tell: God knoweth;) such an one caught up to the third heaven."
  },
  {
    "book": "2 Corinthians",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "And I knew such a man, (whether in the body, or out of the body, I cannot tell: God knoweth;)"
  },
  {
    "book": "2 Corinthians",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "How that he was caught up into paradise, and heard unspeakable words, which it is not lawful for a man to utter."
  },
  {
    "book": "2 Corinthians",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "Of such an one will I glory: yet of myself I will not glory, but in mine infirmities."
  },
  {
    "book": "2 Corinthians",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "For though I would desire to glory, I shall not be a fool; for I will say the truth: but\nnow I forbear, lest any man should think of me above that which he seeth me\nto be, or\nthat he heareth of me."
  },
  {
    "book": "2 Corinthians",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "And lest I should be exalted above measure through the abundance of the revelations, there was given to me a thorn in the flesh, the messenger of Satan to buffet me, lest I should be exalted above measure."
  },
  {
    "book": "2 Corinthians",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "For this thing I besought the Lord thrice, that it might depart from me."
  },
  {
    "book": "2 Corinthians",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "And he said unto me,\nMy grace is sufficient for thee: for my strength is made perfect in weakness. Most gladly therefore will I rather glory in my infirmities, that the power of Christ may rest upon me."
  },
  {
    "book": "2 Corinthians",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "Therefore I take pleasure in infirmities, in reproaches, in necessities, in persecutions, in distresses for Christ’s sake: for when I am weak, then am I strong."
  },
  {
    "book": "2 Corinthians",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "I am become a fool in glorying; ye have compelled me: for I ought to have been commended of you: for in nothing am I behind the very chiefest apostles, though I be nothing."
  },
  {
    "book": "2 Corinthians",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "Truly the signs of an apostle were wrought among you in all patience, in signs, and wonders, and mighty deeds."
  },
  {
    "book": "2 Corinthians",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "For what is it wherein ye were inferior to other churches, except\nit be that I myself was not burdensome to you? forgive me this wrong."
  },
  {
    "book": "2 Corinthians",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "Behold, the third time I am ready to come to you; and I will not be burdensome to you: for I seek not yours, but you: for the children ought not to lay up for the parents, but the parents for the children."
  },
  {
    "book": "2 Corinthians",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "And I will very gladly spend and be spent for you; though the more abundantly I love you, the less I be loved."
  },
  {
    "book": "2 Corinthians",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "But be it so, I did not burden you: nevertheless, being crafty, I caught you with guile."
  },
  {
    "book": "2 Corinthians",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "Did I make a gain of you by any of them whom I sent unto you?"
  },
  {
    "book": "2 Corinthians",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "I desired Titus, and with\nhim I sent a brother. Did Titus make a gain of you? walked we not in the same spirit?\nwalked we not in the same steps?"
  },
  {
    "book": "2 Corinthians",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "Again, think ye that we excuse ourselves unto you? we speak before God in Christ: but\nwe do all things, dearly beloved, for your edifying."
  },
  {
    "book": "2 Corinthians",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "For I fear, lest, when I come, I shall not find you such as I would, and\nthat I shall be found unto you such as ye would not: lest\nthere be debates, envyings, wraths, strifes, backbitings, whisperings, swellings, tumults:"
  },
  {
    "book": "2 Corinthians",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "And lest, when I come again, my God will humble me among you, and\nthat I shall bewail many which have sinned already, and have not repented of the uncleanness and fornication and lasciviousness which they have committed."
  },
  {
    "book": "2 Corinthians",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "This\nis the third\ntime I am coming to you. In the mouth of two or three witnesses shall every word be established."
  },
  {
    "book": "2 Corinthians",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "I told you before, and foretell you, as if I were present, the second time; and being absent now I write to them which heretofore have sinned, and to all other, that, if I come again, I will not spare:"
  },
  {
    "book": "2 Corinthians",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "Since ye seek a proof of Christ speaking in me, which to you-ward is not weak, but is mighty in you."
  },
  {
    "book": "2 Corinthians",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "For though he was crucified through weakness, yet he liveth by the power of God. For we also are weak in him, but we shall live with him by the power of God toward you."
  },
  {
    "book": "2 Corinthians",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "Examine yourselves, whether ye be in the faith; prove your own selves. Know ye not your own selves, how that Jesus Christ is in you, except ye be reprobates?"
  },
  {
    "book": "2 Corinthians",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "But I trust that ye shall know that we are not reprobates."
  },
  {
    "book": "2 Corinthians",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "Now I pray to God that ye do no evil; not that we should appear approved, but that ye should do that which is honest, though we be as reprobates."
  },
  {
    "book": "2 Corinthians",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "For we can do nothing against the truth, but for the truth."
  },
  {
    "book": "2 Corinthians",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "For we are glad, when we are weak, and ye are strong: and this also we wish,\neven your perfection."
  },
  {
    "book": "2 Corinthians",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "Therefore I write these things being absent, lest being present I should use sharpness, according to the power which the Lord hath given me to edification, and not to destruction."
  },
  {
    "book": "2 Corinthians",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "Finally, brethren, farewell. Be perfect, be of good comfort, be of one mind, live in peace; and the God of love and peace shall be with you."
  },
  {
    "book": "2 Corinthians",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "Greet one another with an holy kiss."
  },
  {
    "book": "2 Corinthians",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "All the saints salute you."
  },
  {
    "book": "2 Corinthians",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "The grace of the Lord Jesus Christ, and the love of God, and the communion of the Holy Ghost,\nbe with you all. Amen."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "Paul, an apostle, (not of men, neither by man, but by Jesus Christ, and God the Father, who raised him from the dead;)"
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "And all the brethren which are with me, unto the churches of Galatia:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "Grace\nbe to you and peace from God the Father, and\nfrom\n our Lord Jesus Christ,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "Who gave himself for our sins, that he might deliver us from this present evil world, according to the will of God and our Father:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "To whom\nbe glory for ever and ever. Amen."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "I marvel that ye are so soon removed from him that called you into the grace of Christ unto another gospel:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "Which is not another; but there be some that trouble you, and would pervert the gospel of Christ."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "But though we, or an angel from heaven, preach any other gospel unto you than that which we have preached unto you, let him be accursed."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "As we said before, so say I now again, If any\nman preach any other gospel unto you than that ye have received, let him be accursed."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "For do I now persuade men, or God? or do I seek to please men? for if I yet pleased men, I should not be the servant of Christ."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "But I certify you, brethren, that the gospel which was preached of me is not after man."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "For I neither received it of man, neither was I taught\nit,\n but by the revelation of Jesus Christ."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "For ye have heard of my conversation in time past in the Jews’ religion, how that beyond measure I persecuted the church of God, and wasted it:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "And profited in the Jews’ religion above many my equals in mine own nation, being more exceedingly zealous of the traditions of my fathers."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "But when it pleased God, who separated me from my mother’s womb, and called\nme by his grace,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "To reveal his Son in me, that I might preach him among the heathen; immediately I conferred not with flesh and blood:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "Neither went I up to Jerusalem to them which were apostles before me; but I went into Arabia, and returned again unto Damascus."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "Then after three years I went up to Jerusalem to see Peter, and abode with him fifteen days."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "But other of the apostles saw I none, save James the Lord’s brother."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "Now the things which I write unto you, behold, before God, I lie not."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "Afterwards I came into the regions of Syria and Cilicia;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "And was unknown by face unto the churches of Judaea which were in Christ:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "But they had heard only, That he which persecuted us in times past now preacheth the faith which once he destroyed."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "And they glorified God in me."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "Then fourteen years after I went up again to Jerusalem with Barnabas, and took Titus with\nme also."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "And I went up by revelation, and communicated unto them that gospel which I preach among the Gentiles, but privately to them which were of reputation, lest by any means I should run, or had run, in vain."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "But neither Titus, who was with me, being a Greek, was compelled to be circumcised:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "And that because of false brethren unawares brought in, who came in privily to spy out our liberty which we have in Christ Jesus, that they might bring us into bondage:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "To whom we gave place by subjection, no, not for an hour; that the truth of the gospel might continue with you."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "But of these who seemed to be somewhat, (whatsoever they were, it maketh no matter to me: God accepteth no man’s person:) for they who seemed\nto be somewhat in conference added nothing to me:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "But contrariwise, when they saw that the gospel of the uncircumcision was committed unto me, as\nthe gospel of the circumcision\nwas\n unto Peter;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "(For he that wrought effectually in Peter to the apostleship of the circumcision, the same was mighty in me toward the Gentiles:)"
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "And when James, Cephas, and John, who seemed to be pillars, perceived the grace that was given unto me, they gave to me and Barnabas the right hands of fellowship; that we\nshould go unto the heathen, and they unto the circumcision."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "Only\nthey would that we should remember the poor; the same which I also was forward to do."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "But when Peter was come to Antioch, I withstood him to the face, because he was to be blamed."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "For before that certain came from James, he did eat with the Gentiles: but when they were come, he withdrew and separated himself, fearing them which were of the circumcision."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "And the other Jews dissembled likewise with him; insomuch that Barnabas also was carried away with their dissimulation."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "But when I saw that they walked not uprightly according to the truth of the gospel, I said unto Peter before\nthem all, If thou, being a Jew, livest after the manner of Gentiles, and not as do the Jews, why compellest thou the Gentiles to live as do the Jews?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "We\nwho are Jews by nature, and not sinners of the Gentiles,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "Knowing that a man is not justified by the works of the law, but by the faith of Jesus Christ, even we have believed in Jesus Christ, that we might be justified by the faith of Christ, and not by the works of the law: for by the works of the law shall no flesh be justified."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "But if, while we seek to be justified by Christ, we ourselves also are found sinners,\nis therefore Christ the minister of sin? God forbid."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "For if I build again the things which I destroyed, I make myself a transgressor."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "For I through the law am dead to the law, that I might live unto God."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "I am crucified with Christ: nevertheless I live; yet not I, but Christ liveth in me: and the life which I now live in the flesh I live by the faith of the Son of God, who loved me, and gave himself for me."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "I do not frustrate the grace of God: for if righteousness\ncome\n by the law, then Christ is dead in vain."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "O foolish Galatians, who hath bewitched you, that ye should not obey the truth, before whose eyes Jesus Christ hath been evidently set forth, crucified among you?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "This only would I learn of you, Received ye the Spirit by the works of the law, or by the hearing of faith?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "Are ye so foolish? having begun in the Spirit, are ye now made perfect by the flesh?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "Have ye suffered so many things in vain? if\nit be yet in vain."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "He therefore that ministereth to you the Spirit, and worketh miracles among you,\ndoeth he it by the works of the law, or by the hearing of faith?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "Even as Abraham believed God, and it was accounted to him for righteousness."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "Know ye therefore that they which are of faith, the same are the children of Abraham."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "And the scripture, foreseeing that God would justify the heathen through faith, preached before the gospel unto Abraham,\nsaying, In thee shall all nations be blessed."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "So then they which be of faith are blessed with faithful Abraham."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "For as many as are of the works of the law are under the curse: for it is written, Cursed\nis every one that continueth not in all things which are written in the book of the law to do them."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "But that no man is justified by the law in the sight of God,\nit is\n evident: for, The just shall live by faith."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "And the law is not of faith: but, The man that doeth them shall live in them."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "Christ hath redeemed us from the curse of the law, being made a curse for us: for it is written, Cursed\nis every one that hangeth on a tree:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "That the blessing of Abraham might come on the Gentiles through Jesus Christ; that we might receive the promise of the Spirit through faith."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "Brethren, I speak after the manner of men; Though\nit be but a man’s covenant, yet\nif it be confirmed, no man disannulleth, or addeth thereto."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "Now to Abraham and his seed were the promises made. He saith not, And to seeds, as of many; but as of one, And to thy seed, which is Christ."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "And this I say,\nthat the covenant, that was confirmed before of God in Christ, the law, which was four hundred and thirty years after, cannot disannul, that it should make the promise of none effect."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "For if the inheritance\nbe of the law,\nit is no more of promise: but God gave\nit to Abraham by promise."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "Wherefore then\nserveth the law? It was added because of transgressions, till the seed should come to whom the promise was made;\nand it was ordained by angels in the hand of a mediator."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "Now a mediator is not\na mediator of one, but God is one."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "Is the law then against the promises of God? God forbid: for if there had been a law given which could have given life, verily righteousness should have been by the law."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "But the scripture hath concluded all under sin, that the promise by faith of Jesus Christ might be given to them that believe."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "But before faith came, we were kept under the law, shut up unto the faith which should afterwards be revealed."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "Wherefore the law was our schoolmaster\nto bring us unto Christ, that we might be justified by faith."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 25,
    "text": "But after that faith is come, we are no longer under a schoolmaster."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 26,
    "text": "For ye are all the children of God by faith in Christ Jesus."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 27,
    "text": "For as many of you as have been baptized into Christ have put on Christ."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 28,
    "text": "There is neither Jew nor Greek, there is neither bond nor free, there is neither male nor female: for ye are all one in Christ Jesus."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 29,
    "text": "And if ye\nbe Christ’s, then are ye Abraham’s seed, and heirs according to the promise."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "Now I say,\nThat the heir, as long as he is a child, differeth nothing from a servant, though he be lord of all;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "But is under tutors and governors until the time appointed of the father."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "Even so we, when we were children, were in bondage under the elements of the world:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "But when the fulness of the time was come, God sent forth his Son, made of a woman, made under the law,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "To redeem them that were under the law, that we might receive the adoption of sons."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "And because ye are sons, God hath sent forth the Spirit of his Son into your hearts, crying, Abba, Father."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "Wherefore thou art no more a servant, but a son; and if a son, then an heir of God through Christ."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "Howbeit then, when ye knew not God, ye did service unto them which by nature are no gods."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "But now, after that ye have known God, or rather are known of God, how turn ye again to the weak and beggarly elements, whereunto ye desire again to be in bondage?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "Ye observe days, and months, and times, and years."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "I am afraid of you, lest I have bestowed upon you labour in vain."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "Brethren, I beseech you, be as I\nam; for I\nam as ye\nare: ye have not injured me at all."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "Ye know how through infirmity of the flesh I preached the gospel unto you at the first."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "And my temptation which was in my flesh ye despised not, nor rejected; but received me as an angel of God,\neven as Christ Jesus."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "Where is then the blessedness ye spake of? for I bear you record, that, if\nit had been possible, ye would have plucked out your own eyes, and have given them to me."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "Am I therefore become your enemy, because I tell you the truth?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "They zealously affect you,\nbut not well; yea, they would exclude you, that ye might affect them."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "But\nit is good to be zealously affected always in\na\n good\nthing, and not only when I am present with you."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "My little children, of whom I travail in birth again until Christ be formed in you,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "I desire to be present with you now, and to change my voice; for I stand in doubt of you."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "Tell me, ye that desire to be under the law, do ye not hear the law?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "For it is written, that Abraham had two sons, the one by a bondmaid, the other by a freewoman."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "But he\nwho was of the bondwoman was born after the flesh; but he of the freewoman\nwas by promise."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "Which things are an allegory: for these are the two covenants; the one from the mount Sinai, which gendereth to bondage, which is Agar."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 25,
    "text": "For this Agar is mount Sinai in Arabia, and answereth to Jerusalem which now is, and is in bondage with her children."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 26,
    "text": "But Jerusalem which is above is free, which is the mother of us all."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 27,
    "text": "For it is written, Rejoice,\nthou barren that bearest not; break forth and cry, thou that travailest not: for the desolate hath many more children than she which hath an husband."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 28,
    "text": "Now we, brethren, as Isaac was, are the children of promise."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 29,
    "text": "But as then he that was born after the flesh persecuted him\nthat was born after the Spirit, even so\nit is now."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 30,
    "text": "Nevertheless what saith the scripture? Cast out the bondwoman and her son: for the son of the bondwoman shall not be heir with the son of the free woman."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 31,
    "text": "So then, brethren, we are not children of the bondwoman, but of the free."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "Stand fast therefore in the liberty wherewith Christ hath made us free, and be not entangled again with the yoke of bondage."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "Behold, I Paul say unto you, that if ye be circumcised, Christ shall profit you nothing."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "For I testify again to every man that is circumcised, that he is a debtor to do the whole law."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "Christ is become of no effect unto you, whosoever of you are justified by the law; ye are fallen from grace."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "For we through the Spirit wait for the hope of righteousness by faith."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "For in Jesus Christ neither circumcision availeth any thing, nor uncircumcision; but faith which worketh by love."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "Ye did run well; who did hinder you that ye should not obey the truth?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "This persuasion\ncometh not of him that calleth you."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "A little leaven leaveneth the whole lump."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "I have confidence in you through the Lord, that ye will be none otherwise minded: but he that troubleth you shall bear his judgment, whosoever he be."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "And I, brethren, if I yet preach circumcision, why do I yet suffer persecution? then is the offence of the cross ceased."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "I would they were even cut off which trouble you."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "For, brethren, ye have been called unto liberty; only\nuse\n not liberty for an occasion to the flesh, but by love serve one another."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "For all the law is fulfilled in one word,\neven in this; Thou shalt love thy neighbour as thyself."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "But if ye bite and devour one another, take heed that ye be not consumed one of another."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "This I say then, Walk in the Spirit, and ye shall not fulfil the lust of the flesh."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "For the flesh lusteth against the Spirit, and the Spirit against the flesh: and these are contrary the one to the other: so that ye cannot do the things that ye would."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "But if ye be led of the Spirit, ye are not under the law."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "Now the works of the flesh are manifest, which are\nthese;\n Adultery, fornication, uncleanness, lasciviousness,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "Idolatry, witchcraft, hatred, variance, emulations, wrath, strife, seditions, heresies,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "Envyings, murders, drunkenness, revellings, and such like: of the which I tell you before, as I have also told\nyou in time past, that they which do such things shall not inherit the kingdom of God."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "But the fruit of the Spirit is love, joy, peace, longsuffering, gentleness, goodness, faith,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "Meekness, temperance: against such there is no law."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "And they that are Christ’s have crucified the flesh with the affections and lusts."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 25,
    "text": "If we live in the Spirit, let us also walk in the Spirit."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 26,
    "text": "Let us not be desirous of vain glory, provoking one another, envying one another."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "Brethren, if a man be overtaken in a fault, ye which are spiritual, restore such an one in the spirit of meekness; considering thyself, lest thou also be tempted."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "Bear ye one another’s burdens, and so fulfil the law of Christ."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "For if a man think himself to be something, when he is nothing, he deceiveth himself."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "But let every man prove his own work, and then shall he have rejoicing in himself alone, and not in another."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "For every man shall bear his own burden."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "Let him that is taught in the word communicate unto him that teacheth in all good things."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "Be not deceived; God is not mocked: for whatsoever a man soweth, that shall he also reap."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "For he that soweth to his flesh shall of the flesh reap corruption; but he that soweth to the Spirit shall of the Spirit reap life everlasting."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "And let us not be weary in well doing: for in due season we shall reap, if we faint not."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "As we have therefore opportunity, let us do good unto all\nmen,\n especially unto them who are of the household of faith."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "Ye see how large a letter I have written unto you with mine own hand."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "As many as desire to make a fair shew in the flesh, they constrain you to be circumcised; only lest they should suffer persecution for the cross of Christ."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "For neither they themselves who are circumcised keep the law; but desire to have you circumcised, that they may glory in your flesh."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "But God forbid that I should glory, save in the cross of our Lord Jesus Christ, by whom the world is crucified unto me, and I unto the world."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "For in Christ Jesus neither circumcision availeth any thing, nor uncircumcision, but a new creature."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "And as many as walk according to this rule, peace\nbe on them, and mercy, and upon the Israel of God."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "From henceforth let no man trouble me: for I bear in my body the marks of the Lord Jesus."
  },
  {
    "book": "Galatians",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "Brethren, the grace of our Lord Jesus Christ\nbe with your spirit. Amen."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "Paul, an apostle of Jesus Christ by the will of God, to the saints which are at Ephesus, and to the faithful in Christ Jesus:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "Grace\nbe to you, and peace, from God our Father, and\nfrom the Lord Jesus Christ."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "Blessed\nbe the God and Father of our Lord Jesus Christ, who hath blessed us with all spiritual blessings in heavenly\nplaces\n in Christ:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "According as he hath chosen us in him before the foundation of the world, that we should be holy and without blame before him in love:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "Having predestinated us unto the adoption of children by Jesus Christ to himself, according to the good pleasure of his will,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "To the praise of the glory of his grace, wherein he hath made us accepted in the beloved."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "In whom we have redemption through his blood, the forgiveness of sins, according to the riches of his grace;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "Wherein he hath abounded toward us in all wisdom and prudence;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "Having made known unto us the mystery of his will, according to his good pleasure which he hath purposed in himself:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "That in the dispensation of the fulness of times he might gather together in one all things in Christ, both which are in heaven, and which are on earth;\neven in him:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "In whom also we have obtained an inheritance, being predestinated according to the purpose of him who worketh all things after the counsel of his own will:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "That we should be to the praise of his glory, who first trusted in Christ."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "In whom ye also\ntrusted, after that ye heard the word of truth, the gospel of your salvation: in whom also after that ye believed, ye were sealed with that holy Spirit of promise,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "Which is the earnest of our inheritance until the redemption of the purchased possession, unto the praise of his glory."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "Wherefore I also, after I heard of your faith in the Lord Jesus, and love unto all the saints,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "Cease not to give thanks for you, making mention of you in my prayers;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "That the God of our Lord Jesus Christ, the Father of glory, may give unto you the spirit of wisdom and revelation in the knowledge of him:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "The eyes of your understanding being enlightened; that ye may know what is the hope of his calling, and what the riches of the glory of his inheritance in the saints,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "And what\nis the exceeding greatness of his power to us-ward who believe, according to the working of his mighty power,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "Which he wrought in Christ, when he raised him from the dead, and set\nhim at his own right hand in the heavenly\nplaces,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "Far above all principality, and power, and might, and dominion, and every name that is named, not only in this world, but also in that which is to come:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "And hath put all\nthings under his feet, and gave him\nto be the head over all\nthings to the church,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "Which is his body, the fulness of him that filleth all in all."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "And you\nhath he quickened, who were dead in trespasses and sins;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "Wherein in time past ye walked according to the course of this world, according to the prince of the power of the air, the spirit that now worketh in the children of disobedience:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "Among whom also we all had our conversation in times past in the lusts of our flesh, fulfilling the desires of the flesh and of the mind; and were by nature the children of wrath, even as others."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "But God, who is rich in mercy, for his great love wherewith he loved us,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "Even when we were dead in sins, hath quickened us together with Christ, (by grace ye are saved;)"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "And hath raised\nus up together, and made\nus sit together in heavenly\nplaces in Christ Jesus:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "That in the ages to come he might shew the exceeding riches of his grace in\nhis kindness toward us through Christ Jesus."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "For by grace are ye saved through faith; and that not of yourselves:\nit is the gift of God:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "Not of works, lest any man should boast."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "For we are his workmanship, created in Christ Jesus unto good works, which God hath before ordained that we should walk in them."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "Wherefore remember, that ye\nbeing in time past Gentiles in the flesh, who are called Uncircumcision by that which is called the Circumcision in the flesh made by hands;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "That at that time ye were without Christ, being aliens from the commonwealth of Israel, and strangers from the covenants of promise, having no hope, and without God in the world:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "But now in Christ Jesus ye who sometimes were far off are made nigh by the blood of Christ."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "For he is our peace, who hath made both one, and hath broken down the middle wall of partition\nbetween us;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "Having abolished in his flesh the enmity,\neven the law of commandments\ncontained in ordinances; for to make in himself of twain one new man,\nso making peace;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "And that he might reconcile both unto God in one body by the cross, having slain the enmity thereby:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "And came and preached peace to you which were afar off, and to them that were nigh."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "For through him we both have access by one Spirit unto the Father."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "Now therefore ye are no more strangers and foreigners, but fellowcitizens with the saints, and of the household of God;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "And are built upon the foundation of the apostles and prophets, Jesus Christ himself being the chief corner\nstone;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "In whom all the building fitly framed together groweth unto an holy temple in the Lord:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "In whom ye also are builded together for an habitation of God through the Spirit."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "For this cause I Paul, the prisoner of Jesus Christ for you Gentiles,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "If ye have heard of the dispensation of the grace of God which is given me to youward:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "How that by revelation he made known unto me the mystery; (as I wrote afore in few words,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "Whereby, when ye read, ye may understand my knowledge in the mystery of Christ)"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "Which in other ages was not made known unto the sons of men, as it is now revealed unto his holy apostles and prophets by the Spirit;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "That the Gentiles should be fellowheirs, and of the same body, and partakers of his promise in Christ by the gospel:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "Whereof I was made a minister, according to the gift of the grace of God given unto me by the effectual working of his power."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "Unto me, who am less than the least of all saints, is this grace given, that I should preach among the Gentiles the unsearchable riches of Christ;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "And to make all\nmen see what\nis the fellowship of the mystery, which from the beginning of the world hath been hid in God, who created all things by Jesus Christ:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "To the intent that now unto the principalities and powers in heavenly\nplaces might be known by the church the manifold wisdom of God,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "According to the eternal purpose which he purposed in Christ Jesus our Lord:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "In whom we have boldness and access with confidence by the faith of him."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "Wherefore I desire that ye faint not at my tribulations for you, which is your glory."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "For this cause I bow my knees unto the Father of our Lord Jesus Christ,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "Of whom the whole family in heaven and earth is named,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "That he would grant you, according to the riches of his glory, to be strengthened with might by his Spirit in the inner man;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "That Christ may dwell in your hearts by faith; that ye, being rooted and grounded in love,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "May be able to comprehend with all saints what\nis the breadth, and length, and depth, and height;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "And to know the love of Christ, which passeth knowledge, that ye might be filled with all the fulness of God."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "Now unto him that is able to do exceeding abundantly above all that we ask or think, according to the power that worketh in us,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "Unto him\nbe glory in the church by Christ Jesus throughout all ages, world without end. Amen."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "I therefore, the prisoner of the Lord, beseech you that ye walk worthy of the vocation wherewith ye are called,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "With all lowliness and meekness, with longsuffering, forbearing one another in love;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "Endeavouring to keep the unity of the Spirit in the bond of peace."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "There is one body, and one Spirit, even as ye are called in one hope of your calling;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "One Lord, one faith, one baptism,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "One God and Father of all, who\nis above all, and through all, and in you all."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "But unto every one of us is given grace according to the measure of the gift of Christ."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "Wherefore he saith, When he ascended up on high, he led captivity captive, and gave gifts unto men."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "(Now that he ascended, what is it but that he also descended first into the lower parts of the earth?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "He that descended is the same also that ascended up far above all heavens, that he might fill all things.)"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "And he gave some, apostles; and some, prophets; and some, evangelists; and some, pastors and teachers;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "For the perfecting of the saints, for the work of the ministry, for the edifying of the body of Christ:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "Till we all come in the unity of the faith, and of the knowledge of the Son of God, unto a perfect man, unto the measure of the stature of the fulness of Christ:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "That we\nhenceforth be no more children, tossed to and fro, and carried about with every wind of doctrine, by the sleight of men,\nand\n cunning craftiness, whereby they lie in wait to deceive;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "But speaking the truth in love, may grow up into him in all things, which is the head,\neven Christ:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "From whom the whole body fitly joined together and compacted by that which every joint supplieth, according to the effectual working in the measure of every part, maketh increase of the body unto the edifying of itself in love."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "This I say therefore, and testify in the Lord, that ye henceforth walk not as other Gentiles walk, in the vanity of their mind,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "Having the understanding darkened, being alienated from the life of God through the ignorance that is in them, because of the blindness of their heart:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "Who being past feeling have given themselves over unto lasciviousness, to work all uncleanness with greediness."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "But ye have not so learned Christ;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "If so be that ye have heard him, and have been taught by him, as the truth is in Jesus:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "That ye put off concerning the former conversation the old man, which is corrupt according to the deceitful lusts;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "And be renewed in the spirit of your mind;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "And that ye put on the new man, which after God is created in righteousness and true holiness."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 25,
    "text": "Wherefore putting away lying, speak every man truth with his neighbour: for we are members one of another."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 26,
    "text": "Be ye angry, and sin not: let not the sun go down upon your wrath:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 27,
    "text": "Neither give place to the devil."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 28,
    "text": "Let him that stole steal no more: but rather let him labour, working with\nhis hands the thing which is good, that he may have to give to him that needeth."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 29,
    "text": "Let no corrupt communication proceed out of your mouth, but that which is good to the use of edifying, that it may minister grace unto the hearers."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 30,
    "text": "And grieve not the holy Spirit of God, whereby ye are sealed unto the day of redemption."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 31,
    "text": "Let all bitterness, and wrath, and anger, and clamour, and evil speaking, be put away from you, with all malice:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 32,
    "text": "And be ye kind one to another, tenderhearted, forgiving one another, even as God for Christ’s sake hath forgiven you."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "Be ye therefore followers of God, as dear children;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "And walk in love, as Christ also hath loved us, and hath given himself for us an offering and a sacrifice to God for a sweetsmelling savour."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "But fornication, and all uncleanness, or covetousness, let it not be once named among you, as becometh saints;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "Neither filthiness, nor foolish talking, nor jesting, which are not convenient: but rather giving of thanks."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "For this ye know, that no whoremonger, nor unclean person, nor covetous man, who is an idolater, hath any inheritance in the kingdom of Christ and of God."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "Let no man deceive you with vain words: for because of these things cometh the wrath of God upon the children of disobedience."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "Be not ye therefore partakers with them."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "For ye were sometimes darkness, but now\nare ye light in the Lord: walk as children of light:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "(For the fruit of the Spirit is in all goodness and righteousness and truth;)"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "Proving what is acceptable unto the Lord."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "And have no fellowship with the unfruitful works of darkness, but rather reprove\nthem."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "For it is a shame even to speak of those things which are done of them in secret."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "But all things that are reproved are made manifest by the light: for whatsoever doth make manifest is light."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "Wherefore he saith, Awake thou that sleepest, and arise from the dead, and Christ shall give thee light."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "See then that ye walk circumspectly, not as fools, but as wise,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "Redeeming the time, because the days are evil."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "Wherefore be ye not unwise, but understanding what the will of the Lord\nis."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "And be not drunk with wine, wherein is excess; but be filled with the Spirit;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "Speaking to yourselves in psalms and hymns and spiritual songs, singing and making melody in your heart to the Lord;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "Giving thanks always for all things unto God and the Father in the name of our Lord Jesus Christ;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "Submitting yourselves one to another in the fear of God."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "Wives, submit yourselves unto your own husbands, as unto the Lord."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "For the husband is the head of the wife, even as Christ is the head of the church: and he is the saviour of the body."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "Therefore as the church is subject unto Christ, so\nlet the wives\nbe to their own husbands in every thing."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 25,
    "text": "Husbands, love your wives, even as Christ also loved the church, and gave himself for it;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 26,
    "text": "That he might sanctify and cleanse it with the washing of water by the word,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 27,
    "text": "That he might present it to himself a glorious church, not having spot, or wrinkle, or any such thing; but that it should be holy and without blemish."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 28,
    "text": "So ought men to love their wives as their own bodies. He that loveth his wife loveth himself."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 29,
    "text": "For no man ever yet hated his own flesh; but nourisheth and cherisheth it, even as the Lord the church:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 30,
    "text": "For we are members of his body, of his flesh, and of his bones."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 31,
    "text": "For this cause shall a man leave his father and mother, and shall be joined unto his wife, and they two shall be one flesh."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 32,
    "text": "This is a great mystery: but I speak concerning Christ and the church."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 33,
    "text": "Nevertheless let every one of you in particular so love his wife even as himself; and the wife\nsee that she reverence\nher husband."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "Children, obey your parents in the Lord: for this is right."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "Honour thy father and mother; (which is the first commandment with promise;)"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "That it may be well with thee, and thou mayest live long on the earth."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "And, ye fathers, provoke not your children to wrath: but bring them up in the nurture and admonition of the Lord."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "Servants, be obedient to them that are\nyour masters according to the flesh, with fear and trembling, in singleness of your heart, as unto Christ;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "Not with eyeservice, as menpleasers; but as the servants of Christ, doing the will of God from the heart;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "With good will doing service, as to the Lord, and not to men:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "Knowing that whatsoever good thing any man doeth, the same shall he receive of the Lord, whether\nhe be bond or free."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "And, ye masters, do the same things unto them, forbearing threatening: knowing that your Master also is in heaven; neither is there respect of persons with him."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "Finally, my brethren, be strong in the Lord, and in the power of his might."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "Put on the whole armour of God, that ye may be able to stand against the wiles of the devil."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "For we wrestle not against flesh and blood, but against principalities, against powers, against the rulers of the darkness of this world, against spiritual wickedness in high\nplaces."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "Wherefore take unto you the whole armour of God, that ye may be able to withstand in the evil day, and having done all, to stand."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "Stand therefore, having your loins girt about with truth, and having on the breastplate of righteousness;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "And your feet shod with the preparation of the gospel of peace;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "Above all, taking the shield of faith, wherewith ye shall be able to quench all the fiery darts of the wicked."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "And take the helmet of salvation, and the sword of the Spirit, which is the word of God:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "Praying always with all prayer and supplication in the Spirit, and watching thereunto with all perseverance and supplication for all saints;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "And for me, that utterance may be given unto me, that I may open my mouth boldly, to make known the mystery of the gospel,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "For which I am an ambassador in bonds: that therein I may speak boldly, as I ought to speak."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "But that ye also may know my affairs,\nand how I do, Tychicus, a beloved brother and faithful minister in the Lord, shall make known to you all things:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "Whom I have sent unto you for the same purpose, that ye might know our affairs, and\nthat he might comfort your hearts."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "Peace\nbe to the brethren, and love with faith, from God the Father and the Lord Jesus Christ."
  },
  {
    "book": "Ephesians",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "Grace\nbe with all them that love our Lord Jesus Christ in sincerity. Amen."
  },
  {
    "book": "Philippians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "Paul and Timotheus, the servants of Jesus Christ, to all the saints in Christ Jesus which are at Philippi, with the bishops and deacons:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Philippians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "Grace\nbe unto you, and peace, from God our Father, and\nfrom the Lord Jesus Christ."
  },
  {
    "book": "Philippians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "I thank my God upon every remembrance of you,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Philippians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "Always in every prayer of mine for you all making request with joy,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Philippians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "For your fellowship in the gospel from the first day until now;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Philippians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "Being confident of this very thing, that he which hath begun a good work in you will perform\nit until the day of Jesus Christ:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Philippians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "Even as it is meet for me to think this of you all, because I have you in my heart; inasmuch as both in my bonds, and in the defence and confirmation of the gospel, ye all are partakers of my grace."
  },
  {
    "book": "Philippians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "For God is my record, how greatly I long after you all in the bowels of Jesus Christ."
  },
  {
    "book": "Philippians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "And this I pray, that your love may abound yet more and more in knowledge and\nin all judgment;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Philippians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "That ye may approve things that are excellent; that ye may be sincere and without offence till the day of Christ;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Philippians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "Being filled with the fruits of righteousness, which are by Jesus Christ, unto the glory and praise of God."
  },
  {
    "book": "Philippians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "But I would ye should understand, brethren, that the things\nwhich happened unto me have fallen out rather unto the furtherance of the gospel;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Philippians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "So that my bonds in Christ are manifest in all the palace, and in all other\nplaces;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Philippians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "And many of the brethren in the Lord, waxing confident by my bonds, are much more bold to speak the word without fear."
  },
  {
    "book": "Philippians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "Some indeed preach Christ even of envy and strife; and some also of good will:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Philippians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "The one preach Christ of contention, not sincerely, supposing to add affliction to my bonds:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Philippians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "But the other of love, knowing that I am set for the defence of the gospel."
  },
  {
    "book": "Philippians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "What then? notwithstanding, every way, whether in pretence, or in truth, Christ is preached; and I therein do rejoice, yea, and will rejoice."
  },
  {
    "book": "Philippians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "For I know that this shall turn to my salvation through your prayer, and the supply of the Spirit of Jesus Christ,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Philippians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "According to my earnest expectation and\nmy hope, that in nothing I shall be ashamed, but\nthat with all boldness, as always,\nso now also Christ shall be magnified in my body, whether\nit be by life, or by death."
  },
  {
    "book": "Philippians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "For to me to live\nis Christ, and to die\nis gain."
  },
  {
    "book": "Philippians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "But if I live in the flesh, this\nis the fruit of my labour: yet what I shall choose I wot not."
  },
  {
    "book": "Philippians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "For I am in a strait betwixt two, having a desire to depart, and to be with Christ; which is far better:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Philippians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "Nevertheless to abide in the flesh\nis more needful for you."
  },
  {
    "book": "Philippians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 25,
    "text": "And having this confidence, I know that I shall abide and continue with you all for your furtherance and joy of faith;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Philippians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 26,
    "text": "That your rejoicing may be more abundant in Jesus Christ for me by my coming to you again."
  },
  {
    "book": "Philippians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 27,
    "text": "Only let your conversation be as it becometh the gospel of Christ: that whether I come and see you, or else be absent, I may hear of your affairs, that ye stand fast in one spirit, with one mind striving together for the faith of the gospel;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Philippians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 28,
    "text": "And in nothing terrified by your adversaries: which is to them an evident token of perdition, but to you of salvation, and that of God."
  },
  {
    "book": "Philippians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 29,
    "text": "For unto you it is given in the behalf of Christ, not only to believe on him, but also to suffer for his sake;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Philippians",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 30,
    "text": "Having the same conflict which ye saw in me, and now hear\nto be\n in me."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "For every high priest taken from among men is ordained for men in things\npertaining to God, that he may offer both gifts and sacrifices for sins:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "Who can have compassion on the ignorant, and on them that are out of the way; for that he himself also is compassed with infirmity."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "And by reason hereof he ought, as for the people, so also for himself, to offer for sins."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "And no man taketh this honour unto himself, but he that is called of God, as\nwas Aaron."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "So also Christ glorified not himself to be made an high priest; but he that said unto him, Thou art my Son, to day have I begotten thee."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "As he saith also in another\nplace, Thou\nart a priest for ever after the order of Melchisedec."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "Who in the days of his flesh, when he had offered up prayers and supplications with strong crying and tears unto him that was able to save him from death, and was heard in that he feared;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "Though he were a Son, yet learned he obedience by the things which he suffered;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "And being made perfect, he became the author of eternal salvation unto all them that obey him;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "Called of God an high priest after the order of Melchisedec."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "Of whom we have many things to say, and hard to be uttered, seeing ye are dull of hearing."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "For when for the time ye ought to be teachers, ye have need that one teach you again which\nbe the first principles of the oracles of God; and are become such as have need of milk, and not of strong meat."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "For every one that useth milk\nis unskilful in the word of righteousness: for he is a babe."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "But strong meat belongeth to them that are of full age,\neven\n those who by reason of use have their senses exercised to discern both good and evil."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "Therefore leaving the principles of the doctrine of Christ, let us go on unto perfection; not laying again the foundation of repentance from dead works, and of faith toward God,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "Of the doctrine of baptisms, and of laying on of hands, and of resurrection of the dead, and of eternal judgment."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "And this will we do, if God permit."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "For\nit is impossible for those who were once enlightened, and have tasted of the heavenly gift, and were made partakers of the Holy Ghost,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "And have tasted the good word of God, and the powers of the world to come,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "If they shall fall away, to renew them again unto repentance; seeing they crucify to themselves the Son of God afresh, and put\nhim to an open shame."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "For the earth which drinketh in the rain that cometh oft upon it, and bringeth forth herbs meet for them by whom it is dressed, receiveth blessing from God:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "But that which beareth thorns and briers\nis rejected, and\nis nigh unto cursing; whose end\nis to be burned."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "But, beloved, we are persuaded better things of you, and things that accompany salvation, though we thus speak."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "For God\nis not unrighteous to forget your work and labour of love, which ye have shewed toward his name, in that ye have ministered to the saints, and do minister."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "And we desire that every one of you do shew the same diligence to the full assurance of hope unto the end:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "That ye be not slothful, but followers of them who through faith and patience inherit the promises."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "For when God made promise to Abraham, because he could swear by no greater, he sware by himself,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "Saying, Surely blessing I will bless thee, and multiplying I will multiply thee."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "And so, after he had patiently endured, he obtained the promise."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "For men verily swear by the greater: and an oath for confirmation\nis to them an end of all strife."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "Wherein God, willing more abundantly to shew unto the heirs of promise the immutability of his counsel, confirmed\nit by an oath:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "That by two immutable things, in which\nit was impossible for God to lie, we might have a strong consolation, who have fled for refuge to lay hold upon the hope set before us:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "Which\nhope we have as an anchor of the soul, both sure and stedfast, and which entereth into that within the veil;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "Whither the forerunner is for us entered,\neven Jesus, made an high priest for ever after the order of Melchisedec."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "For this Melchisedec, king of Salem, priest of the most high God, who met Abraham returning from the slaughter of the kings, and blessed him;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "To whom also Abraham gave a tenth part of all; first being by interpretation King of righteousness, and after that also King of Salem, which is, King of peace;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "Without father, without mother, without descent, having neither beginning of days, nor end of life; but made like unto the Son of God; abideth a priest continually."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "Now consider how great this man\nwas, unto whom even the patriarch Abraham gave the tenth of the spoils."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "And verily they that are of the sons of Levi, who receive the office of the priesthood, have a commandment to take tithes of the people according to the law, that is, of their brethren, though they come out of the loins of Abraham:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "But he whose descent is not counted from them received tithes of Abraham, and blessed him that had the promises."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "And without all contradiction the less is blessed of the better."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "And here men that die receive tithes; but there he\nreceiveth them,\n of whom it is witnessed that he liveth."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "And as I may so say, Levi also, who receiveth tithes, payed tithes in Abraham."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "For he was yet in the loins of his father, when Melchisedec met him."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "If therefore perfection were by the Levitical priesthood, (for under it the people received the law,) what further need\nwas there that another priest should rise after the order of Melchisedec, and not be called after the order of Aaron?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "For the priesthood being changed, there is made of necessity a change also of the law."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "For he of whom these things are spoken pertaineth to another tribe, of which no man gave attendance at the altar."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "For\nit is evident that our Lord sprang out of Juda; of which tribe Moses spake nothing concerning priesthood."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "And it is yet far more evident: for that after the similitude of Melchisedec there ariseth another priest,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "Who is made, not after the law of a carnal commandment, but after the power of an endless life."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "For he testifieth, Thou\nart a priest for ever after the order of Melchisedec."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "For there is verily a disannulling of the commandment going before for the weakness and unprofitableness thereof."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "For the law made nothing perfect, but the bringing in of a better hope\ndid; by the which we draw nigh unto God."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "And inasmuch as not without an oath\nhe was made priest:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "(For those priests were made without an oath; but this with an oath by him that said unto him, The Lord sware and will not repent, Thou\nart\n a priest for ever after the order of Melchisedec:)"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "By so much was Jesus made a surety of a better testament."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "And they truly were many priests, because they were not suffered to continue by reason of death:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "But this\nman, because he continueth ever, hath an unchangeable priesthood."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 25,
    "text": "Wherefore he is able also to save them to the uttermost that come unto God by him, seeing he ever liveth to make intercession for them."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 26,
    "text": "For such an high priest became us,\nwho is holy, harmless, undefiled, separate from sinners, and made higher than the heavens;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 27,
    "text": "Who needeth not daily, as those high priests, to offer up sacrifice, first for his own sins, and then for the people’s: for this he did once, when he offered up himself."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 28,
    "text": "For the law maketh men high priests which have infirmity; but the word of the oath, which was since the law,\nmaketh the Son, who is consecrated for evermore."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "Now of the things which we have spoken\nthis is the sum: We have such an high priest, who is set on the right hand of the throne of the Majesty in the heavens;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "A minister of the sanctuary, and of the true tabernacle, which the Lord pitched, and not man."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "For every high priest is ordained to offer gifts and sacrifices: wherefore\nit is of necessity that this man have somewhat also to offer."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "For if he were on earth, he should not be a priest, seeing that there are priests that offer gifts according to the law:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "Who serve unto the example and shadow of heavenly things, as Moses was admonished of God when he was about to make the tabernacle: for, See, saith he,\nthat thou make all things according to the pattern shewed to thee in the mount."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "But now hath he obtained a more excellent ministry, by how much also he is the mediator of a better covenant, which was established upon better promises."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "For if that first\ncovenant had been faultless, then should no place have been sought for the second."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "For finding fault with them, he saith, Behold, the days come, saith the Lord, when I will make a new covenant with the house of Israel and with the house of Judah:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "Not according to the covenant that I made with their fathers in the day when I took them by the hand to lead them out of the land of Egypt; because they continued not in my covenant, and I regarded them not, saith the Lord."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "For this\nis the covenant that I will make with the house of Israel after those days, saith the Lord; I will put my laws into their mind, and write them in their hearts: and I will be to them a God, and they shall be to me a people:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "And they shall not teach every man his neighbour, and every man his brother, saying, Know the Lord: for all shall know me, from the least to the greatest."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "For I will be merciful to their unrighteousness, and their sins and their iniquities will I remember no more."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "In that he saith, A new\ncovenant, he hath made the first old. Now that which decayeth and waxeth old\nis ready to vanish away."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "Then verily the first\ncovenant had also ordinances of divine service, and a worldly sanctuary."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "For there was a tabernacle made; the first, wherein\nwas the candlestick, and the table, and the shewbread; which is called the sanctuary."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "And after the second veil, the tabernacle which is called the Holiest of all;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "Which had the golden censer, and the ark of the covenant overlaid round about with gold, wherein\nwas the golden pot that had manna, and Aaron’s rod that budded, and the tables of the covenant;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "And over it the cherubims of glory shadowing the mercyseat; of which we cannot now speak particularly."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "Now when these things were thus ordained, the priests went always into the first tabernacle, accomplishing the service\nof God."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "But into the second\nwent the high priest alone once every year, not without blood, which he offered for himself, and\nfor the errors of the people:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "The Holy Ghost this signifying, that the way into the holiest of all was not yet made manifest, while as the first tabernacle was yet standing:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "Which\nwas a figure for the time then present, in which were offered both gifts and sacrifices, that could not make him that did the service perfect, as pertaining to the conscience;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "Which stood only in meats and drinks, and divers washings, and carnal ordinances, imposed\non them until the time of reformation."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "But Christ being come an high priest of good things to come, by a greater and more perfect tabernacle, not made with hands, that is to say, not of this building;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "Neither by the blood of goats and calves, but by his own blood he entered in once into the holy place, having obtained eternal redemption\nfor us."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "For if the blood of bulls and of goats, and the ashes of an heifer sprinkling the unclean, sanctifieth to the purifying of the flesh:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "How much more shall the blood of Christ, who through the eternal Spirit offered himself without spot to God, purge your conscience from dead works to serve the living God?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "And for this cause he is the mediator of the new testament, that by means of death, for the redemption of the transgressions\nthat were\n under the first testament, they which are called might receive the promise of eternal inheritance."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "For where a testament\nis, there must also of necessity be the death of the testator."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "For a testament\nis of force after men are dead: otherwise it is of no strength at all while the testator liveth."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "Whereupon neither the first\ntestament was dedicated without blood."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "For when Moses had spoken every precept to all the people according to the law, he took the blood of calves and of goats, with water, and scarlet wool, and hyssop, and sprinkled both the book, and all the people,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "Saying, This\nis the blood of the testament which God hath enjoined unto you."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "Moreover he sprinkled with blood both the tabernacle, and all the vessels of the ministry."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "And almost all things are by the law purged with blood; and without shedding of blood is no remission."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "It was therefore necessary that the patterns of things in the heavens should be purified with these; but the heavenly things themselves with better sacrifices than these."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "For Christ is not entered into the holy places made with hands,\nwhich are the figures of the true; but into heaven itself, now to appear in the presence of God for us:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 25,
    "text": "Nor yet that he should offer himself often, as the high priest entereth into the holy place every year with blood of others;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 26,
    "text": "For then must he often have suffered since the foundation of the world: but now once in the end of the world hath he appeared to put away sin by the sacrifice of himself."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 27,
    "text": "And as it is appointed unto men once to die, but after this the judgment:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 28,
    "text": "So Christ was once offered to bear the sins of many; and unto them that look for him shall he appear the second time without sin unto salvation."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "For the law having a shadow of good things to come,\nand not the very image of the things, can never with those sacrifices which they offered year by year continually make the comers thereunto perfect."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "For then would they not have ceased to be offered? because that the worshippers once purged should have had no more conscience of sins."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "But in those\nsacrifices there is a remembrance again\nmade of sins every year."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "For\nit is not possible that the blood of bulls and of goats should take away sins."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "Wherefore when he cometh into the world, he saith, Sacrifice and offering thou wouldest not, but a body hast thou prepared me:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "In burnt offerings and\nsacrifices for sin thou hast had no pleasure."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "Then said I, Lo, I come (in the volume of the book it is written of me,) to do thy will, O God."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "Above when he said, Sacrifice and offering and burnt offerings and\noffering for sin thou wouldest not, neither hadst pleasure\ntherein; which are offered by the law;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "Then said he, Lo, I come to do thy will, O God. He taketh away the first, that he may establish the second."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "By the which will we are sanctified through the offering of the body of Jesus Christ once\nfor all."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "And every priest standeth daily ministering and offering oftentimes the same sacrifices, which can never take away sins:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "But this man, after he had offered one sacrifice for sins for ever, sat down on the right hand of God;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "From henceforth expecting till his enemies be made his footstool."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "For by one offering he hath perfected for ever them that are sanctified."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "Whereof the Holy Ghost also is a witness to us: for after that he had said before,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "This\nis the covenant that I will make with them after those days, saith the Lord, I will put my laws into their hearts, and in their minds will I write them;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "And their sins and iniquities will I remember no more."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "Now where remission of these\nis, there is no more offering for sin."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "Having therefore, brethren, boldness to enter into the holiest by the blood of Jesus,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "By a new and living way, which he hath consecrated for us, through the veil, that is to say, his flesh;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "And\nhaving an high priest over the house of God;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "Let us draw near with a true heart in full assurance of faith, having our hearts sprinkled from an evil conscience, and our bodies washed with pure water."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "Let us hold fast the profession of\nour faith without wavering; (for he is faithful that promised;)"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "And let us consider one another to provoke unto love and to good works:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 25,
    "text": "Not forsaking the assembling of ourselves together, as the manner of some\nis; but exhorting\none another: and so much the more, as ye see the day approaching."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 26,
    "text": "For if we sin wilfully after that we have received the knowledge of the truth, there remaineth no more sacrifice for sins,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 27,
    "text": "But a certain fearful looking for of judgment and fiery indignation, which shall devour the adversaries."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 28,
    "text": "He that despised Moses’ law died without mercy under two or three witnesses:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 29,
    "text": "Of how much sorer punishment, suppose ye, shall he be thought worthy, who hath trodden under foot the Son of God, and hath counted the blood of the covenant, wherewith he was sanctified, an unholy thing, and hath done despite unto the Spirit of grace?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 30,
    "text": "For we know him that hath said, Vengeance\nbelongeth unto me, I will recompense, saith the Lord. And again, The Lord shall judge his people."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 31,
    "text": "It is a fearful thing to fall into the hands of the living God."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 32,
    "text": "But call to remembrance the former days, in which, after ye were illuminated, ye endured a great fight of afflictions;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 33,
    "text": "Partly, whilst ye were made a gazingstock both by reproaches and afflictions; and partly, whilst ye became companions of them that were so used."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 34,
    "text": "For ye had compassion of me in my bonds, and took joyfully the spoiling of your goods, knowing in yourselves that ye have in heaven a better and an enduring substance."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 35,
    "text": "Cast not away therefore your confidence, which hath great recompence of reward."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 36,
    "text": "For ye have need of patience, that, after ye have done the will of God, ye might receive the promise."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 37,
    "text": "For yet a little while, and he that shall come will come, and will not tarry."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 38,
    "text": "Now the just shall live by faith: but if\nany man draw back, my soul shall have no pleasure in him."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 39,
    "text": "But we are not of them who draw back unto perdition; but of them that believe to the saving of the soul."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "Now faith is the substance of things hoped for, the evidence of things not seen."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "For by it the elders obtained a good report."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "Through faith we understand that the worlds were framed by the word of God, so that things which are seen were not made of things which do appear."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "By faith Abel offered unto God a more excellent sacrifice than Cain, by which he obtained witness that he was righteous, God testifying of his gifts: and by it he being dead yet speaketh."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "By faith Enoch was translated that he should not see death; and was not found, because God had translated him: for before his translation he had this testimony, that he pleased God."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "But without faith\nit is impossible to please\nhim:\n for he that cometh to God must believe that he is, and\nthat\n he is a rewarder of them that diligently seek him."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "By faith Noah, being warned of God of things not seen as yet, moved with fear, prepared an ark to the saving of his house; by the which he condemned the world, and became heir of the righteousness which is by faith."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "By faith Abraham, when he was called to go out into a place which he should after receive for an inheritance, obeyed; and he went out, not knowing whither he went."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "By faith he sojourned in the land of promise, as\nin a strange country, dwelling in tabernacles with Isaac and Jacob, the heirs with him of the same promise:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "For he looked for a city which hath foundations, whose builder and maker\nis God."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "Through faith also Sara herself received strength to conceive seed, and was delivered of a child when she was past age, because she judged him faithful who had promised."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "Therefore sprang there even of one, and him as good as dead,\nso many as the stars of the sky in multitude, and as the sand which is by the sea shore innumerable."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "These all died in faith, not having received the promises, but having seen them afar off, and were persuaded of\nthem, and embraced\nthem, and confessed that they were strangers and pilgrims on the earth."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "For they that say such things declare plainly that they seek a country."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "And truly, if they had been mindful of that\ncountry from whence they came out, they might have had opportunity to have returned."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "But now they desire a better\ncountry, that is, an heavenly: wherefore God is not ashamed to be called their God: for he hath prepared for them a city."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "By faith Abraham, when he was tried, offered up Isaac: and he that had received the promises offered up his only begotten\nson,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "Of whom it was said, That in Isaac shall thy seed be called:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "Accounting that God\nwas able to raise\nhim up, even from the dead; from whence also he received him in a figure."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "By faith Isaac blessed Jacob and Esau concerning things to come."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "By faith Jacob, when he was a dying, blessed both the sons of Joseph; and worshipped,\nleaning upon the top of his staff."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "By faith Joseph, when he died, made mention of the departing of the children of Israel; and gave commandment concerning his bones."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "By faith Moses, when he was born, was hid three months of his parents, because they saw\nhe was a proper child; and they were not afraid of the king’s commandment."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "By faith Moses, when he was come to years, refused to be called the son of Pharaoh’s daughter;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 25,
    "text": "Choosing rather to suffer affliction with the people of God, than to enjoy the pleasures of sin for a season;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 26,
    "text": "Esteeming the reproach of Christ greater riches than the treasures in Egypt: for he had respect unto the recompence of the reward."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 27,
    "text": "By faith he forsook Egypt, not fearing the wrath of the king: for he endured, as seeing him who is invisible."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 28,
    "text": "Through faith he kept the passover, and the sprinkling of blood, lest he that destroyed the firstborn should touch them."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 29,
    "text": "By faith they passed through the Red sea as by dry\nland:\n which the Egyptians assaying to do were drowned."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 30,
    "text": "By faith the walls of Jericho fell down, after they were compassed about seven days."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 31,
    "text": "By faith the harlot Rahab perished not with them that believed not, when she had received the spies with peace."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 32,
    "text": "And what shall I more say? for the time would fail me to tell of Gedeon, and\nof Barak, and\nof Samson, and\nof Jephthae;\nof David also, and Samuel, and\nof the prophets:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 33,
    "text": "Who through faith subdued kingdoms, wrought righteousness, obtained promises, stopped the mouths of lions,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 34,
    "text": "Quenched the violence of fire, escaped the edge of the sword, out of weakness were made strong, waxed valiant in fight, turned to flight the armies of the aliens."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 35,
    "text": "Women received their dead raised to life again: and others were tortured, not accepting deliverance; that they might obtain a better resurrection:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 36,
    "text": "And others had trial of\ncruel mockings and scourgings, yea, moreover of bonds and imprisonment:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 37,
    "text": "They were stoned, they were sawn asunder, were tempted, were slain with the sword: they wandered about in sheepskins and goatskins; being destitute, afflicted, tormented;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 38,
    "text": "(Of whom the world was not worthy:) they wandered in deserts, and\nin mountains, and\nin dens and caves of the earth."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 39,
    "text": "And these all, having obtained a good report through faith, received not the promise:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 40,
    "text": "God having provided some better thing for us, that they without us should not be made perfect."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "Wherefore seeing we also are compassed about with so great a cloud of witnesses, let us lay aside every weight, and the sin which doth so easily beset us, and let us run with patience the race that is set before us,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "Looking unto Jesus the author and finisher of\nour faith; who for the joy that was set before him endured the cross, despising the shame, and is set down at the right hand of the throne of God."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "For consider him that endured such contradiction of sinners against himself, lest ye be wearied and faint in your minds."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "Ye have not yet resisted unto blood, striving against sin."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "And ye have forgotten the exhortation which speaketh unto you as unto children, My son, despise not thou the chastening of the Lord, nor faint when thou art rebuked of him:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "For whom the Lord loveth he chasteneth, and scourgeth every son whom he receiveth."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "If ye endure chastening, God dealeth with you as with sons; for what son is he whom the father chasteneth not?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "But if ye be without chastisement, whereof all are partakers, then are ye bastards, and not sons."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "Furthermore we have had fathers of our flesh which corrected\nus,\n and we gave\nthem reverence: shall we not much rather be in subjection unto the Father of spirits, and live?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "For they verily for a few days chastened\nus after their own pleasure; but he for\nour profit, that\nwe might be partakers of his holiness."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "Now no chastening for the present seemeth to be joyous, but grievous: nevertheless afterward it yieldeth the peaceable fruit of righteousness unto them which are exercised thereby."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "Wherefore lift up the hands which hang down, and the feeble knees;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "And make straight paths for your feet, lest that which is lame be turned out of the way; but let it rather be healed."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "Follow peace with all\nmen, and holiness, without which no man shall see the Lord:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "Looking diligently lest any man fail of the grace of God; lest any root of bitterness springing up trouble\nyou, and thereby many be defiled;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "Lest there\nbe any fornicator, or profane person, as Esau, who for one morsel of meat sold his birthright."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "For ye know how that afterward, when he would have inherited the blessing, he was rejected: for he found no place of repentance, though he sought it carefully with tears."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "For ye are not come unto the mount that might be touched, and that burned with fire, nor unto blackness, and darkness, and tempest,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "And the sound of a trumpet, and the voice of words;\nwhich\n voice they that heard intreated that the word should not be spoken to them any more:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "(For they could not endure that which was commanded, And if so much as a beast touch the mountain, it shall be stoned, or thrust through with a dart:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "And so terrible was the sight,\nthat Moses said, I exceedingly fear and quake:)"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "But ye are come unto mount Sion, and unto the city of the living God, the heavenly Jerusalem, and to an innumerable company of angels,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "To the general assembly and church of the firstborn, which are written in heaven, and to God the Judge of all, and to the spirits of just men made perfect,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "And to Jesus the mediator of the new covenant, and to the blood of sprinkling, that speaketh better things than\nthat of Abel."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 25,
    "text": "See that ye refuse not him that speaketh. For if they escaped not who refused him that spake on earth, much more\nshall not we\nescape,\n if we turn away from him that\nspeaketh from heaven:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 26,
    "text": "Whose voice then shook the earth: but now he hath promised, saying, Yet once more I shake not the earth only, but also heaven."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 27,
    "text": "And this\nword, Yet once more, signifieth the removing of those things that are shaken, as of things that are made, that those things which cannot be shaken may remain."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 28,
    "text": "Wherefore we receiving a kingdom which cannot be moved, let us have grace, whereby we may serve God acceptably with reverence and godly fear:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 29,
    "text": "For our God\nis a consuming fire."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "Let brotherly love continue."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "Be not forgetful to entertain strangers: for thereby some have entertained angels unawares."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "Remember them that are in bonds, as bound with them;\nand them which suffer adversity, as being yourselves also in the body."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "Marriage\nis honourable in all, and the bed undefiled: but whoremongers and adulterers God will judge."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "Let your conversation\nbe without covetousness;\nand be content with such things as ye have: for he hath said, I will never leave thee, nor forsake thee."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "So that we may boldly say, The Lord\nis my helper, and I will not fear what man shall do unto me."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "Remember them which have the rule over you, who have spoken unto you the word of God: whose faith follow, considering the end of\ntheir conversation."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "Jesus Christ the same yesterday, and to day, and for ever."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "Be not carried about with divers and strange doctrines. For\nit is\n a good thing that the heart be established with grace; not with meats, which have not profited them that have been occupied therein."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "We have an altar, whereof they have no right to eat which serve the tabernacle."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "For the bodies of those beasts, whose blood is brought into the sanctuary by the high priest for sin, are burned without the camp."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "Wherefore Jesus also, that he might sanctify the people with his own blood, suffered without the gate."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "Let us go forth therefore unto him without the camp, bearing his reproach."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "For here have we no continuing city, but we seek one to come."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "By him therefore let us offer the sacrifice of praise to God continually, that is, the fruit of\nour lips giving thanks to his name."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "But to do good and to communicate forget not: for with such sacrifices God is well pleased."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "Obey them that have the rule over you, and submit yourselves: for they watch for your souls, as they that must give account, that they may do it with joy, and not with grief: for that\nis unprofitable for you."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "Pray for us: for we trust we have a good conscience, in all things willing to live honestly."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "But I beseech\nyou the rather to do this, that I may be restored to you the sooner."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "Now the God of peace, that brought again from the dead our Lord Jesus, that great shepherd of the sheep, through the blood of the everlasting covenant,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "Make you perfect in every good work to do his will, working in you that which is wellpleasing in his sight, through Jesus Christ; to whom\nbe\n glory for ever and ever. Amen."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "And I beseech you, brethren, suffer the word of exhortation: for I have written a letter unto you in few words."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "Know ye that\nour brother Timothy is set at liberty; with whom, if he come shortly, I will see you."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "Salute all them that have the rule over you, and all the saints. They of Italy salute you."
  },
  {
    "book": "Hebrews",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 25,
    "text": "Grace\nbe with you all. Amen."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "James, a servant of God and of the Lord Jesus Christ, to the twelve tribes which are scattered abroad, greeting."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "My brethren, count it all joy when ye fall into divers temptations;"
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "Knowing\nthis, that the trying of your faith worketh patience."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "But let patience have\nher perfect work, that ye may be perfect and entire, wanting nothing."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "If any of you lack wisdom, let him ask of God, that giveth to all\nmen liberally, and upbraideth not; and it shall be given him."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "But let him ask in faith, nothing wavering. For he that wavereth is like a wave of the sea driven with the wind and tossed."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "For let not that man think that he shall receive any thing of the Lord."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "A double minded man\nis unstable in all his ways."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "Let the brother of low degree rejoice in that he is exalted:"
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "But the rich, in that he is made low: because as the flower of the grass he shall pass away."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "For the sun is no sooner risen with a burning heat, but it withereth the grass, and the flower thereof falleth, and the grace of the fashion of it perisheth: so also shall the rich man fade away in his ways."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "Blessed\nis the man that endureth temptation: for when he is tried, he shall receive the crown of life, which the Lord hath promised to them that love him."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "Let no man say when he is tempted, I am tempted of God: for God cannot be tempted with evil, neither tempteth he any man:"
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "But every man is tempted, when he is drawn away of his own lust, and enticed."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "Then when lust hath conceived, it bringeth forth sin: and sin, when it is finished, bringeth forth death."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "Do not err, my beloved brethren."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "Every good gift and every perfect gift is from above, and cometh down from the Father of lights, with whom is no variableness, neither shadow of turning."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "Of his own will begat he us with the word of truth, that we should be a kind of firstfruits of his creatures."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "Wherefore, my beloved brethren, let every man be swift to hear, slow to speak, slow to wrath:"
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "For the wrath of man worketh not the righteousness of God."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "Wherefore lay apart all filthiness and superfluity of naughtiness, and receive with meekness the engrafted word, which is able to save your souls."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "But be ye doers of the word, and not hearers only, deceiving your own selves."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "For if any be a hearer of the word, and not a doer, he is like unto a man beholding his natural face in a glass:"
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "For he beholdeth himself, and goeth his way, and straightway forgetteth what manner of man he was."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 25,
    "text": "But whoso looketh into the perfect law of liberty, and continueth\ntherein, he being not a forgetful hearer, but a doer of the work, this man shall be blessed in his deed."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 26,
    "text": "If any man among you seem to be religious, and bridleth not his tongue, but deceiveth his own heart, this man’s religion\nis vain."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 27,
    "text": "Pure religion and undefiled before God and the Father is this, To visit the fatherless and widows in their affliction,\nand to keep himself unspotted from the world."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "My brethren, have not the faith of our Lord Jesus Christ,\nthe Lord\n of glory, with respect of persons."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "For if there come unto your assembly a man with a gold ring, in goodly apparel, and there come in also a poor man in vile raiment;"
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "And ye have respect to him that weareth the gay clothing, and say unto him, Sit thou here in a good place; and say to the poor, Stand thou there, or sit here under my footstool:"
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "Are ye not then partial in yourselves, and are become judges of evil thoughts?"
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "Hearken, my beloved brethren, Hath not God chosen the poor of this world rich in faith, and heirs of the kingdom which he hath promised to them that love him?"
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "But ye have despised the poor. Do not rich men oppress you, and draw you before the judgment seats?"
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "Do not they blaspheme that worthy name by the which ye are called?"
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "If ye fulfil the royal law according to the scripture, Thou shalt love thy neighbour as thyself, ye do well:"
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "But if ye have respect to persons, ye commit sin, and are convinced of the law as transgressors."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "For whosoever shall keep the whole law, and yet offend in one\npoint, he is guilty of all."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "For he that said, Do not commit adultery, said also, Do not kill. Now if thou commit no adultery, yet if thou kill, thou art become a transgressor of the law."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "So speak ye, and so do, as they that shall be judged by the law of liberty."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "For he shall have judgment without mercy, that hath shewed no mercy; and mercy rejoiceth against judgment."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "What\ndoth it profit, my brethren, though a man say he hath faith, and have not works? can faith save him?"
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "If a brother or sister be naked, and destitute of daily food,"
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "And one of you say unto them, Depart in peace, be ye warmed and filled; notwithstanding ye give them not those things which are needful to the body; what\ndoth it profit?"
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "Even so faith, if it hath not works, is dead, being alone."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "Yea, a man may say, Thou hast faith, and I have works: shew me thy faith without thy works, and I will shew thee my faith by my works."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "Thou believest that there is one God; thou doest well: the devils also believe, and tremble."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "But wilt thou know, O vain man, that faith without works is dead?"
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "Was not Abraham our father justified by works, when he had offered Isaac his son upon the altar?"
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "Seest thou how faith wrought with his works, and by works was faith made perfect?"
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "And the scripture was fulfilled which saith, Abraham believed God, and it was imputed unto him for righteousness: and he was called the Friend of God."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "Ye see then how that by works a man is justified, and not by faith only."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 25,
    "text": "Likewise also was not Rahab the harlot justified by works, when she had received the messengers, and had sent\nthem out another way?"
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 26,
    "text": "For as the body without the spirit is dead, so faith without works is dead also."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "My brethren, be not many masters, knowing that we shall receive the greater condemnation."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "For in many things we offend all. If any man offend not in word, the same\nis a perfect man,\nand able also to bridle the whole body."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "Behold, we put bits in the horses’ mouths, that they may obey us; and we turn about their whole body."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "Behold also the ships, which though\nthey be so great, and\nare driven of fierce winds, yet are they turned about with a very small helm, whithersoever the governor listeth."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "Even so the tongue is a little member, and boasteth great things. Behold, how great a matter a little fire kindleth!"
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "And the tongue\nis a fire, a world of iniquity: so is the tongue among our members, that it defileth the whole body, and setteth on fire the course of nature; and it is set on fire of hell."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "For every kind of beasts, and of birds, and of serpents, and of things in the sea, is tamed, and hath been tamed of mankind:"
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "But the tongue can no man tame;\nit is an unruly evil, full of deadly poison."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "Therewith bless we God, even the Father; and therewith curse we men, which are made after the similitude of God."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "Out of the same mouth proceedeth blessing and cursing. My brethren, these things ought not so to be."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "Doth a fountain send forth at the same place sweet\nwater\n and bitter?"
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "Can the fig tree, my brethren, bear olive berries? either a vine, figs? so\ncan no fountain both yield salt water and fresh."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "Who\nis a wise man and endued with knowledge among you? let him shew out of a good conversation his works with meekness of wisdom."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "But if ye have bitter envying and strife in your hearts, glory not, and lie not against the truth."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "This wisdom descendeth not from above, but\nis earthly, sensual, devilish."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "For where envying and strife\nis, there\nis confusion and every evil work."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "But the wisdom that is from above is first pure, then peaceable, gentle,\nand easy to be intreated, full of mercy and good fruits, without partiality, and without hypocrisy."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "And the fruit of righteousness is sown in peace of them that make peace."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "From whence\ncome wars and fightings among you?\ncome they\n not hence,\neven of your lusts that war in your members?"
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "Ye lust, and have not: ye kill, and desire to have, and cannot obtain: ye fight and war, yet ye have not, because ye ask not."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "Ye ask, and receive not, because ye ask amiss, that ye may consume\nit upon your lusts."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "Ye adulterers and adulteresses, know ye not that the friendship of the world is enmity with God? whosoever therefore will be a friend of the world is the enemy of God."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "Do ye think that the scripture saith in vain, The spirit that dwelleth in us lusteth to envy?"
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "But he giveth more grace. Wherefore he saith, God resisteth the proud, but giveth grace unto the humble."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "Submit yourselves therefore to God. Resist the devil, and he will flee from you."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "Draw nigh to God, and he will draw nigh to you. Cleanse\nyour\n hands,\nye sinners; and purify\nyour hearts,\nye double minded."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "Be afflicted, and mourn, and weep: let your laughter be turned to mourning, and\nyour joy to heaviness."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "Humble yourselves in the sight of the Lord, and he shall lift you up."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "Speak not evil one of another, brethren. He that speaketh evil of\nhis brother, and judgeth his brother, speaketh evil of the law, and judgeth the law: but if thou judge the law, thou art not a doer of the law, but a judge."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "There is one lawgiver, who is able to save and to destroy: who art thou that judgest another?"
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "Go to now, ye that say, To day or to morrow we will go into such a city, and continue there a year, and buy and sell, and get gain:"
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "Whereas ye know not what\nshall be on the morrow. For what\nis your life? It is even a vapour, that appeareth for a little time, and then vanisheth away."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "For that ye\nought to say, If the Lord will, we shall live, and do this, or that."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "But now ye rejoice in your boastings: all such rejoicing is evil."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "Therefore to him that knoweth to do good, and doeth\nit not, to him it is sin."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "Go to now,\nye rich men, weep and howl for your miseries that shall come upon\nyou."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "Your riches are corrupted, and your garments are motheaten."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "Your gold and silver is cankered; and the rust of them shall be a witness against you, and shall eat your flesh as it were fire. Ye have heaped treasure together for the last days."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "Behold, the hire of the labourers who have reaped down your fields, which is of you kept back by fraud, crieth: and the cries of them which have reaped are entered into the ears of the Lord of sabaoth."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "Ye have lived in pleasure on the earth, and been wanton; ye have nourished your hearts, as in a day of slaughter."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "Ye have condemned\nand killed the just;\nand he doth not resist you."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "Be patient therefore, brethren, unto the coming of the Lord. Behold, the husbandman waiteth for the precious fruit of the earth, and hath long patience for it, until he receive the early and latter rain."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "Be ye also patient; stablish your hearts: for the coming of the Lord draweth nigh."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "Grudge not one against another, brethren, lest ye be condemned: behold, the judge standeth before the door."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "Take, my brethren, the prophets, who have spoken in the name of the Lord, for an example of suffering affliction, and of patience."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "Behold, we count them happy which endure. Ye have heard of the patience of Job, and have seen the end of the Lord; that the Lord is very pitiful, and of tender mercy."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "But above all things, my brethren, swear not, neither by heaven, neither by the earth, neither by any other oath: but let your yea be yea; and\nyour nay, nay; lest ye fall into condemnation."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "Is any among you afflicted? let him pray. Is any merry? let him sing psalms."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "Is any sick among you? let him call for the elders of the church; and let them pray over him, anointing him with oil in the name of the Lord:"
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "And the prayer of faith shall save the sick, and the Lord shall raise him up; and if he have committed sins, they shall be forgiven him."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "Confess\nyour faults one to another, and pray one for another, that ye may be healed. The effectual fervent prayer of a righteous man availeth much."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "Elias was a man subject to like passions as we are, and he prayed earnestly that it might not rain: and it rained not on the earth by the space of three years and six months."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "And he prayed again, and the heaven gave rain, and the earth brought forth her fruit."
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "Brethren, if any of you do err from the truth, and one convert him;"
  },
  {
    "book": "James",
    "chapter": 5,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "Let him know, that he which converteth the sinner from the error of his way shall save a soul from death, and shall hide a multitude of sins."
  },
  {
    "book": "1 Peter",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "Peter, an apostle of Jesus Christ, to the strangers scattered throughout Pontus, Galatia, Cappadocia, Asia, and Bithynia,"
  },
  {
